window.__CPDS_INDEX__={"chapters":{"1":"All Bible scholars are wisdom deficient","2":"God planned every step of creation","3":"God created Christian conflict","4":"My introduction to this book","5":"The importance of Bible school education","6":"The dispensations reported in Scripture","7":"God had a Purpose for Creation","8":"God's purpose was deliberately hidden","9":"Critical definitions and distinctions","10":"The philosophical basis for this book","11":"The Biblical justification for this book","12":"The rationale of God's plan","13":"The conclusion of this book","0":"Dedication"},"paras":[{"c":1,"i":0,"x":"No one wants to be wisdom deficient but 1 Kings 4:29-34 reports God gifting Solomon with wisdom that exceeds the wisdom of “all men.” God even reports the names of a few wise men who were divinely replaced when God gifted Solomon."},{"c":1,"i":1,"x":"See also the web site biblehub.com/q/Why_are_the_men_in_1_Kings_4_31_important.html. The two wise men whom God identified by name may have been from the same class of intellectual \"Wise Men\" who later traveled to Bethlehem to worship the new-born infant Jesus."},{"c":1,"i":2,"x":"Despite all that, 1 Kings 11 was inspired by God to report the wisest man in the world egotistically abusing God’s gift of wisdom such that the gift of wisdom and the gift of great wealth was used sinfully. Solomon finally admitted his sinful ways by the Eccleasties 1:2ff statement “Vanity of vanities, saith the Preacher, all is vanity” and concluding his admission of sin by the Eccleasties 12:13-14 statement “Let us hear the conclusion of the whole matter: Fear God and keep his commandments: for this is the whole duty of man. For God shall bring every work into judgment, with every secret thing, whether it be good, or whether it be evil.” That seems to be Solomon’s basis for the wise commanded issued in Proverbs 3:5-6 “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding. In all thy ways acknowledge Him and He shall direct thy path.” But Solomon’s wise instruction is rejected by wisdom deficient “pastor teachers” who were trained by wisdom deficient Bible school professors to “lean unto thine own sectarian understandings” to hermeneutically manufacture belief systems intended to theologically explain God’s inspired Words."},{"c":1,"i":3,"x":"It is a “mystery” that is difficult for wisdom deficient humans to \"understand\" but God intended for “all men” to be conflicted by creating an environment containing “the god of this world” and “evil” and “death” and then declaring in Genesis 1:31 “behold, it was very good.” God’s Purpose-For-Creation was deliberately hidden from humans simply because every God beliiver, including me and you as well as Adam and Eve, would strenulously object to any Purpose that included the crucifixion of “the LORD of Glory” predicted by God in 1Corinthians 2:8."},{"c":1,"i":4,"x":"The reality is that a DNA having a high IQ is distinct from God’s gracious gift of wisdom. For example, I literally heard a wisdom deficient high IQ “pastor teacher” publicly read 2Peter 1:8 from his pulpit “For if these things be in you, and abound, they make you that ye shall neither be barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ” followed by his wisdom deficient “understanding” that “giving all diligence to believe” is required before an omnipotent God can fulfil His 2Peter 1:4 “promise that by these ye might be partakers of the divine nature, having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust.” God believing but wisdom deficient “pastor teachers” are preaching their opinionated assumptions about that which God really intended to say."},{"c":1,"i":5,"x":"That high IQ but wisdom deficient “pastor teacher leans unto his own understanding” to teach that John 3:16 requires “whosoever to believe in Him” before “whosoever” can be “born again of the Spirit” even though the Apostle John was reporting Jesus answering a question by Niccodemus about “entering the second time into his mother’s womb to be born?” Jesus accused Niccodemus of being “a ruler of the Jews” who didn’t seem to know the John 3:6 axiom “that which is born of the Flesh is Flesh, and that which is born of the Spirit is Spirit.” But God’s inspired Words in John 3 literally teach “whosoever” that “salvation is by grace through faith that is not your own effort lest you should be tempted to boast” as reported in Ephesians 2:8-9. Wisdom deficient “pastor teachers” require “belief in Him” by those who are “Spiritually dead in sin and thus incapable of believing anything.” Wisdom deficient “pastor teachers” proof text John 3:16 to teach that God requires “belief” before a sovereign and omnipotent God can “predestine dead in trespasses and sin” humans to no longer be “dead” by receiving the gift of “everlasting life” as the guaranteed outcome of being “born again of the Spirit.”"},{"c":1,"i":6,"x":"Miriam-Webster.COM defines “proof text” as “a Scriptural passage adduced as proof for a theological doctrine, belief, or principle.” Thus, that wisdom deficient “pastor teacher” has “adduced a Scriptural passage” to mean something that literally conflicts with the answer by “God’s only beloved Son” to the question asked by “Niccodemus.”"},{"c":1,"i":7,"x":"Wisdom deficient preaching is always “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture.” That’s why the philosophical basis for this book is WHY > WHAT."},{"c":1,"i":8,"x":"The Christian religion is characterized by sectarian affiliations and denominations which conflict with each of their sectarian rivals. Even so-called “Independent” churches affiliate to conflict with rival “Independent” churches."},{"c":1,"i":9,"x":"But the mere existence of sectarian conflict forces me to question WHY a sovereign God created anything at all when He omnisciently knew wisdom deficient sectarian Bible scholars were going to “lean unto their own understanding” to persuade church attendees to “trust” a conflicted sectarian belief system “with all their heart” even though ALL sectarian belief systems conflict with rival sectarian belief systems?"},{"c":1,"i":10,"x":"The text of Romans 12:3 “commands” us to “not think of ourselves more highly than we ought to think.” But every wisdom deficient Bible scholar “thinks” his own “understanding” is superior to the “understanding” of every rival Bible scholar."},{"c":1,"i":11,"x":"It is axiomatic that knowing WHY anything happens always yields more “understanding” than any opinionated knowledge about WHAT may have happened. In other words, WHY > WHAT."},{"c":1,"i":12,"x":"For example, USA Judges tend to sentence criminals based on WHY a crime was committed despite WHAT crime is being judged. Similarly, wisdom deficient Bible scholars ignore the axiom by “leaning unto their own understanding” about WHAT God really meant to say rather than asking WHY God said anything at all. Bible scholars are observed “Trusting their own understandings” about WHAT God may have inspired to be written even when those “understandings” conflict with the “understandings” of rival Bible scholars."},{"c":1,"i":13,"x":"Ephesians 4:11 teaches “God gifts pastor teachers to the saints till we all come in the unity of the faith.” However, “church attending saints” have never been “unified” since Acts 9:15 when Saul was divinely appointed as an Apostle “to bear my name before the Gentiles, and kings, and the children of Israel.” 1Corinthians 1:10ff is irrefutable evidence that “church attending saints” have never been “unified in the faith.” It is reality that every conflicted sectarian doctrine was hermeneutically manufactured by wisdom deficient Bible scholars who claim to “Trust in the LORD with all their heart.” That wisdom deficient claim was “predestined” by “the determinant counsel and foreknowledge of God” (Acts 2:23) “from before the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8). God deliberately hid His Purpose from God believers."},{"c":1,"i":14,"x":"Conflicted belief systems are taught by sectarian Bible school professors who were not given enough wisdom to recognize their own wisdom deficiency."},{"c":1,"i":15,"x":"Genesis 2:9 reports both “good and evil” Bible scholars are avatars of “The tree of the knowledge of good and evil.” The cause-and-effect of time-and-space has resulted in modern Bible scholars being wisdom deficient just as Adam and Eve were deliberately \"made\" by an omniscient and immutable (i.e., unchanging) God to be wisdom deficient."},{"c":1,"i":16,"x":"It is intuitively obvious that only humans are capable of sin. Germs and animals are never guilty of sin even when they kill and eat humans. Romans 3:23 teaches “all have sinned and come short of the glory of God.” That verse also describes Adam and Eve. Despite Romans 3:23, modern wisdom deficient Bible scholars teach that Adam and Eve were created to be sinless before Eve was tempted by Satan to sin. In other words, modern wisdom deficient Bible scholars teach the incredible doctrine that an immutable God changed His immutable mind because “the god of this world” whom an immutable God had previously created had literally obeyed Creator God by tempting Eve to sin. That kind of teaching is obviously completely wisdom deficient."},{"c":1,"i":17,"x":"Some Bible schools deliberately choose to be unaccredited, but accreditation never fixes non-Biblical hermeneutics. Despite accreditation, every Bible school teaches hermeneutical rules which conflict with the hermeneutical rules taught in rival Bible schools. Without exception Bible schools justify their belief systems by hermeneutically “leaning unto sectarian understandings” about WHAT God really meant to say rather than teach WHY an immutable God said anything at all."},{"c":1,"i":18,"x":"Your own conflicted “understandings” are always “Trusted with all your heart” to be Scripturally correct despite conflicting with all sectarian rivals. Sectarian conflict always indicates an “understanding” which is a hermeneutical interpretation (i.e., an opinion) about WHAT God really meant to say rather than “Trusting” an exposition of WHY an omniscient God literally inspired anything to be written."},{"c":1,"i":19,"x":"Merriam-webster.com defines “hermeneutics” as “the study of the methodological principles of interpretation (as of the Bible).” Without exception your own hermeneutical “understanding” methodically conflicts with rival hermeneutical “understandings.”"},{"c":1,"i":20,"x":"And yet an omniscient God declares that all creation was “very good” exactly as He intended because everything was created to accomplish God’s Purpose-For-Creation. An immutable God knew exactly what He was doing. An omniscient and immutable God deliberately created universal “Wars and rumors of war” (Matt 24:6) . Your own Bible school trained “pastor teacher” has learned a conflicted version of sectarian belief because an omniscient and immutable God intends for all Bible schools to teach proficiency in sectarian (i.e., conflicted) hermeneutics rather than teach proficient methods for “rightly dividing” (2Tim 2:15) the context of WHAT an omniscient and immutable God literally inspired to be written. Bible schools never major on “the things that thou hast heard of me, the same commit thou to faithful men, who shall be able to teach others also” (2Tim 2:2)."},{"c":1,"i":21,"x":"Even Bible schools that are famous for promoting an expositional preaching style are observed hermeneutically “understanding” doctrines which conflict with rival Bible school hermeneutical “understandings.” Every hermeneutical “understanding” reflects a sectarian opinion about WHAT God really meant to say."},{"c":1,"i":22,"x":"The title of this book is Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. The outcome of that kind of preaching is always the establishment and maintenance of conflicted affiliations of sectarian churches. The book title describes every instance when a “pastor teacher” applies a hermeneutically interpreted Biblical proof-text. And yet an omniscient God includes Christian preaching that devalues Scripture when God evaluates everything He has created as being “very good” simply because without exception everything was created exactly as Creator God intended."},{"c":1,"i":23,"x":"Without exception every instance of theological conflict is the outcome of a wisdom deficient hermeneutical opinion about WHY God created anything. And conflicted opinions (i.e., “understandings”) about WHY God created anything are always derived from a hermeneutical analysis of WHAT God literally said that He did."},{"c":1,"i":24,"x":"However, the context of Isaiah 48:6 teaches that God’s inspired Words were deliberately “hidden” from God’s chosen people. Similarly, the inspired context of Ephesians 3:3-9 teaches that God’s Purpose-For-Creation was intended to be “hidden” from everyone until AD60 when God inspired the Epistle to the Ephesians."},{"c":1,"i":25,"x":"Sectarian conflict is proof that God’s Purpose-For-Creation was especially “hidden” from Bible school professors. The alternative to “leaning unto thine own understanding” is always “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart” that an omniscient God immutably knew “before the foundation of the world” the reason WHY He created anything at all including the reason WHY an omniscient God “predestined” Adam and Eve to “lustfully sin” (Gen 3:6 and James 1:14-15) so they could be evicted from the Garden of Eden."},{"c":1,"i":26,"x":"It is conceivable that some sectarian opinions approach being consistent with God’s Purpose-For-Creation. However, every “born of the flesh” human (John 3:6) is temporary and disposable being deliberately “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment” (Heb 9:27). Thus, everyone who is “born of the flesh” is eternally precluded from knowing the reason WHY God created anything at all unless an omniscient God deliberately chooses to inform everyone the reason WHY anything was created. WHY God created anything is always more informative than any hermeneutical opinion about WHAT God did or any opinion about WHAT God expects you and me to do. “Leaning unto thine own understanding” is the reason WHY you and I are characterized by conflict with every sectarian rival who claims to be a God believer."},{"c":1,"i":27,"x":"That conclusion results from observing the Christian religion as a marketing agency for persuading and selling conflicted sectarian belief systems. The philosophical axiom is WHY > WHAT. Please meditate on that philosophical axiom as it applies to your preferred sectarian system of conflicted beliefs."},{"c":1,"i":28,"x":"Your preferred Bible scholar never cites Scripture to explain WHY a sovereign and omniscient God allows your own sectarian belief system to conflict with rival belief systems. Ephesians 3:3 & 3:9 reports a sovereign God “mysteriously hid” that knowledge from virtually everyone before AD60 when the epistle to the Ephesians was inspired to be written. Nevertheless, each conflicted belief system was included in God’s Genesis 1:31 evaluation that all creation was “very good” exactly as God intended it to be. The reality is that God created sectarian conflict “to the intent that” God’s Purpose-For-Creation will be fulfilled without risking sabotage (1Cor 2:8)."},{"c":1,"i":29,"x":"Some wisdom deficient Bible scholars teach that an immutable God changes His mind after “dead in trespasses and sin humans” have been persuaded to make volitional-free-will decisions to no longer be “dead.” Yet an omniscient God asserts in Genesis 1:31 that every free-will decision made by “dead humans” is “very good” simply because invalid assumptions about volitional-free-will are exactly what God intended when God omnisciently created temporary and disposable humans “who are dead in trespasses and sin” (Eph 2:1)."},{"c":1,"i":30,"x":"I have literally heard wisdom deficient Bible scholars “leaning unto their own understanding” about WHAT God said He did so they could teach that God did everything “for His own Glory.” God’s inspired Words teach that God is Glorious. Nevertheless, Bible scholars ignore Ephesians 4:11ff that God gifts “the saints with pastor teachers till we all come in the unity of the faith.” Every Bible school teaches homiletics that literally prevent “church attending saints from ever being unified.”"},{"c":1,"i":31,"x":"“Trusting in the LORD with all thine heart” will immediately fix the conflict that characterizes your own wisdom deficient sectarian belief system. However, “Trusting in the LORD with all thine heart” is the outcome rather than the reason anyone is “born again of the Spirit.” “Dead in trespasses and sin” humans are “mysteriously called and elect” to salvation (2Pet 1:10). Those names were “written in the Lamb’s book of life before the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8), (i.e., before believing was possible)."},{"c":1,"i":32,"x":"The fact is that “The Lamb’s book of life” was written “before the foundation of the world.” God DID NOT create anything so that sinful humans could “come in the unity of the faith.” God’s own inspired Words inform us in Isaiah 6:10 and Matthew 13:11ff that NEITHER God NOR Jesus intends for EVERY human to “come in the unity of the faith and the knowledge of the Son of God.” And yet an omniscient God declared in Genesis 1:31 that God’s “command” to Isaiah was “very good” despite God’s “commands” contradicting your own wisdom deficient sectarian opinion."},{"c":1,"i":33,"x":"The fact that God DOES NOT WANT EVERY human to “come in the unity of the faith” has always been a “mystery” for wisdom deficient “pastor teachers” who have been religiously taught that 2Peter 3:9 is proof-text teaching that God is “not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.” If a sovereign God really WANTED EVERY human to repent and be saved then that’s exactly the way it would happen."},{"c":1,"i":34,"x":"However, that incorrect “understanding” of 2Peter 3:9 is literary nonsense simply because wisdom deficient “pastor teachers” are being taught to ignore that 2Peter is written “to them that have obtained like precious faith with us through the righteousness of God and our Saviour Jesus Christ” (2Pet 1:1)."},{"c":1,"i":35,"x":"Peter’s 2nd Epistle teaches that God deliberately limits His “faithful promise” of “calling and election” to the “few who enter at the narrow gate” (Matt 7:14) simply because “the Lord is not slack concerning his promise <to the called and elect> as some men such as the Scoffers who are identified in 2Peter 3:4 count slackness but is longsuffering to us <who are called and elect>, not willing that any <of us who are called and elect> should perish, but that all <who are called and elect> should come to repentance” (this editing is dependent on the literal context of 2Peter 3:9)."},{"c":1,"i":36,"x":"Incidentally, Matthew 7:13-23 of The Sermon on the Mount reports that “many who address Jesus as LORD” will be told to “depart from me, ye that work iniquity.” The incredible reality is that “many” Bible school trained “pastor teachers” will not be allowed to enter Heaven. That incredible reality contradicts “many wisdom deficient understandings” of that which a sovereign God inspired to be written."},{"c":1,"i":37,"x":"Those same wisdom deficient Bible scholars incorrectly proof-text John 3:16 to read “For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that <any dead person who has been intellectually persuaded to> believeth in him should not perish but have everlasting life.” That proof-text is literary nonsense simply because every human “dies and perishes” just as an immutable (i.e., unchangeable) God intended when God “predestined Adam and Eve to be sinners” who were both “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment” (Heb 9:27). That reality is specifically and intentionally confirmed in Ephesians 2:8-9 simply because the intellectual “work” of “believing in him” has never saved anyone. Salvation has always been “the gift of God. Not of works, lest any man who is dead in trespasses and sin should boast.” According to merriam-webster.com every “proof-text” is “a Scriptural passage adduced as proof for a theological doctrine, belief, or principle.” Thus, every “proof-text” is merely your own wisdom deficient attempt to “adduce” a hermeneutical “understanding” about that which an immutable God really intended to say if only He had stopped for a moment to think about what He said."},{"c":1,"i":38,"x":"The Scriptural alternative to every wisdom deficient “proof-text” is to “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding. In all thy ways acknowledge him, and He shall direct thy paths” (Prov 3:5-6)."},{"c":1,"i":39,"x":"Conflict with rival sectarian opinions is proof that your own wisdom deficient sectarian methods for hermeneutically interpreting (i.e., altering) God’s immutable Words is evidence that you “lean unto your own understanding.”"},{"c":1,"i":40,"x":"Please meditate on the Scriptural command to “lean not unto thine own understanding” (Prov 3:5). Did “the LORD” really inspire Solomon to command every human including both me and you to “lean not unto thine own understanding”?"},{"c":1,"i":41,"x":"The outcome of “rightly dividing the Word of Truth” is never an interpretation of Scripture which conflicts with rival interpretations."},{"c":1,"i":42,"x":"In the past I interpreted Proverbs 3:5 consistent with sectarian doctrinal beliefs. More recently I was led by God’s Spirit to “Study to shew myself approved unto God, a workman that needeth not to be ashamed, rightly dividing the word of truth” (2Tim 2:15). That kind of study led me to write this book about Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. I finally discovered that thousands of years ago in AD60 God finally inspired His Purpose-For-Creation to be revealed in Ephesians 3:10."},{"c":1,"i":43,"x":"That “Study” taught me to “Trust in the LORD with all my heart” about the reason WHY God created anything “to the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known by the church the manifold wisdom of God” (Eph 3:10)."},{"c":1,"i":44,"x":"Please be aware that Ephesians 3:10 specifically ignores any so-called “Great Commission” for either establishing or maintaining “the church” simply because Jesus said in Matthew 16:18 that “He would build His church and the gates of hell would not prevail against it.” Please affirm that the “Great Commission” at the end of Matthew 28 was specifically directed to only “eleven” disciples so that Jesus could divinely command them to “Teach them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you.” Disciples other that the “eleven” were taught only “some things.”"},{"c":1,"i":45,"x":"It ought to be intuitively obvious that Matthew 28 has absolutely nothing to do with either “winning souls” (Prov 11:30) or establishing and maintaining “churches.” So, WHY do wisdom deficient “pastor teachers” teach otherwise? That reality contradicts the belief systems taught in Bible schools. The reality is that God’s Ephesians 3:10 Purpose-For-Creation completely ignores all temporary and disposable “dead in trespasses and sin” humans except as they assemble together into a conflicted sectarian “church” (i.e., an “ἐκκλησία”)."},{"c":1,"i":46,"x":"Some of the “born of the flesh” humans who assemble together into an “ἐκκλησία” were named in “the Lamb’s book of life before the foundation of the world” but the names of “ἐκκλησία” groupies have always been notably missing from “the Lamb’s book of life from the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":1,"i":47,"x":"The remainder of this book is my analysis of God’s Purpose-For-Creation with respect to “the church” which “mysteriously” was not even hinted when “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.”"},{"c":1,"i":48,"x":"WHY did God wait until AD60 to inspire the Apostle Paul to write the epistle to the Ephesians that describes God’s purpose for “the church”?"},{"c":1,"i":49,"x":"WHY didn’t God tell everyone about His purpose for “the church” when “in the beginning” God was creating everything including a “sinful” Adam and Eve who volitionally “lusted after” food that was provided by a God who is “good all the time; all the time, God is good”?"},{"c":1,"i":50,"x":"Nevertheless, it is intuitively obvious that God deliberately created temporary and disposable humans to be wisdom deficient. The religious leaders of “God’s chosen people” as well as Satan and his demons were denied knowledge about God’s Purpose-For-Creation because “none of the princes of this world knew: for had they known it, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory” (1Cor 2:8). The “crucifixion of the Lord of glory” had always been God’s Purpose-For-Creation “from before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":1,"i":51,"x":"The reality is that no one who claims to be “born again of the Spirit” would ever vote to “crucify the Lord of glory.” And yet the crucifixion of “the Lord of glory” is exactly what God intended when He created everything consistent with His Ephesians 3:10 Purpose Statement. That’s the reason WHY an omniscient God had to “hide the mystery” from everyone until after Jesus had been crucified and until after “the church” had been established by the Apostle Paul. Otherwise, “the Lord of glory” would have never been crucified simply because every God believer would have voted against it."},{"c":1,"i":52,"x":"You and I and every other human who is “born again of the Spirt” (John 3:6) would have sabotaged God’s Purpose-For-Creation by voting against the crucifixion of “the Lord of glory.” Please meditate on that painful reality as you continue reading."},{"c":2,"i":0,"x":"Genesis 1:1 summarizes God’s creative effort as “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.” Creation was completed in six days after which God evaluated all His creative effort in Genesis 1:31 as “behold, it was very good” simply because everything was created exactly as God intended. So “God rested on the seventh day.”"},{"c":2,"i":1,"x":"Bible scholars “lean unto their own wisdom deficient understandings” to manufacture conflicted opinions about why God created anything at all. Those opinions always conflict with the opinions of rival Bible scholars. Following is an exposition of the inspired account of what God literally created. The Genesis account was inspired by a sovereign God when He omnisciently and immutably created everything ex nihilo (i.e., “out of nothing”). True exposition is always “Trusting the LORD with all your heart.” True exposition is never a conflicted “understanding.”"},{"c":2,"i":2,"x":"A summary of Day 1 is reported in Genesis 1:1-5."},{"c":2,"i":3,"x":"God initialized Creation to be “without form, and void.” Tangible things are never “without form, and void” and yet in Genesis 1:4 God saw that everything “was good” simply because beeing without form and void was exactly what God planned to happen."},{"c":2,"i":4,"x":"These verses are a summary rather than a detail description as indicated by vague and imprecise Hebrew words. For example, “the first day” of God’s Creation is vague and imprecisely delimited by “evening and morning” even though the Earth, Sun, and Moon do not yet exist."},{"c":2,"i":5,"x":"Some wisdom deficient Bible scholars “understand” this to imply a prior existence of “the earth.” That kind of \"understanding” is often referred to as the so-called “Gap Theory.” Search the web for “Gap Theory” if you are curious about the term. However, the English word “created” was translated from Hebrew with the definition of “a primitive root; (absolute) to create; (qualified) to cut down (a wood), select, feed (as formative processes) :- choose, create (creator), cut down, dispatch, do, make (fat).” Thus, Strong’s Concordance seems to teach that H1254 “absolutely” describes the creation of something that had no prior existence."},{"c":2,"i":6,"x":"These verses also vaguely and imprecisely summarize that “the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters” before “water” or anything else had been created. The reality is that all creation “was without form, and void” prior to “the Spirit of God moving upon the face of the waters.” Accordingly, that statement is vague and imprecise just as we expect from a mere summary."},{"c":2,"i":7,"x":"The English word “water” was translated from Strong's H4325 defined as “dual of a primitive noun (but used in a singular sense); water; figurative juice; by euphemism urine, semen :- + piss, wasting, water (-ing, [-course, -flood, -spring]).” H4325 normally describes H2O. In that regard, verse six will describe the division between “the waters which were under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament.” Thus, water in verse 6 is literal H2O."},{"c":2,"i":8,"x":"This confused usage of “waters” suggests Genesis 1:1-5 summarizes Strong's H4325 to emphasize “the completely void nature of the time-and-space container created in Day 1” by euphemistically comparing “the face of the deep” with raw sewage (i.e., “urine, semen, piss, wasting”). Accordingly, this euphemistic usage of “‫ ”מַ יִם‬ emphasizes that being “without form, and void” suggests a Creation having the same value as raw sewage. It is extremely difficult to “understand” but a God who simply speaks and it instantly happens describes God’s Creation as being initialized with a dimension of “time-and-space” that was completely “without form, and void” even though “the Spirit of God” acted on it sequentially consistent with the “cause-and-effect” intrinsic to “time-and-space.”"},{"c":2,"i":9,"x":"Another indication these verses are merely a summarization is that at least three levels of “heaven” are known to exist. The English word “heaven” in Genesis 1:1 was translated from the Hebrew word \"שָּ מַ יִם” Strong’s H8064) “alluding to the visible arch in which the clouds move, as well as to the higher ether where the celestial bodies revolve.” However, it is intuitive that God did not create the “heaven” where God has eternal residency."},{"c":2,"i":10,"x":"Many who translate Strong’s H8064 into English treat it as a plural noun simply because Strong’s H8064 describes both “the visible arch in which the clouds move as well as the higher ether where all the celestial bodies revolve.” However, neither of those meanings describes “the third heaven” where God eternally resided with the principalities and powers before “the earth” existed. English translators describe the place where God resides as “the third heaven” based on the 2Corinthians 12:2 translation of the Greek noun “τρίτος” (Strong's G5154) “order from <G5140> (treis); third; neuter (as noun) a third part, or (as adverb) a (or the) third time, thirdly :- third (-ly).” The environmental dimension of “The third heaven” has never been described to created humans but that environment is not restricted by either “cause-and-effect” or by “time-and-space.”"},{"c":2,"i":11,"x":"And the Ephesians 3:10 Greek adjective “ἐπουράνιος” (Strong's G2032) is translated into English as “heavenly places” or “the heavenlies” to qualify “the third heaven” where God resides eternally. Strong's definition of G2032 is “from <G1909> (epi) and <G3772> (ouranos); above the sky :- celestial, (in) heaven (-ly), high.” Thus, translators of God’s inspired Words recognize at least three distinct places called “heaven”, but the English language makes no distinction between those three."},{"c":2,"i":12,"x":"The other English term in these verses describing God’s creation is “the earth” which is translated from the Hebrew word “‫”רץ‬ ֶ (Strong’s H776) “from an unused root probably meaning to be firm; the earth (at large, or partitively a land) :- × common, country, earth, field, ground, land, × nations, way, + wilderness, world.”"},{"c":2,"i":13,"x":"It is critically important to notice that verse 1:2 focuses on “the earth” simply because “the earth” is where God’s Purpose-For-Creation will be accomplished rather than being accomplished within either the Universe (i.e., the sky above “the firmament”) or accomplished within “the third heaven” where God resides eternally."},{"c":2,"i":14,"x":"The English word “earth” refers to the entire ball-of-matter where all humans will eventually reside after God’s creative effort is complete. But the summary usage of H776 in Genisis 1-5 makes no attempt to identify the source for the matter God used to insert an “earth” into “the void container.”"},{"c":2,"i":15,"x":"Some wisdom deficient Bible scholars assume matter is eternal even though there is no Scriptural basis for “leaning unto that understanding.” However, I suggest that an omnipotent God’s infinite energy is the source for all the matter that fills “the void time-and-space container” with “the earth” as well as with the stars and galaxies and everything else that exists within the Universe."},{"c":2,"i":16,"x":"“The earth” will eventually be created within the “empty and void container” but the English clause “darkness was upon the face of the deep” suggests the “void container” was initialized to be “completely void” of even the spectrum of electromagnetic energy that will allow human eyes to sense illumination."},{"c":2,"i":17,"x":"This is critical information because the English word “darkness” in Genesis 1:2 was translated from Hebrew “‫( ”חשֶ ך‬Strong’s H2822) “the dark; hence (literal) darkness; figurative misery, destruction, death, ignorance, sorrow, wickedness,- dark (-ness), night, obscurity.” The English word “darkness” is normally used to describe a partial absence of the visible spectrum of electromagnetic energy. However, the term “darkness” in verse 2 seems to describe the contents of an empty container that is completely “void” of everything including the entire spectrum of electromagnetic energy until “the Spirit of God moved upon the wasted face of raw sewage.” Thus, the English word “darkness” in verse 2 describe a condition which is much more descriptive than the mere absence of illumination. “Darkness” in verse 2 describes the contents of an empty container that is completely “void” of everything including all forms of energy."},{"c":2,"i":18,"x":"The English word “upon” or “over” in verse 2 was translated from the Hebrew word “‫ ”עַל‬Strong’s H5921. That Hebrew word qualifies the empty container as having a dimension of time-and-space. This is critical because the English term “moved upon” absolutely requires the length, width, and depth that is intrinsic to time- and-space. Nevertheless, the container was “completely void.”"},{"c":2,"i":19,"x":"The implications of a “completely void” container of time-and-space tends to be ignored by wisdom deficient Bible scholars simply because they assume they were created to have freedom of “movement upon the earth.” Educated Bible scholars display wisdom deficiency whenever volitional free will is discussed."},{"c":2,"i":20,"x":"However, a creation that requires the sequential cause-and-effect which is intrinsic within time-and-space is critical to God’s Purpose-For-Creation simply because every event in “the third Heaven” where God resides eternally is always instantaneous and simultaneous without any dependence on the cause-and-effect of time-and-space."},{"c":2,"i":21,"x":"It is difficult for mere humans to “understand” but both the beginning and ending of Creation has already been observed by all who reside in the heavenlies including “the seraphim” of Isaiah 6:2ff."},{"c":2,"i":22,"x":"Every historic event as well as all future events including the scheduled destruction of the Universe has already been observed “in the heavenlies” exactly as God planned. In other words, everything was “predestined” by a sovereign Creator named God. Absolutely nothing is controlled by volitional free will."},{"c":2,"i":23,"x":"The cause-and-effect that is intrinsic to time-and-space does not exist in “The third Heaven” where God resides. For example, “be not ignorant of this one thing, that one day is with the Lord as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day” (2Pet 3:8). In other words, “The third Heaven” where God resides is always today. It is never yesterday or tomorrow in “The third Heaven.”"},{"c":2,"i":24,"x":"Humans (i.e., me and you) are restricted to a sequential time-and-space. Humans cannot conceive a dimension that allows simultaneous existence anywhere and everywhere. But “the third Heaven” does not have those restrictions. Consequently, a temporary and disposable environment having those restrictions had to be created to accomplish God’s Purpose-For-Creation. The existence of time- and-space is required by every philosophical and scientific statement about motion. In fact, everything in the created universe moves predictably with respect to everything else in the created universe. For example, space travel requires knowing the cause-and-effect of time-and-space by depending on the formula F=M A as described in Newton’s Laws of Motion. Ephesians 1:3 describes this phenomenon as a “mystery” which cannot be “understood” by wisdom deficient humans who have been created to live and die on the surface of a time-and-space earth having the dimensions of length, width, and depth."},{"c":2,"i":25,"x":"Travel on the earth as well as space travel would be impossible if time-and-space was instantaneous and simultaneous rather than controlled by cause-and-effect. Theological assumptions about the existence of Free-Will-decision-making are based on assumptions that “born of the flesh” humans can make Spiritual decisions. But “born of the flesh” humans who have no Spiritual existence before being “born again of the Spirit” are incapable of believing Spiritual Truth. In particular, “born of the flesh” humans cannot be persuaded to “believeth in Him” (John 3:16) before they have been “born again of the Spirit.” “The determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” (Acts 2:23) caused the name of each “born of the flesh” human who has been “called and elect for salvation” to be listed in “the Lamb’s book of life before the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8). It is wisdom deficient to think that a sovereign and omniscient God who omnipotently created everything would allow mere “born of the flesh” humans who are each “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment” (Heb 8:27) to volitionally make decisions about who can and who cannot reside in Heaven with a sovereign God."},{"c":2,"i":26,"x":"The dimension of time-and-space is so embedded in the human psyche that “born of the flesh” humans tend to ignore the dimension controlling every event in “The Third Heaven” where God resides. Humans seem incapable of “understanding” that God eternally exists everywhere and everyplace. The only viable alternative to wisdom deficiency is to “let the LORD direct thy path” (Prov 3:6). But wisdom deficient Bible school trained Biblical scholars prevent that from happening."},{"c":2,"i":27,"x":"With respect to the insertion of “light” into a completely “void” container, the English word “light” in Genesis 1:3 was translated from the Hebrew word “‫”אֹור‬ (Strong’s H216) “from <H215> ('owr); illumination or (concrete) luminary (in every sense, including lightning, happiness, etc.) :- bright, clear, + day, light (-ning), morning, sun.” English usage of the word “light” normally describes a literal existence simply because “light” is measurable. The intensity of “light” is measured using “Lumens” as the measurement scale. By contrast, “darkness” cannot be measured simply because “darkness” does not exist. Thus, “God calling the light Day, and the darkness Night” is merely a summary statement of the way God intends “the earth” to be observed by human eyes which will not exist until day 6."},{"c":2,"i":28,"x":"The English word “light” typically describes the spectrum of electromagnetic energy that is visible to human eyes. But the word “light” in verse 1:3 seems to include ultraviolet light, infrared light, x-rays, and radio frequencies which are also spectrums of electromagnetic energy. Thus, it is intuitive that this initial summarization of God’s creation suggests something which is much more significant than mere illumination."},{"c":2,"i":29,"x":"Wisdom deficient secular scientists insist on speculating about the source of matter. By contrast, I suggest the supernatural electromagnetic energy of an omnipotent Creator God is the source for all matter in The Created Universe."},{"c":2,"i":30,"x":"The English word “Science” assumes observations can be repeated and measured. But humans cannot repeat God’s creation. Thus, human theories (e.g., evolution, the age of the earth, etc.) can never be “scientific” simply because creation cannot be repeated. That’s the reality of Paul’s 1Timothy 6:20 command about “Science falsely so called.” My prayer is that “science falsely so called” does not describe my own speculation reported in this book."},{"c":2,"i":31,"x":"However, Einstein’s formula E=M C2 or E/M=C2 can be repeatably observed creating matter. Search the web for “creation of matter by E=M C2” if you are not familiar with that process. I suggest God’s command “let there be light” is the linguistic basis for the scientific (i.e., repeatable) creation of all matter that exists in the Universe."},{"c":2,"i":32,"x":"I suggest the word “Light” in these Genesis verses refers to the full spectrum of God’s omnipotent electromagnetic energy thus providing the initial value of E in Einstein’s ratio formula E/M=C2. The initial values of both M and C are zero simply because uncooled electron motion is always at the maximum Kelvin temperature."},{"c":2,"i":33,"x":"However, the speed of electron motion decreases as the zero Kelvin temperature of a “void” container is warmed by the maximum Kelvin temperature of God’s infinite energy. As the Kelvin temperature decreases the value of M increases thus eventually producing every atomic element in the Periodic Table."},{"c":2,"i":34,"x":"The variable C in Einstein’s formula is treated as a constant representing the speed of all electromagnetic energy transmissions such as the speed of visible “Light” as well as the speed of invisible radio waves, x-rays, etc. Every decrease in Kelvin temperature increases the value of both C and M until both values approach the stability observed by modern scientists. I suggest that each atomic element in the Periodic Table was created this way. I also observe that cooled atomic elements naturally combine to form molecules. And molecules naturally combine to become the matter within God’s initially “void” time- and-space container which will eventually be identified as “The Universe” by English speaking people."},{"c":2,"i":35,"x":"God’s energy is infinite thus the production of matter is also infinite. However, the Universe was initialized by God to have no size limit. As the Kelvin temperature continues to cool, the black holes in space continue to be filled with newly created matter and the Universe continues expanding."},{"c":2,"i":36,"x":"That is exactly what scientists observe happening today."},{"c":2,"i":37,"x":"My appeal to Einstein’s formula is not intended to imply the validity of my own speculation but rather to suggest a scientifically repeatable process that literally creates matter."},{"c":2,"i":38,"x":"Admittedly, my wisdom deficient appeal to E/M=C2 answers many questions but it probably leaves many other questions unanswered. Nevertheless, I propose this scientifically repeatable argument to refute all the wisdom deficient scholarly assumptions about creation which have resulted in the pervasiveness of Christian preaching that devalues Scripture."},{"c":2,"i":39,"x":"In that regard, I have literally heard wisdom deficient Bible school trained Christian “pastor teachers” state that inspired texts of Scripture are ambiguous and must be clarified (i.e., interpreted) by theologically trained Bible scholars before an omnipotent and omniscient God’s inspired text can be believed and obeyed."},{"c":2,"i":40,"x":"However, if an omnipotent God has the capability to create matter, and if God’s inspired Words scientifically describe the process of creation, then wisdom deficient Theologians foolishly “think of themself more highly than they ought to think” (Rom 12:3). Every human who was created to be wisdom deficient ought to be extremely cautious about critiquing that which an omnipotent and omniscient sovereign God immutably inspired to be written."},{"c":2,"i":41,"x":"Literary critique by wisdom deficient Bible scholars always results in conflicted versions of Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. Yet an omniscient God declares in Genesis 1:31 that wisdom deficient theological conflict is “very good” because God’s Purpose-For-Creation is accomplished by theological conflict."},{"c":2,"i":42,"x":"Despite pervasive conflict between wisdom deficient Bible scholars, our time- and-space Universe continues to expand as the Kelvin temperature of God’s infinite energy continues to cool. A continual cooling of the Universe continues to produce the matter which continues to fill the black holes which continues to expand the size of the Universe. That could explain the reason why our Universe continues to expand. The intriguing comment about “Peleg” in Genesis 10:25 suggests both the Universe and our Earth are much larger now than they were in Genesis 1:1."},{"c":2,"i":43,"x":"The following parenthetic reports that Einstein’s “Theory of Relativity” also predicts that Time is proportional to the Speed of mass. Begin parenthetic about Kelvin temperature WRT time"},{"c":2,"i":44,"x":"Space travel at speeds great enough to escape the force of gravitation"},{"c":2,"i":45,"x":"demonstrate atomic clocks running faster than atomic clocks that remain on"},{"c":2,"i":46,"x":"the surface of the Earth."},{"c":2,"i":47,"x":"That phenomenon suggests a 24-hour day during the initialization of creation"},{"c":2,"i":48,"x":"had a much shorter duration than it has today."},{"c":2,"i":49,"x":"Thus, a cooling Kelvin temperature potentially explains the appearance of a"},{"c":2,"i":50,"x":"decreasing life span until the Biblical standard of “threescore years and ten; and"},{"c":2,"i":51,"x":"if by reason of strength they be fourscore years” (Ps 90:10)."},{"c":2,"i":52,"x":"However, that discussion is beyond the scope of this book. End parenthetic about Kelvin temperature WRT time"},{"c":2,"i":53,"x":"Isaiah 6:2ff describes Isaiah’s vision of “Seraphim” praising God for His Holiness. But “Seraphim” praising God for Holiness is like humans praising God for the availability of breathable air. Humans never praise God for providing breathable air simply because breathable air tends to be unlimited and free of cost on the surface of “the earth” where temporary and disposable humans normally reside."},{"c":2,"i":54,"x":"If we understand “the third heaven” correctly, God’s Holiness was un-worshipped and un-praised prior to “the foundation of the World.” God’s Holiness has always been an unlimited and free commodity in “the third Heaven” so if “Seraphim” are to intelligently worship God’s Holiness, then God must create an environment where the Holiness of God is extremely limited and extremely costly."},{"c":2,"i":55,"x":"In that regard, God’s inspired literature in Ephesians 3:10 reports that creation was “To the intent that, now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known, by the church, the manifold wisdom of God.” The English phrase “To the intent that” identifies Ephesians 3:10 as a Purpose Statement. Thus, Ephesians 3:10 reports the reason why God created anything and everything. In other words, Ephesians 3:10 reports God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":2,"i":56,"x":"God’s inspired Words in Genesis 1:1ff report God creating a temporary and disposable environment (2Peter 3:10) containing two temporary and disposable humans named Adam and Eve who were “appointed once to die and after that the judgement.” Some of the temporary and disposable offspring of Adam and Eve would eventually be “born again of the Spirit” by being “called and elect to salvation.” Both saved and unsaved temporary and disposable humans would eventually assemble together into “churches” to demonstrate “the manifold wisdom of God to the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.” However, humans who are only “born of the flesh” were never “called and elect before the foundation of the world.” Nevertheless, they assemble with “born again believers” thus demonstrating conflict to “the principalities and powers” so they can observe God’s gracious provision of salvation to temporary and disposable humans who were “called and elect to salvation.”"},{"c":2,"i":57,"x":"The conflict between “called and uncalled” temporary and disposable humans demonstrates God’s “manifold wisdom” by providing “the Lamb who was slain before the foundation of the world” so that ”the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” can observe God’s limited and costly Holiness being simultaneously accepted and rejected by conflicted sectarians whom Creator God has assembled together into “churches.” Thus, the time-and-space environment God uses to demonstrate “The Church” is observed “in the heavenlies” to have already been destroyed (2Peter 3:10). The Universe was destroyed simply because it is no longer needed to demonstrate God’s “manifold wisdom in the heavenlies” where both God and “Seraphim” reside."},{"c":2,"i":58,"x":"Admittedly, this is an extremely feeble wisdom deficient speculation about the inscrutable mind of an immutable and omnipotent God. However, my feeble speculation is logically consistent with Ephesians 3:10 where God declares His Purpose was the reason why God created anything and everything."},{"c":2,"i":59,"x":"Nevertheless, wisdom deficient Bible scholars religiously conflict about God’s Purpose-For-Creation. For example, some wisdom deficient Bible scholars speculate that God created you and me “for His own Glory.” No one can question that God is Glorious nor question that God is the embodiment of Love. However, there is no text of Scripture written “To the intent that Creation was motivated by God’s Love.” Every speculation about God’s Purpose (including my own feeble speculation) is “leaning unto your own understanding” rather than “trusting the Lord with all your heart.” But God commands us in Proverbs 3:5 to “lean NOT unto your own understanding.”"},{"c":2,"i":60,"x":"Thus, my feeble speculation as well as your feeble speculation are both judged by God to be “lies” (Rom 3:4). I confess I have a propensity for “sinful lust” (Jas 1:15). You ought to make the same confession. However, typical church-attenders tend to foolishly characterize the religious leaders of their preferred sectarian belief system as being the epitome of truthfulness and righteousness and understanding."},{"c":2,"i":61,"x":"My own speculation is that God inspired Ephesians 3:10 to finally inform us that God has created a sequential time-and-space case study using temporary and disposable humans who were created as the means God uses to demonstrate a rationality for requiring “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” to intellectually worship God for His Holiness even though God’s Holiness cannot be challenged in “the heavenlies” where God and “the principalities and powers” both reside."},{"c":2,"i":62,"x":"God did everything despite wisdom deficient religious leaders claiming to “understand” the “oracles of God.” God’s reaction as reported in Romans 3:4 is to evaluates God-fearing religious leaders as “liars.” It is a harsh but realistic evaluation of religious leaders who will eventually be commanded to “depart from me ye workers of iniquity because I never knew you.”"},{"c":2,"i":63,"x":"Despite the deceitful and incorrect assumptions made by wisdom deficient Bible school educated Biblical scholars, God concludes the initialization of Creation by declaring “And the evening and the morning were the first day.”"},{"c":2,"i":64,"x":"Day 2 – Genesis 1:6-8"},{"c":2,"i":65,"x":"The void container is filled"},{"c":2,"i":66,"x":"And God said, let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the"},{"c":2,"i":67,"x":"waters from the waters. And God made the firmament, and divided the waters which"},{"c":2,"i":68,"x":"were under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament: and it"},{"c":2,"i":69,"x":"was so. And God called the firmament Heaven."},{"c":2,"i":70,"x":"And the evening and the morning were the second day."},{"c":2,"i":71,"x":"The English word “waters” in verse 6 is translated from the same Hebrew word “‫ ”מַ יִם‬used in verse 2 but from this point on the English word “waters” no longer emphasizes the raw sewage of “urine, semen, piss, wasting” simply because the “void” container of time-and-space is no longer “void.”"},{"c":2,"i":72,"x":"The English word “firmament” or “expanse” in 1:6 was translated from the"},{"c":2,"i":73,"x":"ָּ (H7549) “from <H7554> (raqa`); properly an expanse, i.e. the Hebrew word “‫”רקִ י ַע‬ firmament or (apparently) visible arch of the sky :- firmament.” Thus, the English word “firmament” describes the envelope of air that surrounds the Earth."},{"c":2,"i":74,"x":"The English word “firmament” qualifies the word “Heaven” which was translated from the Hebrew word “‫( ”שָּ מַ יִם‬Strong’s H8064). The English word “firmament” qualifies “Heaven” to be much more specific than the summary definition used in Genesis 1:1."},{"c":2,"i":75,"x":"Nevertheless, day 2 ends with God’s statement “And the evening and the morning were the second day.” Day 3 – Genesis 1:9-13"},{"c":2,"i":76,"x":"The earth, grass, and trees are created"},{"c":2,"i":77,"x":"And God said, Let the waters under the heaven be gathered together unto one place,"},{"c":2,"i":78,"x":"and let the dry land appear: and it was so. And God called the dry land Earth; and"},{"c":2,"i":79,"x":"the gathering together of the waters called the Seas. And God saw that it was good."},{"c":2,"i":80,"x":"And God said, Let the earth bring forth grass, the herb yielding seed, and the fruit"},{"c":2,"i":81,"x":"tree yielding fruit after his kind, whose seed is in itself, upon the earth: and it was so."},{"c":2,"i":82,"x":"And the earth brought forth grass, and herb yielding seed after his kind, and the tree"},{"c":2,"i":83,"x":"yielding fruit, whose seed was in itself, after his kind: and God saw that it was good."},{"c":2,"i":84,"x":"And the evening and the morning were the third day."},{"c":2,"i":85,"x":"Genesis 1:9-13 reports “the earth” being prepared for sustaining every form of non-plant life. Life exists only on “the earth” despite the best efforts of wisdom deficient scientists who don’t hesitate to use our tax money to search for evidence of life in other parts of the Universe."},{"c":2,"i":86,"x":"The English word “heaven” in verse 9 has already been qualified by the English word “firmament” in verse 6. Accordingly, the word “heaven” in verse 9 does not describe the space we know as the Universe. Thus, verses 9-13 describe God’s activity with respect to only “the earth” followed by God’s statement that “the evening and the morning were the third day.”"},{"c":2,"i":87,"x":"Day 4 – Genesis 1:14-19"},{"c":2,"i":88,"x":"The solar system is finally created"},{"c":2,"i":89,"x":"And God said, let there be lights in the firmament of the heaven to divide the day"},{"c":2,"i":90,"x":"from the night; and let them be for signs, and for seasons, and for days, and years."},{"c":2,"i":91,"x":"And let them be for lights in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth:"},{"c":2,"i":92,"x":"and it was so. And God made two great lights; the greater light to rule the day, and"},{"c":2,"i":93,"x":"the lesser light to rule the night: he made the stars also. And God set them in the"},{"c":2,"i":94,"x":"firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth, and to rule over the day and"},{"c":2,"i":95,"x":"over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness: and God saw that it was"},{"c":2,"i":96,"x":"good."},{"c":2,"i":97,"x":"And the evening and the morning were the fourth day."},{"c":2,"i":98,"x":"As of Genesis 1:14-19 the Kelvin temperature of God’s electromagnetic energy has already been cooled enough to create all the Mass that forms the solar system within which the Earth orbits about a Sun as well as rotates on an axis and a Moon which orbits about the Earth. Nothing else in God’s elaborate Universe has any significance for understanding God’s Purpose-For-Creation. Everything else exists only as an extremely elaborate fulfilment of God’s Purpose-For-Creation to educate “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” about their intellectual requirement to worship God for His Glorious Holiness."},{"c":2,"i":99,"x":"The multi-word English term “the firmament of the heaven” in Genesis 1:14 seems to include the entire solar system that provides both “light and darkness” as well as an “evening and morning” to be used for measuring time. God’s Purpose-For-Creation is concentrated on the Earth within a solar system rather than concentrated on the Universe. The Universe is merely an elaborate container for a Solar System that exists within the Milky Way Galaxy."},{"c":2,"i":100,"x":"Genesis 1:14-19 seems to suggest seasons are anticipated as a function of the Solar System even though “seedtime and harvest” are not promised until the end of the flood in Genesis 8:22. It seems that the axis of “the earth” was not tipped from being vertical until after the flood. The tipping of “the earth” may suggest the means God used to cause the flood. Nevertheless, a rotating “earth” provides the means by which we measure time."},{"c":2,"i":101,"x":"One rotation of the Earth always describes “One 24-hour Day” despite the speed of rotation of the Earth. Hours on the Earth are always measured as 1/24 of one rotation. Minutes are always 1/60 of an hour despite the Earth’s rotation speed. This is true even though modern timekeepers have instituted a so-called “Leap Year” just so modern earth dwellers don’t need to replace all our clocks to reflect the constantly changing duration of an hour."},{"c":2,"i":102,"x":"Time was established by God based on The Creator’s foreknowledge of the relationship between one orbit of the Earth about the Sun and the speed of rotation of the Earth. Thus, every question about days being 24-hour periods is moot because days have never been anything other than a 24-hour period despite the speed of rotation of “the earth.”"},{"c":2,"i":103,"x":"Despite any wisdom deficient scholarly speculations about the time God took to create the Earth (i.e., six days, millions of years, etc.), God’s inspired report of the Creation event is the only source of information that was written by the divine Creator."},{"c":2,"i":104,"x":"The Creation event cannot be repeated so the conflicted opinions of wisdom deficient Bible scholars about what happened are each based on foolish speculations. Wisdom deficient Bible scholars are the source for every instance of conflicted theology. Nevertheless, day 4 ends with the statement “And the evening and the morning were the fourth day.” Day 5 – Genesis 1:20-23"},{"c":2,"i":105,"x":"Lower forms of life are created"},{"c":2,"i":106,"x":"And God said, Let the waters bring forth abundantly the moving creature that hath"},{"c":2,"i":107,"x":"life, and fowl that may fly above the earth in the open firmament of heaven. And God"},{"c":2,"i":108,"x":"created great whales, and every living creature that moveth, which the waters"},{"c":2,"i":109,"x":"brought forth abundantly, after their kind, and every winged fowl after his kind: and"},{"c":2,"i":110,"x":"God saw that it was good. And God blessed them, saying, be fruitful, and multiply,"},{"c":2,"i":111,"x":"and fill the waters in the seas, and let fowl multiply in the earth."},{"c":2,"i":112,"x":"And the evening and the morning were the fifth day."},{"c":2,"i":113,"x":"These verses describe God’s creation of non-human life which will eventually provide nutrition for sustaining human life. However, during “the fifth day” these non-human life forms simply exist and multiply."},{"c":2,"i":114,"x":"Day 5 ends with the statement “And the evening and the morning were the fifth day.”"},{"c":2,"i":115,"x":"Day 6 – Genesis 1:24-31"},{"c":2,"i":116,"x":"Human life is finally created"},{"c":2,"i":117,"x":"And God said, Let the earth bring forth the living creature after his kind, cattle, and"},{"c":2,"i":118,"x":"creeping thing, and beast of the earth after his kind: and it was so. And God said, let"},{"c":2,"i":119,"x":"us make man in our image, after our likeness: and let them have dominion over the"},{"c":2,"i":120,"x":"fish of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over the cattle, and over all the earth,"},{"c":2,"i":121,"x":"and over every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth. So, God created man"},{"c":2,"i":122,"x":"in his own image, in the image of God created he him; male and female created he"},{"c":2,"i":123,"x":"them."},{"c":2,"i":124,"x":"And God blessed them, and God said unto them, be fruitful, and multiply, and"},{"c":2,"i":125,"x":"replenish the earth, and subdue it: and have dominion over the fish of the sea, and"},{"c":2,"i":126,"x":"over the fowl of the air, and over every living thing that moveth upon the earth."},{"c":2,"i":127,"x":"And God said, Behold, I have given you every herb bearing seed, which is upon the"},{"c":2,"i":128,"x":"face of all the earth, and every tree, in the which is the fruit of a tree yielding seed; to"},{"c":2,"i":129,"x":"you it shall be for meat. And to every beast of the earth, and to every fowl of the air,"},{"c":2,"i":130,"x":"and to everything that creepeth upon the earth, wherein there is life, I have given"},{"c":2,"i":131,"x":"every green herb for meat: and it was so."},{"c":2,"i":132,"x":"And God saw everything that he had made, and behold, it was very good.."},{"c":2,"i":133,"x":"And the evening and the morning were the sixth day."},{"c":2,"i":134,"x":"Wisdom deficient Bible scholars typically “understand” the clause “God created man in his own image” to mean each of us humans have some of the same attributes that describe God. But John 1:18 teaches “No man hath seen God at any time; the only begotten Son, which is in the bosom of the Father, he hath declared him.” However, Revelation 13:8 teaches that an observable image of Jesus had already been established “from the foundation of the world.” Thus, I suggest the plural possessive “our image” in Genesis 1:26 literally refers to the human image of “Lamb slain from the foundation of the world” who was incarnated by the plural Godhead of God-the-Father and God-the-Spirit and Gpd-the-Son about 2000 years ago to become “the Son of Man” who was “born of the flesh” to a young virgin named Mary. Thus, Adam and Eve were intentionally “made” to have the same DNA as “the Son of Man”, who was named Jesus."},{"c":2,"i":135,"x":"The initialization of God’s plan was ended with God’s declaration in Genesis 1:31 that “behold, it was very good” simply God had created everything that was required to accomplish God Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":2,"i":136,"x":"The English adjective “good” in Genesis 1:31 was translated from Hebrew “‫”טֹוב‬ (Strong’s H2896) defined simply as “from <H2895> “(towb); good (as an adjective) in the widest sense …” Indeed, everything about “God’s plan is good all the time; all the time God’s plan is good.” Nevertheless, a “good” God deliberately “predestined” Adam and Eve to “sin” so that they could be exiled from the Garden of Eden in fulfillment of the reason why God “made” Adam and Eve."},{"c":2,"i":137,"x":"The English word “replenish” used in the KJV of 1:28 was translated from the Hebrew word “‫( ”מָּ לֵא‬Strong’s H4390) “or mala', maw-law'; (Esth. 7:5), a primitive root, to fill or (intransitive) be full of, in a wide application (literal and figurative) :- accomplish, confirm, + consecrate, be at an end, be expired, be fenced, fill, fulfil, (be, become, × draw, give in, go) full (-ly, -ly set, tale), [over-] flow, fulness, furnish, gather (selves, together), presume, replenish, satisfy, set, space, take a [hand-] full, + have wholly.” Accordingly, H4390 is better translated into English as “filled” rather than “replenish.” In fact, English translations other than the KJV use the word “fill” rather than “replenish.” Despite religious objections to the concept of “predestination,” day 6 ends with God’s statement “And the evening and the morning were the sixth day.”"},{"c":2,"i":138,"x":"Day 7 – Genesis 2:1-3"},{"c":2,"i":139,"x":"Creation is complete, so God rested"},{"c":2,"i":140,"x":"Thus, the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host of them. And on the"},{"c":2,"i":141,"x":"seventh day God ended his work which he had made; and he rested on the seventh"},{"c":2,"i":142,"x":"day from all his work which he had made."},{"c":2,"i":143,"x":"And God blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it: because that in it he had rested"},{"c":2,"i":144,"x":"from all his work which God created and made. Genesis 2:4-9a"},{"c":2,"i":145,"x":"God’s post-review of the six days of creation"},{"c":2,"i":146,"x":"These are the generations of the heavens and of the earth when they were created,"},{"c":2,"i":147,"x":"in the day that the LORD God made the earth and the heavens, and every plant of"},{"c":2,"i":148,"x":"the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the"},{"c":2,"i":149,"x":"LORD God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till"},{"c":2,"i":150,"x":"the ground. But there went up a mist from the earth, and watered the whole face of"},{"c":2,"i":151,"x":"the ground. And the LORD God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed"},{"c":2,"i":152,"x":"into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living soul. And the LORD God"},{"c":2,"i":153,"x":"planted a garden eastward in Eden; and there he put the man whom he had formed."},{"c":2,"i":154,"x":"And out of the ground made the LORD God to grow every tree that is pleasant to the"},{"c":2,"i":155,"x":"sight, and good for food …"},{"c":2,"i":156,"x":"These verses are a summary review of God combining various atomic elements into molecules to create an elaborate environment within a sequential time-and- space thus initiating God’s plan to display “churches” that are composed by “the manifold wisdom of God” to contain both “redeemed” and “unredeemed” attendees to “the principalities and powers in The Heavenlies” according to God’s Purpose-For- Creation."},{"c":2,"i":157,"x":"There can be no question that everything including “the man who was formed by the LORD God ” “was very good” exactly as God had intended. God’s Word teaches that nothing happens that was not “predestined” to happen by “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” (Acts 2:23). In other words, nothing exists in Creation that is not “good” simply because everything is exactly as God intended."},{"c":2,"i":158,"x":"“The LORD God formed man of the dust of the ground” and then completed the process by “breathing into man’s nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living soul.” This is the same “man” whom “the LORD God sent him forth from the garden of Eden, to till the ground from whence he was taken” (Gen 3:23)."},{"c":2,"i":159,"x":"Genesis 2:9b"},{"c":2,"i":160,"x":"God’s Purpose-For-Creation is finally initiated"},{"c":2,"i":161,"x":"God planted “the tree of life also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of"},{"c":2,"i":162,"x":"knowledge of good and evil.”"},{"c":2,"i":163,"x":"Whether these two trees are real or metaphorical is of no consequence to you or me. Scripture does not further speak about these trees until Revelations 22:2. Nevertheless, the “the tree of life” being planted in the Garden of Eden seems to suggest God gave Eve every opportunity to choose to obey God’s command regarding “the tree of knowledge of good and evil.” However, if Eve had chosen to eat of “the tree of life” rather than “the tree of knowledge of good and evil” she would have presumably received “everlasting life” without any need for “the Lamb slain before the foundation of the world.” Thus, it seems Eve’s “sin” and “the slaying of the Lamb” were both intentionally “predestined from before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":2,"i":164,"x":"It seems God’s Purpose-For-Creation “from the foundation of the world” was to incarnate “the Lamb that was slain” to shed His blood as the “redemption for sin” (i.e., the ransom price) demanded by Satan for the purchase of slaves of sin. It seems Adam and Eve were literally “predestined” to learn the distinction between “good and evil” by eating of “the tree of knowledge of good and evil” so that they required “redemption for sin.”"},{"c":2,"i":165,"x":"God “predestined” it to happen that way “from the foundation of the world” just so “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” could observe “the manifold wisdom of God” demonstrating the reason why God should be worshipped for His Holiness."},{"c":2,"i":166,"x":"Scripture doesn’t say so, but we hope the names of Adam and Eve were listed in “the Lamb’s book of life from the foundation of the world.” We “Trust in the LORD with all our heart” that their names were listed but only God knows the names listed in “the Lamb’s book of life from the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":2,"i":167,"x":"The remainder of Genesis, indeed, the remainder of all of Scripture continues to describe either what God did or else to describe what God expects you and me to do. Nevertheless, God’s Purpose-For-Creation has been initiated. And everything God did is evaluated as being “very good” simply because God did exactly what God intended to do. But our knowledge of what God did would be much more accurate if only God had revealed why He created anything."},{"c":2,"i":168,"x":"The conclusion of WHAT God actually did"},{"c":2,"i":169,"x":"God scientifically created everything in six days. God literally created the “Laws-of-Motion” which wouldn’t be “discovered” until the 17th Century by Isaac Newton. God also created the “Theory of Relativity” which wouldn’t be “discovered” until the 20th Century by Albert Einstein."},{"c":2,"i":170,"x":"Despite any divine revelation of God’s Purpose-For-Creation, rival Bible schools teach conflicted wisdom deficient opinions about the “mystery” of that which God really meant to do or say. And yet every wisdom deficient instance of Bible school taught sectarian conflict is included in God’s evaluation that “everything God created was very good.” Amazingly, every (no exceptions) conflicted sectarian leader is doing exactly that which God has “predestined” them to do. The reality is that God’s “calling” to be a conflicted sectarian “pastor teacher” is theologically disjoint from God’s “calling to salvation.” It is to be hoped that “many” sectarian “pastor teachers” will hear God say, “Well done, thou good and faithful servant … enter thou into the joy of thy LORD” (Matt 25:21) but conflict between sectarian belief systems makes that kind of hope to be very doubtful."},{"c":2,"i":171,"x":"I say “Hopefully” only because salvation is entirely due to being “predestinated unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of his will” (Eph 1:5). You and I have no control over that “adoption” process."},{"c":2,"i":172,"x":"Salvation is only offered to temporary and disposable humans “whose names were written in the book of life of the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8). In other words, salvation is only for those who are “predestined to salvation.” Bugs, catfish, cows, and crows are never “predestined to salvation.”"},{"c":2,"i":173,"x":"It seems reasonable that “pastor teachers” who were “called by God to a pulpit pastorate” are also “called and elected to be saved” by being named in “the Lamb’s book of life” but the “determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” is not something that can be altered by volitional-free-will decision making."},{"c":2,"i":174,"x":"Temporary and disposable humans are precluded from writing their own name in “the Lamb’s book of life that was divinely written before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":3,"i":0,"x":"Every Bible believer knows God is sovereign, omnipotent, and omniscient."},{"c":3,"i":1,"x":"If those attributes literally characterize God, then why did a sovereign and omnipotent God create humans whom God omnisciently knew would “sin and come short of the glory of God” (Rom 3:23)? And yet an omniscient God included “a sinful Adam and Eve” in God’s Genesis 1:31 evaluation that “behold, everything was very good” exactly as He had planned."},{"c":3,"i":2,"x":"An omniscient God knows every human is temporary and disposable due to being “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment” (Heb 9:27) so why did a sovereign omnipotent God plant “the tree of knowledge of good and evil in the midst of the garden” (Gen 2:9) and then threaten a temporary and disposable Adam and Eve by “commanding thou shalt not eat of it: for in the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die” (Gen 2:17)? God knew that every human “dies” and yet God omnisciently evaluated the death and judgment of every temporary and disposable human as being “very good” exactly as He had planned. Why did God make that evaluation?"},{"c":3,"i":3,"x":"An omniscient God knew “the Lamb was slain from the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8) before He made Adam and Eve. Thus, Adam and Eve were “predestined from the foundation of the world” to disobey God otherwise there would have been no reason for God to incarnate “the slain Lamb” to be “born of the flesh” as the son of a virgin named Mary. On the other hand, “all that dwell upon the earth shall worship him, whose names are NOT written in the book of life” (Rev 13:8). That kind of universal worship could never happen without the “predestined disobedience” of both “redeemed and unredeemed Wheat and Tares” (Matt 13:24ff). Without exception literally everything was divinely created to be consistent with God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":3,"i":4,"x":"An omniscient God also knew Cain would offer an unacceptable sacrifice while Abel’s sacrifice would be accepted. That same omniscient God knew that Cain would react to God’s evaluation of sacrificial methods by martyring Abel (Gen 4:1- 8). And yet God included the conflict between Cain and Abel as being “very good.”"},{"c":3,"i":5,"x":"An omniscient God knew the progeny of Abram and Sara’s grandson Jacob/Israel would eventually become known as “God’s chosen people” or “the children of Israel.” But an omniscient God also knew that Abram’s progeny with Hagar and Abram’s 2nd wife Keturah would be the mortal enemies of “God’s chosen people.” And yet an omniscient God evaluated that fact as being “very good.”"},{"c":3,"i":6,"x":"It is intuitive that before “in the beginning God created the heaven and the earth” an omniscient God already knew “which names were written in the Lamb’s book of life.” That’s why the Apostle Paul begins his divinely inspired Ephesians 1:4-6 words with the invocation “Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings in heavenly places in Christ according as he hath chosen us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and without blame before him. In love having predestinated us unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of his will.” In other words, in AD60 God “made known unto us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure which he hath purposed (i.e., predestinated) in himself” (Eph 1:9 and 3:3)."},{"c":3,"i":7,"x":"An omniscient God knew that “everything was very good” despite knowing that bad stuff would continuously happen. Yet God’s assertion of “very good” was absolute Truth simply because a sovereign and omniscient God omnipotently predestinated His Words to be absolute Truth “from before the foundation of the world.” Nevertheless, wisdom deficient Bible scholars “lean unto their own understanding” to manufacture hermeneutically conflicted interpretations about that which an immutable God changed His mind to do and say."},{"c":3,"i":8,"x":"An omniscient and omnipotent God sovereignly created everything including both figurative and literal sectarian “wars and rumors of war” to be fought by those who claim to believe “Thy Word is Truth.” Sectarian conflict is publicly observable in the form of Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. And yet sectarian “wars and rumors of war” are included in God’s omniscient declaration that “everything created by God was very good.”"},{"c":3,"i":9,"x":"The evidence is that a “good” God deliberately “predestinated” everything that has happened since creation including the crucifixion of “His only begotten Son.” However, if an omniscient God evaluates what has been created as being “very good” then God’s definition of “good” is different from the sectarian chants that assert “God is good all the time; all the time, God is good.” A “good” God created all the “bad” stuff like sickness and every other form of human suffering."},{"c":3,"i":10,"x":"In Exodus 4:11 God asked Moses “Who hath made man's mouth? or who maketh the dumb, or deaf, or the seeing, or the blind? have not I the LORD?” God’s own Words assert that “a good” God deliberately created sickness, suffering, and all other human frailties. God has always used sin, sickness, and suffering to accomplish God’s Purpose-For-Creation. The reason an omniscient God declared “everything was very good” is because everything was created consistent with God’s Purpose-For-Creation. An omniscient God created universal conflict between sectarian belief systems and then declared “it was very good.”"},{"c":3,"i":11,"x":"Conflict fulfills God’s plan"},{"c":3,"i":12,"x":"It is philosophically intuitive that asking why anything was done is always more informative than knowing what has been done. For example, sentencing by judges in USA Courts of Law is typically based on why a crime was committed rather than based on what elected lawmakers legislated as the maximum penalty for that same crime. Thus, it is philosophically intuitive that Christian conflict fulfills God’s plan."},{"c":3,"i":13,"x":"The philosophical nomenclature is written as “WHY > WHAT.”"},{"c":4,"i":0,"x":"This book is introduced by asking two questions which require minimal Bible knowledge to answer correctly. 1st question: “Do any other life forms exist in the Heavenlies where God resides?” 2nd question: “Does death exist in the Heavenlies where God resides?”"},{"c":4,"i":1,"x":"Anyone who knows anything about Heaven will answer the 1st question as “Yes, angels also exist in the Heavenlies” and the 2nd question will be answered “No; death does not exist in the Heavenlies where God resides.”"},{"c":4,"i":2,"x":"Those questions were suggested by simply reading the first 3 verses of Isaiah 6 which report that “Seraphim cry, Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts. The whole earth is full of his glory.” Why do “Seraphim” claim “the whole earth is full of his glory” when all the available evidence demonstrates the whole earth is full of sin and death? And why do “Seraphim” think they ought to worship “the LORD’s Holiness” when they don’t worship every other Holy thing that can be found in Heaven?"},{"c":4,"i":3,"x":"Revelation 13:8 suggests answers to these questions by asserting “And all that dwell upon the earth shall worship him, whose names are not written in the book of life of the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world.” It is intuitively obvious that “redemption by slaying the Lamb” (i.e., death by crucifixion of “the Lamb”) cannot happen in the place where God and “Seraphim” both reside. Thus, God must create a non-Heavenly environment just so “Seraphim” can observe “the death of the Lamb that was slain from the foundation of the world.” God’s inspired Words reveal that’s exactly what happened. However, wisdom deficient sectarian Bible scholars continue to “lean unto their own understandings” about God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":4,"i":4,"x":"The “rightly divided” context of Scripture (i.e., Gen 1:1, Eph 3:5-10, Acts 2:29) reveals “In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth as a mystery, which from the beginning of the world hath been hid in God, who created all things by Jesus Christ to the intent that now UNTO THE PRINCIPALITIES AND POWERS in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God.”"},{"c":4,"i":5,"x":"“Rightly divided” Scriptural context reveals God’s “determinate counsel and foreknowledge” was to create an environment where “death by crucifixion” could happen. This was necessary simply because “death” is impossible in the place “where God resides in the heavenlies with the principalities and powers.” In fact, everything was created according to God’s “determinate counsel and foreknowledge.” That multi-worded English phrase can be summarized by the single English word “predestination.”"},{"c":4,"i":6,"x":"Authors of secular murder mysteries create environments containing a murdered victim even though typical secular authors have never experienced anyone being murdered. In like manner, “the mystery story” inspired to be written by the Divine Author (i.e., God) creates an environment where “the Lamb of God will be slain” even though no one had ever been “slain” where The Divine Author resides. However, “the mystery of His-Story” (i.e., “history”) must be contextually “studied” if God’s motivation “is to be understood” by wisdom deficient Bible scholars."},{"c":4,"i":7,"x":"God’s motivation ought to be contextually intuitive simply because “In the beginning” NEITHER “the heavens” NOR “the earth” NOR “the Lamb that was slain” NOR “the church” existed in the place where God resides along with “the principalities and powers in heavenly places.” Thus, God’s “determinate counsel and foreknowledge” was to create an environment for telling “His-Story.” However, God deliberately “hid” any knowledge of His “determinate counsel and foreknowledge” as a “mystery, which from the beginning hath been hid in God, who created all things by Jesus Christ” (Eph 3:9)."},{"c":4,"i":8,"x":"God also chose to “mysteriously hide” the identity of “the principalities and powers.” (I assume “Seraphim” are included in the classification of “principalities and powers” but this is “mysteriously” never confirmed within Scripture). A search of God’s “mystery story” reveals “principalities and powers” are created to be either “good” or “evil.” However, “evil principalities and powers” cannot reside “in the heavenlies” where God resides with “the Seraphim.” So, God had to create an alternative environment where “evil principalities and powers” can reside with wisdom deficient Bible scholars."},{"c":4,"i":9,"x":"From the moment of Creation until AD60 God recognized the risk that God’s Purpose-For-Creation can be sabotaged by humans who thought they were literally honoring God’s Holiness by resisting the “evilness of the principalities and powers whom God had created”. That kind of sabotage was actually attempted in Scripture when the leadership of “God’s chosen people” attempted to protect the Holiness of God by accusing Jesus of “blasphemy” (Matt 26:65 and Mark 14:64). Nevertheless, an omnipotent God caused God’s Purpose-For-Creation to be fulfilled by crucifying “His only begotten Son.”"},{"c":4,"i":10,"x":"Tradition reports that in AD60 God inspired the Apostle Paul to write the epistle to the Ephesians about “the good principalities and powers who continue to exist in the Heavenlies along with God.” In other words, in AD60 God finally revealed “the mystery” to those who “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart.” However, wisdom deficient Bible scholars continue to “lean unto their own” theological opinions “to the intent” of interpreting God’s Words as if their wisdom deficient “conflicted understanding” truly reflects God’s motivation."},{"c":4,"i":11,"x":"Wisdom deficient Bible scholars pretend to agree with John 17:7 that “Thy Word is Truth” while literally teaching sectarian opinions which conflict with rival sectarian opinions as well as conflict with God’s Purpose as revealed within the inspired context of “Thy Word is Truth.” Conflicted wisdom deficient sectarian opinions are publicly observable in the form of Christian preaching that devalues Scripture."},{"c":4,"i":12,"x":"The point being made in this book"},{"c":4,"i":13,"x":"The point is that without exception every Bible school educated “pastor teacher” disagrees with rival “pastor teachers” about the literal meaning of “Thy Word is Truth.” Without exception the outcome of that kind of disagreement is always Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. God’s Creation has always been characterized by conflict despite an omniscient Creator God’s making His strange assertion in Genesis 1:31 that “all His creative effort was very good.” Scripture reports conflict between humans immediately after Adam and Eve were evicted from The Garden of Eden at the end of Genesis 3. 1Corinthians 1:12 reports sectarian conflict in one of the earliest Churches established by the Apostle Paul. Conflict existed long before Jesus was crucified and conflict between God believers continues to be characteristic of modern times. However, God inspired Paul in AD60 to reveal in his Ephesians Epistle the “the mystery of God’s Purpose-For-Creation that has been hidden since the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":4,"i":14,"x":"Despite God’s inspiration, wisdom deficient Bible schools continue to teach “pastor teachers” to trust sectarian opinions about God promise of salvation to those who are “dead in trespasses and sin.” Bible scholars foolishly “proof-text” 2Peter 3:9 to teach “The Lord is not slack concerning his promise, as some men count slackness; but is longsuffering to us-ward, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.” However, if a sovereign and immutable God really wants “all to come to repentance” then why do so many NOT “come to repentance”?"},{"c":4,"i":15,"x":"Those same wisdom deficient Bible schools “deceitfully lean unto their own understanding” to teach “pastor teachers” the unscriptural opinion that John 3:16 universally offers “everlasting life” to “whosoever” makes-a-free-will-decision “to believe in Him.”"},{"c":4,"i":16,"x":"There is a high statistical probability approaching 100% that you also “trust” those same deceitfully wrong wisdom deficient sectarian “understandings.” However, the human author of John 3:16 implies in Revelation 13:8 that salvation is “predestined by the list of names that were already written in the Lamb’s book of life before the foundation of the world.” If John’s implication is true, then wisdom deficient Bible scholars either “misunderstand” or else deliberately “misinterpret” the context of both John 3:16 and 2Peter 3:9."},{"c":4,"i":17,"x":"Please affirm that the Wisdom Literature of Proverbs 3:5-6 specifically teaches us to “lean NOT unto our own understanding” simply because “conflicted understandings” always result in Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. The wise alternative is to “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart. In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.” It is philosophically intuitive that the reason WHY God created anything at all is always more instructive than knowing WHAT God has created."},{"c":4,"i":18,"x":"The philosophical nomenclature is “WHY > WHAT.”"},{"c":4,"i":19,"x":"If your “understanding” of God’s Word happens to be contextually correct, then you have literally exposited God’s Word rather than interpreted God’s Word. It is egotistically absurd to claim “interpreted understandings” are honoring to God. In other words, “Thy Word is Truth” despite every egotistical wisdom deficient attempt to “lean unto thine own understanding” to interpret that which God may have meant to say."},{"c":4,"i":20,"x":"Without exception, a humble “trusting” of contextual expositions of God’s Words always evaluates Scripture at the highest level possible rather than egotistically devaluing Scripture with “thine own understanding.” Romans 3:4 teaches that “Pastor teachers” who counsel church attendees from a pulpit ought to worry about their own salvation simply because they are each “liars.”"},{"c":4,"i":21,"x":"The Apostle John’s assertion in John 3:16 that “God so loved the world” seems to contradict the same Apostle John’s command in 1John 2:15 to “Love not the world, neither the things that are in the world.” How can it be that “God so loved the world” while “whosoever believeth in him” is commanded to “Love not the world”?"},{"c":4,"i":22,"x":"John rationalizes his 1John 2:15 command by asserting “If any man loves the world, the love of the Father is not in him.” The English word “world” in both John 3:16 and 1John 2:15 was translated from the same Greek word “κόσμος” (Strong’s G2889). Thus, the only way to resolve the appearance of a contradiction between 1John 2:15 and John 3:16 is to exposit (i.e., “rightly divide”) the context of both verses."},{"c":4,"i":23,"x":"The “rightly divided” context of 1John 2:15 teaches that “loving the world” rather than “loving God” evaluates “the world” as having more value than “the Creator of the world” which is merely a minute part of an elaborately created Universe. However, 2Peter 3:10 reveals God’s elaborate Universe is scheduled for destruction. And God’s divinely scheduled destruction includes both living and dead un-redeemed humans. Thus, John teaches that “loving a temporary and disposable world” rather than “loving the Creator of the temporary and disposable world” is nonsense simply because “loving a world that is scheduled for destruction” is literally religious sabotage of God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":4,"i":24,"x":"A contextual exposition of John 3 reports “Nicodemus” asking “how can a man be born again when he is old?” Jesus bases His answer on the 3:6 axiom “That which is born of the flesh is flesh; and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.” It is axiomatic that every life form (no exception) is determined by parentage so Jesus tells “Nicodemus to marvel not that I said unto thee, Ye must be born again. The wind bloweth where it listeth, and thou hearest the sound thereof, but canst not tell whence it cometh, and whither it goeth. So is every one that is born of the Spirit.” In other words, being “born of the Spirit” is “predestined” by the same Father who “predestines the blowing of the wind.”"},{"c":4,"i":25,"x":"The axiom of John 3:6 teaches that the birth of bugs, catfish, cows, crows, and humans is always the outcome of parental copulation that created a previously non- existing DNA. In like manner, being “born again of the Spirit” describes a previously non-existing Spiritual DNA being created by “the determinant council and foreknowledge of God the Father.” That previously non-existing Spiritual DNA intrinsically “believeth in Him” as well as intrinsically inherits “everlasting life.” But only humans can be “born again of the Spirit.” Bugs, catfish, cows, and crows are never “born again of the Spirit.”"},{"c":4,"i":26,"x":"It is intuitive that both “born of the Flesh” and “born again of the Spirit” are the outcome of “the determinant counsel and foreknowledge of God” as reported in Acts 2:23. Both kinds of life were “predestined” by the same “determinant counsel and foreknowledge of God.”"},{"c":4,"i":27,"x":"The reality is that God “predestines the DNA” of both “Fleshly” and “Spiritual” conceptions and births. In fact, nothing happens that Creator God did not “predestine” to happen. Nevertheless, the concept of “predestination” is often rejected by wisdom deficient Bible scholars."},{"c":4,"i":28,"x":"“Predestination” is clearly taught within the context of “Thy Word is Truth” so why does anyone question the reality of “predestination.” The reality of “predestination” is the reason WHY God commands all humans to “trust in the LORD with all thine heart and lean NOT unto thine own understanding.”"},{"c":4,"i":29,"x":"God’s Word is always Truthful. For example, the context of Peter’s 2nd epistle literally reports Peter writing “to them that have obtained like precious faith with us through the righteousness of God and our Savior Jesus Christ.” The literal Truth is that Peter writes to “brethren” whose names were already “written in the Lamb’s book of life from the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8). However, the concept of a “predestined calling and election” is often hermeneutically interpreted to be “understood” as “The Lord is longsuffering to us <sinful humans>, not willing that any <sinful humans> should perish, but that all <sinful humans> should come to repentance.” By contrast, the literal context of 2Peter 1:10 specifically instructs “the brethren” to “give diligence to make your calling and election sure.” Accordingly, typical wisdom deficient Bible scholars and “pastor teachers” are guilty of “giving diligence to” interpret 2Peter 3:9 incorrectly in order to proof-text their foolish wisdom deficient assumptions."},{"c":4,"i":30,"x":"It is a “mystery” that “MANY who address Jesus as LORD” (Matt 7:22) literally misunderstand the concept of “giving diligence” even though an omniscient God declared in Genesis 1:31 that “everything God created was very good.”"},{"c":4,"i":31,"x":"Another example reports Saul on the road to Damascus was a highly educated leader in the Jewish religion who diligently hated Christians. Thus, Saul was the epitome of “giving diligence” by diligently rejecting The Gospel. But the resurrected Jesus who was also “the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world” had already “called and elected” that diligent unbeliever named Saul to be reeducated (Gal 1:15ff) by the resurrected Jesus to be divinely “commissioned” as “Paul, the apostle to the Gentiles” (Rom 11:13)."},{"c":4,"i":32,"x":"The reality is that every “call to salvation” was “predestined from the foundation of the world” before the gift of “everlasting life” could be given to humans who won’t even be conceived and birthed (i.e., “born of the flesh”) until thousands of years after “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.”"},{"c":4,"i":33,"x":"2Peter is written to those who are “predestined to obtain like precious faith” who will each “diligently add to your faith virtue; etc.” In other words, “Giving all diligence” is merely doing the absolute minimum God has “called and elected” you to do “For if these things be in you, and abound, they make you that ye shall NEITHER be barren NOR unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ” (2Pet 1:8)."},{"c":4,"i":34,"x":"“Giving all diligence” is the absolute minimum expected by a Creator God who asserts that “everything was created exactly as God intended.”"},{"c":4,"i":35,"x":"Those who don’t “give all diligence to add to your faith virtue; etc.” are “blind” and incapable to “see they were purged from their old sins” (2Peter 1:9). However, \"giving all diligence” is NOT what is MOST IMPORTANT."},{"c":4,"i":36,"x":"2Peter 1:10 reports THAT WHICH IS MOST IMPORTANT IS TO “make your calling and election sure” by “remembering” that “God always keeps His promise.” Multiple “reminders of God keeping His promise” are listed in 1:12, 1:13, 1:15, and all of chapter 2. Thus, Peter concludes in 3:9 “The Lord is not slack concerning His promise, as <scoffers> count slackness; but is longsuffering to <the called and elect>, not willing that any <called and elect> should perish, but that all <called and elect> should come to repentance.”"},{"c":4,"i":37,"x":"The reality is that Peter’s 2nd epistle teaches “the assurance of promised salvation” rather than “an offer of volitional salvation if wisdom deficient Bible scholars can somehow persuade you to make-a-free-will-decision.”"},{"c":4,"i":38,"x":"However, wisdom deficient Bible schools ignore the context of John 3:16, 1John 2:15, and 2Peter 3:9 as well as many other contexts of Scripture. It is obvious that Bible schools never teach Biblical proficiency simply because without exception graduates of every Bible school are observed believing doctrines that conflict with the doctrines believed by those who graduated from rival Bible schools. Pervasive sectarian conflict is irrefutable evidence of a pervasive lack of Biblical proficiency. That irrefutable evidence cannot be “understood incorrectly.”"},{"c":4,"i":39,"x":"Instead of teaching Biblical proficiency, Bible schools teach proficiency in a hermeneutical “understanding” about that which God really meant to say if only God had thought about it just a little bit more."},{"c":4,"i":40,"x":"The outcome of that kind of hermeneutical “understanding” is always Christian preaching that devalues Scripture even when that message contains “proof-text” verses quoted from “Thy Word is Truth.”"},{"c":4,"i":41,"x":"Referencing a “proof-text” of Scripture is the exact opposite of Biblical preaching. The distinction is made obvious by asking if the preacher in your church ever conflicts with any other preacher. The alternative is always an exposition of the literal context of Scripture. The evidence is irrefutable that Bible schools neglect teaching methods for expositing Scripture."},{"c":4,"i":42,"x":"God commands everyone to “Trust in the LORD”"},{"c":4,"i":43,"x":"Every living human resides in a world that was created by God. But no human was present when “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.” Thus, if any living human wants to know what God did during the first 5 days of creation he must be told. Revealing history is what God does in “Thy Word is Truth” and God does a really good job of revealing history."},{"c":4,"i":44,"x":"Scriptural History reveals that “all have sinned and come short of the glory of God” (Rom 3:23). That kind of Scriptural History is not “a mystery.”"},{"c":4,"i":45,"x":"However, the reason why God created “a world that comes short of the glory of God” has always been a “mystery, which from the beginning of the world hath been hid in God, who created all things by Jesus Christ” (Eph 3:9). Tradition teaches that Paul was inspired to write the epistle to the Ephesians in AD60. Prior to AD60 God only informed us about what God has already done or else a prophesy of what God is going to do."},{"c":4,"i":46,"x":"Instead of revealing the reason why the world was created, God commands every human to “Trust in the LORD with all your heart and He shall direct your path.” The alternative to “Trusting the LORD” has always been disobedience of God’s command by “leaning unto thine own understanding” to manufacture speculations about that which God really meant to do or say if only God had stopped for a moment to think about what He was doing and saying."},{"c":4,"i":47,"x":"The irrefutable evidence is that Bible schools teach “pastor teachers” to disobey God by “leaning unto their own understanding.” There are no exceptions to that evidence. And rival “pastor teachers” teach church attendees to “lean unto an approved sectarian understanding” about that which God really meant to tell us if only God could have done a better job of communicating. Sectarian church attendees are taught to trust their wisdom deficient “sectarian authorized pastor teacher” rather than taught to “trust God.” The Christian religion is characterized by sectarian conflict between both organized and so-called independent affiliations of churches. It is intuitively obvious that every “born of the Flesh” human is “predestined to sin” simply because “all have sinned and come short of the glory of God” (Rom 3:23). The only exception is the incarnate “Lamb of God” who was “in all points tempted like as we are, yet without sin” (Heb 4:15). He was “slain from the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8) as a prelude to His “coming to seek and to save that which was lost” (Lk 19:10)."},{"c":4,"i":48,"x":"“Cain killing Abel” is another irrefutable example of “leaning unto a conflicted understanding” about that which God really meant to say. “All have sinned and come short of the glory of God” is exactly what God “predestined” to happen when “the LORD God sent <Cain’s parents> forth from the garden of Eden, to till the ground from whence <his parents were> taken” (Gen 3:23)."},{"c":4,"i":49,"x":"A more modern example of “leaning unto a conflicted understanding” is churches conflicting with rival churches about what God really meant to say. Wisdom deficient Bible students are taught to “lean unto their own understanding” that Eve’s “sin” was due to Satan’s temptation. But the real reason why God did anything at all was “mysteriously” (Eph 3:3) hidden by God."},{"c":4,"i":50,"x":"To be sure, Scripture frequently identifies Satan as “the Tempter” but the context of Revelation 13:8 implies that “the Lamb was slain to pay the penalty for sin” before Satan had been “cast down” to become “the Tempter.”"},{"c":4,"i":51,"x":"I humbly ask each reader to exposit the context of Genesis 3 to affirm “the serpent which the LORD God had made” (rather than Satan) merely verified that Eve understood God’s command (3:1) followed by “the serpent” (rather than Satan) revealing Truth which God had “mysteriously hid” from Adam and Eve (Gen 3:4-5, Eph 3:9). The Truth which God “mysteriously hid” is contextually explained in Hebrews 9:27 that Adam and Eve were already “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment.”"},{"c":4,"i":52,"x":"Admittedly, “The Tempter” Satan wants everyone to “sin” but Genesis 3:6 reveals Eve’s sin was entirely due to “the woman <lustfully> saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was pleasant to the eyes, and a tree to be desired to make one wise, she took of the fruit thereof, and did eat, and gave also unto her husband with her, and he did eat.” Apostle Peter contextually explains in Acts 2:22ff that “Eve’s sin” was “deliberately predestined from the foundation of the world” by “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God.” The literature of God’s Word is clear that “predestination” and “foreknowledge” are symbiotic terms. Each of those symbiotic words assumes the reality of the other word. But wisdom deficient Bible scholars seem ignorant of literary symbiosis."},{"c":4,"i":53,"x":"The reality is that Eve’s sin was nothing more than an every-day event of eating food which God had graciously provided."},{"c":4,"i":54,"x":"It is a “mystery” to virtually all wisdom deficient Bible scholars that God used an every-day event to initiate God’s Purpose-For-Creation as well as God’s purpose for the conception and birth of each “born of the flesh” human who has temporary and disposable existence on “the earth” which was created by God to be temporary and disposable."},{"c":4,"i":55,"x":"To be sure, the angelic Lucifer/Satan used “the serpent which God had created” to reveal the Hebrews 9:27 context that was “predestined” to be hidden from Adam and Eve according to God’s own “determinate council and foreknowledge.” Genesis 3:14 explains that an omniscient God “made the serpent” to be cursed “above all cattle, and above every beast of the field.”"},{"c":4,"i":56,"x":"For certain the angelic Satan or Lucifer is implicated by Genesis 3:14, however, the evidence of God’s curse “of serpents” continues to be observed by all modern humans despite any wisdom deficient theological opinion about Satan or Lucifer."},{"c":4,"i":57,"x":"The context doesn’t say so but “cursing the serpent” could be the event causing God to “cast down the angelic Lucifer” to become “Satan the tempter” of every human including temptation of the incarnated “Lamb of God” (Lk 4:1ff)."},{"c":4,"i":58,"x":"However, Job 1:6ff reveals “the cast down Tempter Satan” is restricted to doing only that which fulfills God’s Purpose-For-Creation as revealed in Ephesians 3:10 that everything was created by God “To the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God.” A history professor named Santayana is credited with the quoted analysis “Those who cannot remember the past are condemned to repeat it.” (Search the web for “Santayana’s quotes” if you are curious about his quotes. Santayana was a prolific analyzer of history.)"},{"c":4,"i":59,"x":"Santayana’s quote provides a perspective for “understanding” why “the woman whom thou gavest to be with me” chose to “lean unto her own understanding” rather than choosing to “Trust the LORD with all her heart.” Santayana’s perspective is that Eve had no concept of “death” simply because Eve had no past that could be remembered. Thus, the penalty “thou shalt surly die” was a complete “mystery” to Eve. The only thing Eve could remember was that “God provided trees as the source for food.” Eve “lustfully sinned” simply because God chose to never tell her why she was created. The reality is that Eve was “predestined by God to sin” and yet God asserted “everything that He had created was very good” simply because it fulfilled God’s Purpose."},{"c":4,"i":60,"x":"The angelic Satan who spoke thru “the serpent which the LORD God had made” (Gen 3:1) “leaned unto his own understanding” about that which God had deliberately hidden from Adam and Eve. Even the very best Bible school trained “pastor teachers” emulate the angelic Satan by “leaning unto their own understanding” when preparing pulpit messages. Bible schools persuade wisdom deficient preachers to believe that a sectarian proof-text about that which God did NOT mean to say is more applicable to human needs than that which God literally did say. That kind of sectarian interpretation is exactly what Satan led “the serpent” to do in Genesis 3."},{"c":4,"i":61,"x":"Bible schools teach the homiletic that pulpit sermons are to be structured as Christian counseling to persuade sectarian approved applications of good behavior. Wisdom deficient Bible schools teach that “Spiritually dead humans” can make-a- volitional-decision to no longer be “Spiritually dead.” That absurdity is a sectarian approved wisdom deficient message application."},{"c":4,"i":62,"x":"Bible schools ignore the reality that “conflicted understandings” (i.e., sectarian interpretations) about that which God meant to say always result in Christian preaching that devalues Scripture even when the preacher is counseling “Entire Sanctification” such that human behavior can be observed as emulating “Holiness unto the Lord.” Counseling an emulation of “Entire Sanctification” rejects “If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us” (1John 1:10)."},{"c":4,"i":63,"x":"The reality is that humans are incapable of emulating “Holiness unto the Lord” because “Holiness” is always “the gift of God. That gift is Not of works lest any man should boast” (Eph 2:8-9)"},{"c":4,"i":64,"x":"Scripture teaches 2Timothy 2:2 that preaching ought to be “the things that thou hast heard of me among many witnesses, the same commit thou to faithful men, who shall be able to teach others also.” That verse restricts preaching to only expositions of “the things that thou hast heard of me.” However, Bible schools never emphasize “the things that thou hast heard of me.” Bible schools always emphasize homiletics that result in Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. There are no exceptions."},{"c":4,"i":65,"x":"Many Bible schools teach the homiletic that pulpit messages must end with applications that resist Satan’s temptations by obeying a list of sectarian approved rules and regulations. However, God’s Laws have never been consistently obeyed by “born of the Flesh” humans. In just that way “pastor teachers” are taught to reject the Ephesians 4:11-13 “gifting of God” intended to result in every church “coming in the unity of the faith.”"},{"c":4,"i":66,"x":"Rival church affiliations tend to teach similar Biblical doctrines. So, why don’t rival churches emphasize their similarities rather than affiliate based on their distinctive doctrines? Rival affiliated local church buildings have even been built on opposite corners of the same streets."},{"c":4,"i":67,"x":"God’s answer to questions about why God created sectarian rivalries is that every CHURCH is created “To the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God” (Eph 3:10). “The principalities and powers in the heavenlies” learn the distinction between “good and evil” by observing the conflicted versions of Truth which are taught in rival sectarian CHURCHES. God’s plan requires the “good and evil” that characterizes every sectarian CHURCH which claims to believe “Thy Word is Truth.” Conflicted CHURCHES are merely temporary and disposable tools for teaching the distinction between “God’s goodness” and “the evil of conflicted opinions about that which God really meant to say.”"},{"c":4,"i":68,"x":"Instead of teaching “pastor teachers” how to “Trust in the LORD with all your heart” Bible schools teach “pastor teachers” to “trust” the conflicted writings of dead theologians such as Agustine, Arminius, Calvin, Ignatius, Pelagius, Spurgeon, Wesley, as well as various other living and dead sectarian approved theological scholars. Each of those men seems to have desired to serve God even though each taught a conflicted system of belief."},{"c":4,"i":69,"x":"To be sure, conflicted opinions often partially reflect that which God really meant to say, but even the most nearly correct conflicted opinion is never the outcome of a literal exposition of “Thy Word is Truth.”"},{"c":4,"i":70,"x":"It is intuitive that “Trust in the LORD” requires trusting God’s Words without any interpretation. By contrast, “leaning unto your own understanding” absolutely always requires altering God’s Words by interpretation."},{"c":4,"i":71,"x":"Please affirm the historic teachings of conflicted Bible scholars such as Arminius, Calvin, Wesley, Whitfield, and Pelagius are being used to initiate religious “wars and rumors of war.” History is replete with both religious and secular “wars and rumors of war.” The motivation for every “war” is to eliminate the opposition by effective martyrdom. In that regard, the divine author who inspired Proverbs 3:5-6 also inspired Ecclesiastes 1:9 “There is no new thing under the sun” since “Cain martyred Able” after “leaning unto conflicted understandings about approved methods for offering sacrifices.” That kind of conflict is the guaranteed outcome when sectarian theologians “lean unto proprietary interpretations of God’s Words.”"},{"c":4,"i":72,"x":"The “war” between “Cain and Able” is reported immediately after their parents were “ejected from the garden of Eden, to till the ground from whence they were taken” (Gen 3:23). The martyrdom of “Able” and the later martyrdom/crucifixion of the incarnate “Lamb of God” was “predestined” by “the determinate council and foreknowledge of God.”"},{"c":4,"i":73,"x":"Despite Bible schools “leaning unto thine own understanding” they tend to be valuable simply because it is impossible to “understand” (i.e., interpret) that which God meant to say unless you already know that which God literally did say."},{"c":4,"i":74,"x":"It is extremely important for local church “pastor teachers” to be Biblically proficient simply because typical church attendees are NOT Biblically proficient. Church attendees need to literally hear God’s Words rather than hear conflicted sectarian proof-text speculations about that which God may have really meant for church attendees to hear. Literally hearing God’s Words is the only way church attendees can possibly “come in the unity of the faith.”"},{"c":4,"i":75,"x":"But Bible schools never emphasize Biblical proficiency. The very best Bible schools teach hermeneutics that conflict with the hermeneutics taught at rival Bible schools. Bible schools attract new students by marketing the sectarian hermeneutics preferred by students rather than specializing in Biblical proficiency. It is a financially expedient marketing strategy."},{"c":4,"i":76,"x":"Every Bible school trained “pastor teacher” is taught to conflict with rival Bible school trained “pastor teachers.” Thus, it is inevitable that every church attendee conflicts with rival church attendees. Conflict between CHURCHES is so pervasive that the only conceivable conclusion is that conflict between CHURCHES is “predestined” by God “to the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CONFLICT BETWEEN CHURCHES the manifold wisdom of God.”"},{"c":4,"i":77,"x":"Moses was told that God deliberately “maketh the dumb, or deaf, or the seeing, or the blind” (Ex 4:11). And God also created CONFLICT BETWEEN CHURCHES to fulfill His Purpose-For-Creation. Why did God delay revealing His plan"},{"c":4,"i":78,"x":"It is natural to be curious about why a sovereign and omniscient God would “mysteriously” wait until AD60 to finally reveal why God created anything at all. I suggest one reason why God delayed revealing His Plan was to preclude well- intentioned and sincere God-believers from sabotaging God’s Purpose-For- Creation."},{"c":4,"i":79,"x":"A well-intentioned resistance to God’s Purpose-For-Creation is described in 1Corinthians 2:8 where Paul admits “for had they known it they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.” Please affirm the statistical probability that the best educated Jewish Scholars would never request Pilate to crucify Jesus if God had allowed those well-intentioned scholarly Jewish leaders to know that Jesus was really their promised Messiah."},{"c":4,"i":80,"x":"God literally intends His Words to be hidden as commanded in Isaiah 6:9-10 “And he said, Go, and tell this people, HEAR ye indeed, BUT UNDERSTAND NOT; and SEE ye indeed, BUT PERCEIVE NOT.”"},{"c":4,"i":81,"x":"As a matter of fact, well-intentioned modern Bible scholars emulate Jewish scholars by tolerating the “evil conflict” of doctrinal diversity simply because God “caused or predestined THE CHURCH” to be conflicted as required by Ephesians 3:10."},{"c":4,"i":82,"x":"Isaiah 6:9-10 contradicts Bible school hermeneutics that teach God universally offers “salvation and healing” to anyone and everyone simply because “God so loved the world.” However, the “mysterious” reality is that God does NOT want everyone to be saved and/or healed."},{"c":4,"i":83,"x":"Thus, it was statistically necessary for God to hide “the mystery” until after Jesus had been crucified to provide “redemption from sin for those who are called and elect” and after New Testament Churches had been initiated by Apostle Paul. Otherwise, some well-intended Bible scholar may inadvertently “understand” and God would be obligated to allow them to “convert and be healed.”"},{"c":4,"i":84,"x":"Hiding the “mystery from the foundation of the world” prevented statistical sabotage of the “mystery.” An infinitely omniscient and wise God recognized the statistical risk of sabotage by well-intentioned but wisdom deficient religious leaders."},{"c":4,"i":85,"x":"My caveat"},{"c":4,"i":86,"x":"Please affirm that the consensus of “many” (Matt 7:22) wisdom deficient Bible scholars and Bible school teachers is that God created the world simply because God wanted to be glorified by free agent humans choosing to “believeth in Him.” But that consensus literally disagrees with “Thy Word is Truth.” My own wisdom deficient opinion is that the “mysterious reason” why an omniscient and omnipotent God created the world is “to the intent that” wisdom deficient Bible scholars and Bible school teachers would fail to teach Ephesians 3:10 as God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":4,"i":87,"x":"That is exactly what has happened."},{"c":4,"i":88,"x":"Wisdom deficient Bible scholars typically interpret God’s Words to teach that “whosoever believeth in Him” will be divinely rewarded for making that volitional decision by divinely receiving “everlasting life.” Bible scholars and city-wide Evangelists typically think God created the world so that “dead in trespasses and sin” free-agent humans could make-a-decision to no longer be “dead” by coming forward during their “Hour-of-Decision.”"},{"c":4,"i":89,"x":"Wisdom deficient Bible scholars tend to assume the human descendants of Adam and Eve are the beneficiaries of God’s creation. However, the reality is that every human is “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment” (Heb 9:27). The reality is that both “redeemed” and “unredeemed” humans are merely temporary and disposable tools being used by God to educate “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” (Eph 3:10)."},{"c":4,"i":90,"x":"Educated religious leaders tend to “think of themselves more highly than they ought to think” (Rom 12:3). Egotistical religious leaders never characterize themselves by the Beatitudes listed in Matthew 5:3-11. However, I have no academic credential for criticizing the doctrines manufactured by egotistical Bible scholars and city-wide Evangelists."},{"c":4,"i":91,"x":"I have never enrolled in an academic Bible school. Thus, I admit I lack academic credentials as a Biblical scholar I am totally dependent on the opinionated teaching of Bible school trained “pastor teachers” who preach from the pulpit of whichever church I happen to be attending. However, I am typically disappointed by the lack of Biblical proficiency displayed by Bible school trained pulpit preachers. I observe Bible school trained preacher’s contradicting God’s inspired Words with their"},{"c":4,"i":92,"x":"As a Bible believer I claim to “Trust in the LORD with all my heart” simply because I know from experience that every time anyone attempts to “lean unto their own understanding” we humans always end up conflicting with each other. The mere existence of sectarian affiliations and denominations is irrefutable evidence of that kind of universal conflict between Bible believing sectarians."},{"c":4,"i":93,"x":"This book is a call to Bible school trained pulpit preachers to encourage exposition of the Literature of Scripture and to do it just as if you really believe Scripture is God’s Holy Words because WHY God inspired Scripture to be written Is more valuable than any conflicted opinion about WHAT God meant to say."},{"c":5,"i":0,"x":"Students choose to attend a specific Bible school because they already believe the doctrines being taught at that school. Students may claim they are learning Biblically proficiency but the school they select always justifies conflicted doctrinal beliefs with a hermeneutical system of “leaning unto thine own understanding.” Exceptions are conceivable but I am not aware of any Bible school that deliberately exposits Scripture to discover the reason why “In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.”"},{"c":5,"i":1,"x":"Trusting Bible scholars to reveal God’s Purpose-For-Creation is a wasted exercise simply because their Biblical knowledge was attained by “leaning unto their own understanding” of conflicted theological opinions about what God really meant to say. The reality is that each Bible school prefers to teach the hermeneutical methods preferred by uniquely conflicted sectarian theologians."},{"c":5,"i":2,"x":"The honorific of “Biblical scholar” is never a degree granted by a Bible school. That honorific merely indicates the preference of biased theologians who claim to be familiar with WHAT God has done. Bible scholars are each theologically opinionated when they cite proof-texts they manufactured to support their opinions. Despite what they may claim, every Bible school exists only by the financial approval of conflicted sectarian leaders. And God declares that conflict is “very good” because God’s Purpose-For-Creation requires conflict."},{"c":5,"i":3,"x":"Bible schools teach the doctrines manufactured by conflicted theologians who wrote commentaries and study helps about that which God really meant to say even though a sovereign and omniscient God personally inspired every Word written in Scripture. Every Bible school ignores God command to “Trust in the LORD and He shall direct our paths.” Instead, every Bible school, every commentary, every study help teaches us to “lean unto your own understanding” by becoming proficient in sectarian hermeneutics which authorize the interpretation of doctrinally conflicted religious opinions."},{"c":5,"i":4,"x":"Accordingly, Churches that hire Bible school graduates typically hear Christian preaching that devalues Scripture rather than hear contextual expositions of that which God literally said. The “understanding” of John 3:16 I grew up trusting was the outcome of conflicted Bible schools teaching students to “lean unto thine own understanding” about that which God really meant to say rather than teaching “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart” as commanded in Proverbs 3:5."},{"c":5,"i":5,"x":"I later concluded my prior “trust” about the meaning of John 3:16 literally disobeyed God’s command in 1Timothy 6:20 “keep that which is committed to thy trust, avoiding profane and vain babblings, and oppositions of science falsely so called.” The English word “science” was translated from the Greek word “γνῶσις” (Strong’s G1108) “from <G1097> (ginosko); knowing (the act), i.e. (by implication) knowledge :- knowledge, science.” Thus, that verse instructs us to avoid “knowledge falsely so called” by “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart, and He shall direct thy paths.”"},{"c":5,"i":6,"x":"Scientific knowledge is repeatable else it is scientific speculation. But God’s creation cannot be repeated. Thus, the pervasiveness of scientific speculations about WHY God created anything” is the reason Paul warns religious leaders like Timothy in 1Timothy 6:20 and the Mars hill philosophers in Acts 17:18ff as well as all Bible school educated “pastor teachers” that “scientific theological speculations” are being idolatrously worshipped just as if those “speculations” are literal Truth. The mere existence of sectarian affiliations and denominations is proof that 1Timothy 6:20 is being disobeyed by modern Bible school educated “pastor teachers.”"},{"c":5,"i":7,"x":"In the past I trusted the “theological speculation” that God created the world so that humans who are “dead in trespass and sin” could make-a-decision to no longer “be dead” by volitionally choosing to have “everlasting life.” But, that kind of “speculation” ignores the fact that “dead” people are incapable of choosing anything simply because they are “dead.”"},{"c":5,"i":8,"x":"The reality is that humans who are “dead in trespasses and sin” must be “Spiritually born again” before God’s Truth can be known."},{"c":5,"i":9,"x":"Every Bible school “speculation” is the outcome of manufactured hermeneutics which conflict with rival Bible school hermeneutics. Without exception, the outcome of every hermeneutical conflict is Christian preaching that devalues Scripture rather than Scriptural exposition."},{"c":5,"i":10,"x":"Nevertheless, Biblical education is necessary despite any reliance on conflicted opinions because it is impossible to have correct opinions about that which God planned to do and say unless the entire context of God’s inspired Words are “rightly divided” from beginning to end."},{"c":5,"i":11,"x":"Bible schools ought to teach Biblical proficiency rather than teach proficiency in sectarian “speculations.” But every Bible school teaches proficiency in hermeneutical systems that are used to manufacture conflicted “speculations” about WHY an omniscient God created a world where “God’s only begotten Son” was murdered by crucifixion."},{"c":5,"i":12,"x":"Conflicted theological “speculations” de facto reject the Ephesians 4:11ff doctrine that God “gifts pastor teachers” so that church people will “come in the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of the Son of God, unto a perfect man, unto the measure of the stature of the fulness of Christ.”"},{"c":5,"i":13,"x":"As a matter of fact, every instance of sectarian and/or denominational preference (Baptist, Catholic, Evangelical Free, Holiness, Methodist, Presbyterian, etc.) is a theologically approved rejection of “the unity of the faith.” Without exception “pastor teachers” are trained to deliberately and purposefully reject “the unity of the faith.”"},{"c":5,"i":14,"x":"Admittedly, Bible school professors frequently teach a version of theologically manufactured opinions that partially agrees with God’s Purpose-For-Creation so that God is partially glorified. Bible school professors may even cite proof texts of Scripture which seem to verify those manufactured opinions. However, proof text opinions are never “rightly divided” expositions of “Truth.”"},{"c":5,"i":15,"x":"1Corinthians 2:14 argues against Bible school taught hermeneutics “But the natural man receives not the things of the Spirit of God: for they are foolishness unto him: neither can he know them, because they are spiritually discerned.” Bible schools use hermeneutics as substitutes for “the Spirit of God.” “Spiritual discernment” is withheld from Bible scholars who egotistically “think of themself more highly than they ought to think” (Rom 12:3). And yet, an omniscient God declared that egotistical opinions are “very good” simply because that’s exactly the reason God Created Bible scholars."},{"c":5,"i":16,"x":"Withholding “Spiritual discernment” was literally commanded by God when Isaiah was commissioned as a prophet in 6:9ff; “Make the heart of this people fat, and make their ears heavy, and shut their eyes; lest they see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and understand with their heart, and convert, and be healed.” Jesus references Isaiah 6:9ff in Matthew 13:13ff when explaining correct doctrine to His disciples. Modern sectarian conflict between Bible school trained “pastor teachers” always without exception indicates a lack of “spiritual discernment.”"},{"c":5,"i":17,"x":"A modern example of “withheld Spiritual discernment” is the “theological speculation” that God requires “whosoever believeth in Him” to fulfil the so-called “Great Commission” as specifically commanded (Matthew 28:16ff) to “eleven disciples” who “went away into Galilee, into a mountain where Jesus had appointed them” as Apostles for fulfilling their God assigned mission."},{"c":5,"i":18,"x":"The English word “commission” appears only once in KJV Bibles when Paul describes his trip to Damascus in Acts 26:12 as being “with authority and commission from the chief priests.” The English word “commission” was translated from Greek “ἐπιτροπή” (Strong’s G2011) “from <G2010> (epitrepo); permission, i.e. (by implication) full power :- commission.”"},{"c":5,"i":19,"x":"Thus, the so-called “Great Commission” is merely a theological concept manufactured by Bible scholars who without God’s permission have expanded the Matthew 28:20 “Apostolic command” to include all “disciples.”"},{"c":5,"i":20,"x":"Those Bible scholars are “liars” according to Romans 3:4."},{"c":5,"i":21,"x":"The English word “command” in Matthew 28:20 is translated in multiple texts from the Greek word “ἐντέλλω” (Strong's 1781) “from <G1722> (en) and the base of <G5056> (telos); to enjoin :- (give) charge, (give).”"},{"c":5,"i":22,"x":"Thus, it seems that the so-called “Great Commission” is being erroneously taught as a literal “command” to “all disciples to teach all nations to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you.” It is erroneous simply because only the “eleven Apostles” had been taught “all things whatsoever I have commanded you.” Every other disciple of Jesus was taught only “some things” rather than “all things.” Thus, the “many” disciples of Jesus lack “Spiritual discernment” for teaching “the unity of the faith to all nations.”"},{"c":5,"i":23,"x":"It is utter nonsense to expect poorly trained “disciples” to teach “all things whatsoever I have commanded you.” So, I ask why any highly respected Biblical scholar would teach that “whosoever believeth in Him” is required to “go and teach all nations.” But that’s exactly what many Bible scholars teach from church pulpits."},{"c":5,"i":24,"x":"God’s Words are inexplicably silent about the “churches” established by the “eleven apostles.” Instead, God’s own inspired Words emphasize the New Testament churches that were established by a Jewish Pharisee who was educationally highly credentialed and who “diligently” opposed Christianity until he was divinely “called and elect” on the road to Damascus by the resurrected Jesus Christ to become “the Apostle of the Gentiles” (Rom 11:2). The Christ-trained Apostle Paul (Gal 1:17-18) literally fulfilled God’s Ephesians 3:10 Purpose-For-Creation “To the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God.” The apostle Paul rather than any of the “COMMISSIONED” disciples literally initiated “THE CHURCH.”"},{"c":5,"i":25,"x":"However, if God actually “intends” to use “THE CHURCH” to display “the manifold wisdom of God” to “the principalities and powers in heavenly places” then it is intuitive that God’s Purpose for the “the book of life of the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8) was nothing more than preparation for Paul’s establishment of THE CHURCH. Paul’s epistles reveal each CHURCH established by Paul had problems that needed to be corrected. That’s because God’s Purpose-For-Creation is fulfilled by conflicted churches which are populated with “redeemed” as well as “unredeemed” people (i.e., with “tares and wheat”)."},{"c":5,"i":26,"x":"The churches established by Paul are pre-imaged in the Garden of Eden as “the tree of the knowledge of good and evil which God planted in the midst of the Garden” (Gen 2:9). In that regard I have literally heard a highly respected Bible scholar instruct both “redeemed” and “unredeemed” radio listeners to “make no mistake about it” that every Christian is “commanded” to fulfil the humanly titled “Great Commission” even though Matthew 28:16 reports only “eleven disciples” being appointed as Apostles. In other words, the very best Bible scholars (he had been the President of a major theological seminary) devalue “The Acts of the Apostles” by ignoring the 1:2 declaration “Until the day in which he was taken up, after that he through the Holy Ghost had given commandments unto the Apostles whom he had chosen.”"},{"c":5,"i":27,"x":"I confess I taught that same false “understanding” of God’s Words to my own young children as well as to AWANA children. Thus, I am ashamed to confess I share the guilt of judging the “oracles of God” by “God’s chosen people” whom the inspiration of God evaluated as “liars” in Romans 3:4."},{"c":5,"i":28,"x":"The reality is that Bible scholars hermeneutically manufacture the need to “win souls” rather than exposit the Scriptural “command” that established every conflicted church which is being used by God to educate “the principalities and powers” in Ephesians 3:10. God’s Words teach that God and His “only begotten Son” are the only Ones having the responsibility to “seek and save that which is lost.” Romans 3 teaches “There is none that understandeth, there is none that seeketh after God. They are all gone out of the way. They are together become unprofitable. There is none that doeth good, no, not one.”"},{"c":5,"i":29,"x":"So, where do popular Purpose Driven book writers find the Biblical concept that teaches all Christians should be “Seeker sensitive?” God’s inspired Words in Romans 3 teach us that “Seekers” don’t even exist."},{"c":5,"i":30,"x":"The term “proof-text” is defined in Mirriam-Webster.com as “a Scriptural passage adduced as proof for a theological doctrine, belief, or principle.” Thus, proof-texting 2Peter 3:9 is nothing more than a strongly held “theological doctrine, belief, or principle” about a theologically assumed need to “win souls.”"},{"c":5,"i":31,"x":"God’s Words never teach the need for “winning souls.” The term appears only as an obscure Old Testament reference in Proverbs 11:30. That reference is obviously obscure because the wisdom of “winning souls” is neither explained nor repeated in either Testament of Scripture. The concept of “soul winning” is incorrectly “proof-texted” by wisdom deficient academic scholars to manufacture a justification for generating an evangelistic application of Biblical counseling."},{"c":5,"i":32,"x":"Those same scholars interpret John 3:16 to teach “all who are dead in trespasses and sin” can “come forward to the prayer room” to learn how to choose “everlasting life” during their “Hour of decision.” However, a contextual exposition of John’s Gospel, as well as Peter’s 2nd epistle, and Acts 16:31 teaches the exact opposite “understanding.”"},{"c":5,"i":33,"x":"Both “good and evil” interpretations of Scripture are the outcome of “leaning unto thine own understanding.” Neither “good” nor “evil” interpretations are ever the outcome of “Trusting the LORD with all your heart.” The reality is that a sovereign God intends His inspired Words to be exposited rather than interpreted."},{"c":5,"i":34,"x":"Biblical proficiency always requires “Study to shew thyself approved unto God” (2Tim 2:15). The alternative to Biblical proficiency is the hermeneutical proficiency that without exception is taught in every sectarian Bible school."},{"c":5,"i":35,"x":"In AD60 the Apostle Paul was inspired to write “to the saints which are at Ephesus, and to the faithful in Christ Jesus.” In Ephesians 1:3-5 Paul introduces God’s inspired Words with the invocation “Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings in heavenly places in Christ: according as he hath chosen us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and without blame before him, in love having predestinated us unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself according to the good pleasure of his will.”"},{"c":5,"i":36,"x":"Within approximately that same time period, the Apostle John was inspired to write “to the seven churches which are in Asia” (i.e., the same churches that were established by the Apostle Paul rather that by any of the “eleven” disciples). John implied that “from the foundation of the world” God had already written “the Lamb’s book of life that predestined those who are to be adopted as children of Jesus Christ” (Rev 13:8)."},{"c":5,"i":37,"x":"The English word “church” is translated from the Greek word “ἐκκλησία” (Strong's G1577) “from a compound of <G1537> (ek) and a derivative of <G2564> (kaleo); a calling out, i.e. (concretely) a popular meeting, especially a religious congregation (Jewish synagogue, or Christian community of members on earth or saints in heaven or both) :- assembly, church.” And the English word “assembly” in Acts 19:39 was translated from the same G1577 to describe an unruly mob of angry rioters in Ephesus led by “Demetrius.”"},{"c":5,"i":38,"x":"Thus, Biblical usage of the English word “church” merely refers to an identifiable group of people. The point is that the Greek word “ἐκκλησία” in Ephesians 3:10 describes a group of people whom Jesus parabolically describes in Matthew 13:24ff as being populated by an admixture of “Tares and Wheat.” The term “Wheat and Tares” parabolically emulates “the tree of the knowledge of Good and Evil” that God planted in the Garden of Eden. That parabolic emulation would NOT have been possible if Eve had NOT “sinned by eating the fruit of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.” It is an incredibly difficult concept for modern wisdom deficient Christians to “understand,” but Eve was “predestined to sin” by God’s Purpose-For-Creation as described in Ephesians 3:10."},{"c":5,"i":39,"x":"Some Bible scholars teach that both Proverbs and the Parables of Jesus are merely wise examples of the behavior preferred by God. The invalid assumption is that Jesus was teaching “disciples” to be examples of righteous living in order that they could emulate an unattainable “Holiness unto the LORD.”"},{"c":5,"i":40,"x":"However, if Proverbs 3:5 is literally God’s inspired command to “Trust in the LORD with all our heart” then we must “Trust” that “from the foundation of the world” God had already “predestined” which humans would become “an adopted child of Jesus Christ according to the good pleasure of his will.” That kind of “predestination” includes blind people as well as seeing people, deaf people as well as hearing people, good people as well as evil people, etc. That kind of “predestination” could also include babies who die at birth before they have ever been either “good or evil.” The “predestination” of babies could result in millions of souls from “every tribe and nation” populating Heaven. “Predestination” is always by “the determinant counsel and foreknowledge of God.” God’s “predestination” is never an outcome of “believing in Him.” The conversion of a dedicated unbeliever on the road to Damascus is an example of God’s “predestined determinant counsel and foreknowledge” rather than an example of making-a-volitional-decision to “believe in Him.”"},{"c":5,"i":41,"x":"However, “pastor teachers” often chant that “God is good all the time. All the time, God is good.” “Pastor teachers” are typically taught that a “good God” loves everyone and really wants everyone to be saved even though a “good God” could have prevented Eve’s “sin” if that’s what a “good God” really wanted. The reality is that a “good God” literally “predestined” Eve to introduce “the knowledge of good and evil” into God’s created environment of time-and-space “to the intent that the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” can be educated by observing the distinction between “good and evil.”"},{"c":5,"i":42,"x":"Prior to “God creating the heaven and the earth” it was impossible for “the principalities and powers” to compare “good” vs “evil” simply because “evil and death” had never existed “in the heavenlies” where God resides."},{"c":5,"i":43,"x":"The “Lord Jesus Christ” about whom Paul writes in Ephesians 1:3 was the same “Lamb that was slain from the foundation of the world” who only a few decades prior to AD60 had been divinely incarnated to become the “born of the flesh” son of a “sinful born of the flesh” human virgin named Mary (Luke 1:27). The incarnated “Lamb that was slain” inherited Mary’s “sinful” DNA including Mary’s gene that guaranteed “a propensity to sin and death.”"},{"c":5,"i":44,"x":"The Apostolic writings of John, Paul, and Peter have been unchanged for 2000 years. That’s more than enough time for everyone to “understand” that which God literally said so it is intuitively obvious that every Bible school has been divinely “predestined” to neglect teaching the reason why God delayed reporting the “mystery” until after Jesus had been crucified and after Jesus was resurrected and after “the New Testament Church” had been established to contain both “Tares and Wheat” and after “Jesus prepared the means for adopting the children” who were “predestined” in “the Lamb’s book of life.”"},{"c":5,"i":45,"x":"Without exception, Bible schools are “predestined” by “the determinant counsel and foreknowledge of God” to be doctrinally conflicted simply because doctrinal conflict between “CHURCHES” is an absolute requirement of God’s Purpose-For- Creation."},{"c":5,"i":46,"x":"The inspired epistle to the Ephesians was written by the Apostle Paul “to the faithful in Christ Jesus” to reveal that all creation was “to the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in the heavenlies might be known by the CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God” (Eph 3:10). Please exposit the context of Ephesians 1:1 to 3:9 to affirm that I have “rightly divided the Word of Truth” rather than “leaned unto my own understanding.”"},{"c":5,"i":47,"x":"The Apostles John, Paul, and Peter were each inspired by God to write about “God’s purpose from the foundation of the world” but Paul’s inspiration adds the fact that “CHURCHES” which are populated with both “Wheat and Tares” were created “to the intent that the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” needed to learn “the knowledge of good and evil.” In other words, “the principalities and powers” need to learn the distinction between the “Wheat and Tares” (Matt 13:24ff) who populate every “local CHURCH.”"},{"c":5,"i":48,"x":"Bible schools never teach the reason why God delayed revealing God’s Purpose- For-Creation. That neglect has resulted in pervasive Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. Each Bible school neglect is a “predestined evil” in fulfillment of God’s Purpose-For-Creation as revealed in Ephesians 3:10."},{"c":5,"i":49,"x":"“The mystery” of God’s Purpose-For-Creation was publicly revealed in AD60 when Paul was inspired to write the epistle to the Ephesians. That public revelation happened about 2000 years ago."},{"c":5,"i":50,"x":"However, Bible schools continue to ignore and/or devalue “the mystery” that “the conflicted population of churches” (i.e., “the Wheat and Tares”) was “predestined” before “God created the heavens and the earth” (Gen1:1). The reality is that God’s Purpose-For-Creation “from before the foundation of the world” has always been “to the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in the heavenlies might be known the manifold wisdom of God” by observing the eternal status of conflicted church people."},{"c":5,"i":51,"x":"Bible scholars and “pastor teachers” tend to egotistically “think of themself more highly than they ought to think” (Rom 12:3). Bible scholars are rarely if ever characterized by the Beatitudes in Matthew 5 (i.e., “poor in spirit,” “mourn,” “meek,” “persecuted.” etc.) Thus, Bible scholars tend to egotistically ignore or devalue the fact that absolutely nothing was created for the benefit of temporary and disposable humans who are “appointed once to die, but after that the judgement” (Heb 9:27)."},{"c":5,"i":52,"x":"The reality is that Adam, Eve, and each of their descendants, as well as “the tree of the knowledge of good and evil” (Gen 1:17) and “the serpent which the LORD God had made” (Gen 3:1) and “churches” (Eph 3:10) are each merely temporary and disposable teaching tools to be used by “the manifold wisdom of God” in the process of educating “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.”"},{"c":5,"i":53,"x":"Nevertheless, an omniscient God declared in Genesis 1:31 the everything was created to be “very good” simply because is initiated God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":5,"i":54,"x":"A specific example of temporary and disposable educational tools is reported in John 8:41ff where the incarnated “Lamb of God” reveals that the most religious God believers in all of God’s creation are “predestined as children of your father the devil” “to the intent that” God’s educational Purpose could be accomplished without well- intentioned and sincere religious resistance to God’s demonstration of the distinction between “good and evil.”"},{"c":5,"i":55,"x":"An additional example of temporary and disposable educational tools is reported in Matthew 7:21ff when Jesus (i.e., “the incarnated Lamb of God”) commands “many who address Jesus as LORD” to “depart from me, ye that work iniquity.” Scripture deliberately teaches that “many” church leaders are “predestined” to be judged with their “father the devil” despite religiously pretending that Jesus is their “LORD.”"},{"c":5,"i":56,"x":"The “mystery” revealed in AD60 is that “slaying the Lamb” and listing the names of disposable humans who were “predestined” to be included “in the Lamb’s book of life” are each nothing more than preparation for the Ephesians 3:10 “demonstration of the manifold wisdom of God to the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” by “making him” (i.e., “the incarnated Lamb”) “to be a little lower than the angels” (Ps 8:4-5; Heb 2:6- 7). The reality is that every human including “the incarnated Lamb of God” is “appointed once to die and after this the judgment” (Heb 9:27)."},{"c":5,"i":57,"x":"Nevertheless, Bible school trained religious experts ignore “the mystery” that God’s plan is to populate “churches with both Wheat and Tares to the intent that the principalities and powers who reside in the heavenlies” can learn the distinction between “Good and Evil.” That has always been God’s Purpose-For-Creation “from before the foundation of the world” before “the beginning of time.”"},{"c":5,"i":58,"x":"Bible school trained religious leaders chant that “God is good all the time; all the time God is good” even though John 8:44 teaches “many” of those same religious leaders are “predestined to die as children of the god of this world” and despite Matthew 7:22-23 teaching that “many” religious leaders will claim “Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in thy name? and in thy name have cast out devils? and in thy name done many wonderful works?” to which Jesus will respond “depart from me, I never knew you.”"},{"c":5,"i":59,"x":"Bible scholars teach everything was “very good” (Gen 1:31) until “the serpent which the LORD God had made” (Gen 3:1) temped Eve to sin. In other words, Bible scholars believe the nonsense that “the foreknowledge of an immutable God” reacted to “Eve’s sin” rather than “predestined Eve’s sin.”"},{"c":5,"i":60,"x":"However, 1Corthians 1:25 teaches “the foolishness of God is wiser than men; and the weakness of God is stronger than men.” Scripture teaches that “many of the wisest and best educated Bible scholars” have been “predestined” to reside in Hell eternally with Satin and his demons. Although, “a few of the best educated Bible scholars” are “predestined” to be “adopted as children of Jesus Christ according to the good pleasure of his will.”"},{"c":5,"i":61,"x":"The problem with Biblical education"},{"c":5,"i":62,"x":"I observe modern Bible school trained religious leaders attempting to force a “wise and strong” God whom they believe to be “good all the time” to react to sin by requiring “whosoever” to “believeth in Him” before God’s “promised gift of everlasting life” can be gifted by a sovereignly omnipotent and immutable God who always does whatever He wants to do."},{"c":5,"i":63,"x":"In other words, modern Bible school trained religious leaders “lean unto their own understanding” to manufacture that which God really meant to say."},{"c":5,"i":64,"x":"Thus, the problem with Biblical education is that every Bible school is staffed with academically trained Bible scholars who have been taught to “lean unto their own understanding” about that which God really meant to say rather than being taught to “trust in the LORD with all your heart and lean not unto your own understanding.” That kind of academic training always results in Christian preaching that devalues Scripture as well as results in a dedicated belief in conflicted sectarian belief systems."},{"c":5,"i":65,"x":"The Biblical concept of “predestination” is observed to be denied rather than exposited by “many” Bible school trained religious leaders. That kind of denial of God’s literally inspired Words is always publicly observable in the form of Christian preaching that devalues Scripture."},{"c":5,"i":66,"x":"You may think this book is repetitive just to try to make a point. I acknowledge you are correct simply because I continuously observe a preference for theological commentaries and study helps that encourage “leaning unto your own understanding” about the literal meaning of Scripture."},{"c":5,"i":67,"x":"I sincerely believe repetition and over-kill is the only way to highlight or emphasize those observations. I sincerely intend doctrinal error by wisdom deficient Bible scholars to be refuted in this book."},{"c":5,"i":68,"x":"My prayer is that every Bible scholar will “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding” so that they will “In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.” Amen."},{"c":5,"i":69,"x":"The alternative to “Trust in the LORD” has always been to trust the opinions of conflicted Bible scholars who teach mere speculations about that which God really meant to say. However, Partial Truth is never Literal Truth. The outcome of partial Truth is always Christian preaching that devalues Scripture despite who is partially right and who is completely wrong."},{"c":5,"i":70,"x":"My caveat"},{"c":5,"i":71,"x":"Ecclesiastical conflict between Bible scholars motivated me to write this book about Christian preaching that devalues Scripture. The unfortunate reality is that Bible scholars are Theologically proficient rather than proficient in Biblical knowledge. Church pulpits are dedicated to teaching the opinions of conflicted theologians rather than dedicated to expositing the contextual Words inspired by God."},{"c":5,"i":72,"x":"The inexplicable reality is that God has “mysteriously predestined” Bible scholars to be conflicted. However, this book claims to reveal “the mystery” which “the determinant counsel and foreknowledge of God” had “predestined” to be hidden “from before the foundation of the world.” Accordingly, I freely admit that I struggle with the possibility that God does not want this book to be published simply because that “mystery” continues to pervasively describe currently conflicted pulpit preaching."},{"c":5,"i":73,"x":"The fact that the “the mystery” was “predestined” to be hidden “from before the foundation of the world” is evidence that God didn’t want “the mystery” to be publicly revealed even though in AD60 God inexplicably inspired the Apostle Paul to reveal “the mystery.” Bible scholars and “pastor teachers” continue to be unaware that “the mystery” has been revealed. Even my own family and friends resist the message of this book. My own family and friends tend to be dedicated to the historic doctrines being taught by their preferred set of conflicted Bible scholars. Many of my own family and friends were educated at the best Bible schools in the USA. Some even have advanced academic degrees in religious studies."},{"c":5,"i":74,"x":"If God hid “the mystery” for thousands of years prior to AD60 then perhaps I am being presumptive to reveal “the mystery” in this book?"},{"c":5,"i":75,"x":"That question really bothers me because God’s Purpose-For-Creation is clearly dependent on the inherent conflict between the “Wheat and Tares” who populate every “church.” The conflict between “Good and Evil” is the reality being “mysteriously” demonstrated to “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.” Thus, merely asking the question may be wrong."},{"c":5,"i":76,"x":"The only reason I continue writing this book is that current events seem to suggest the predicted 2nd coming of the resurrected Jesus Christ will occur in my lifetime. My humble opinion is that God is emphasizing His Purpose-For-Creation once again simply because the time scheduled for the 2nd coming is nigh."},{"c":5,"i":77,"x":"My “faith and trust” is that my humble recognition of God’s Purpose-For-Creation is linguistically confirmed by quoting God’s own inspired Words rather than by “leaning unto my own understanding” about the conflicted speculations of Biblically trained theologians."},{"c":5,"i":78,"x":"Nevertheless, I admit I continue to be concerned."},{"c":6,"i":0,"x":"2Peter 3:10 reveals that “the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up” when God’s education of “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” is finally complete. The reason for that final destruction is that all those temporary and disposable educational tools are no longer needed simply because God’s Purpose- For-Creation has been completely fulfilled as divinely “predestined from the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":6,"i":1,"x":"Please be aware that the position of 2Peter 3:10 in proximity with verse 3:9 does NOT imply that the destruction of Creation happens immediately after “the CHURCH” has been completely populated and ultimately “resurrected.” As a matter of fact, the “resurrection of the church” merely introduces the next dispensation of God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":6,"i":2,"x":"Every Christian must recognize that the division of Scripture into “The Old Testament” and “The New Testament” was a naming technique developed by wisdom deficient humans who were divinely precluded from knowing the implications of what they were doing. That unfortunate naming decision made by wisdom deficient humans has resulted in a conflicted “understanding” between theologians who emphasize either a “Dispensational” or a “Covenant” interpretation of Scripture. The reality is that there are at least eight (8) distinct dispensations within God’s Purpose-For-Creation and each of those dispensations contains a particular covenant made by God. Perhaps there are more than eight dispensations and eight covenants."},{"c":6,"i":3,"x":"Despite the number of dispensations God has described in His inspired Words, all of God’s Creation is scheduled for utter destruction as reported in 2Peter 3:10."},{"c":7,"i":0,"x":"It is axiomatic that “failing to plan is to plan to fail.” Plans are publicly announced with public Purpose Statements. Successful Purpose Statements always provide benefit to both providers and users else those Plans will always fail. (search the web for “What is a Purpose Statement” if you are not familiar with the concept)"},{"c":7,"i":1,"x":"In that regard, the Apostle Peter tells us in The Acts of the Apostles that “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” had literally authored a successful Purpose Statement that prepared the way for “wicked hands to deliverer Jesus to be crucified and slain” (2:23). God planned it all before “In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.”"},{"c":7,"i":2,"x":"However, God’s plan was “a mystery that had been hidden” from “God’s chosen people” who “delivered Jesus to be slain by crucifixion.” If “God’s chosen people” had been aware of God’s plan they would never have “delivered Jesus to be slain by crucifixion.” But that decision would have sabotaged God’s plan for “the Lamb that was slain from the foundation of the world.” Thus, it was necessary that God’s plan would be a “mystery, which from the beginning of the world hath been hid in God, who created all things by Jesus Christ” (Eph 3:9)."},{"c":7,"i":3,"x":"Tradition tells us the Apostle Paul was inspired in AD60 to write “to the saints which are at Ephesus, and to the faithful in Christ Jesus” (1:1) to reveal “the mystery” of God’s plan was “To the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known by THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God” (3:10). However, “the principalities and powers in heavenly places” are the only beneficiaries of God’s “mysterious” Purpose Statement. God’s Purpose Statement continues to be a “mystery” to modern Bible scholars who are taught to believe everything was created to benefit “sinful” humans."},{"c":7,"i":4,"x":"Apostle Peter’s 2nd epistle reveals that “a few called and elect humans” will also benefit from God’s successful plan “According as his divine power hath given unto us <few humans> all things that pertain unto life and godliness, through the knowledge of him that hath called us <few humans> to glory and virtue: whereby are given unto us <few humans> exceeding great and precious promises: that by these ye might be partakers of the divine nature, having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust” (2:3-4). Peter identifies “us few humans” as “the brethren” who were created to be “dead in trespasses and sin” (Eph 2:1) but “before the foundation of the world were called and elect” to be used as examples in the demonstration of God’s divine gift of “redemption” for the education of “the principalities and powers in heavenly places.”"},{"c":7,"i":5,"x":"Despite the teaching of Apostles Peter and Paul, wisdom deficient Bible scholars “lean unto their own understanding” to speculate conflicted opinions about who really benefits from God’s plan rather than “trust the LORD with all their heart.” “The mystery” is that only “a few redeemed temporary and disposable humans” will benefit from God’s plan to educate “the principalities and powers in heavenly places.”"},{"c":7,"i":6,"x":"However, please note that God’s plan depends on the existence of “THE CHURCH” and every “CHURCH” is populated with both “Wheat and Tares” (Matt 13:24ff and Eph 3:2-10). Church attendees are either “redeemed Wheat” or else they are “unredeemed Tares.” Both “Wheat and Tares” are nothing more than tools being used to fulfill God’s successful plan."},{"c":7,"i":7,"x":"Despite the eternal status of current church attendees, God’s plan is guaranteed to be successful because both God and “the principalities and powers” benefit from a demonstration of “THE CHURCH.” God benefits because God’s “Holiness” is learned by observing God’s distinction between “the redeemed Wheat” and “the unredeemed Tares.” “The principalities and powers” benefit because God’s gift of “redemption” becomes a tool for intellectually learning the Isaiah 6:3 need to “cry Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts simply because the whole earth is full of his glory.”"},{"c":7,"i":8,"x":"The “principalities and powers in the heavenlies” could not possibly know “the whole earth is full of his glory” unless “a future glorified earth” was already observable “in the heavenlies” when in 6:1 Isaiah reported “ In the year that king Uzziah died I saw also the Lord sitting upon a throne, high and lifted up, and his train filled the temple.” Please affirm that everyone “in the heavenlies” exists outside the creation of time-and-space. Thus, everyone “in the heavenlies” sees both “the beginning and the end” as a present tense event."},{"c":7,"i":9,"x":"Jesus teaches in Matthew 7:13-14 that only a “few” humans will benefit from God’s Purpose-For-Creation. However, both “many” as well as “few” humans are “predestined” (i.e., “appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment” as described in Hebrews 9:27) to be temporary and disposable tools who are being used to educate “the principalities and powers.” All Creation will be destroyed when God’s education of the “principalities and powers” is finally complete as predicted in 2Peter 3:10."},{"c":7,"i":10,"x":"Nevertheless, Bible scholars continue to be unaware that only a “few” temporary and disposable humans will benefit from the 3:9 promise that “The Lord is not slack concerning his promise” of “everlasting life” for the “few” who are “called and elect” as reported in 2Peter 1:10."},{"c":7,"i":11,"x":"Human authors of “mystery” stories withhold pertinent information until the end of their story. That is also true of the Author of both Ephesians and Revelations when the divine Author withholds pertinent inspiration until AD60 near the end of God’s inspired story (i.e., History)."},{"c":7,"i":12,"x":"Temporary and disposable humans are accused in Romans 12:3 of “thinking of themself more highly than they ought to think.” God rejects that egotistical “thinking” by asserting Adam, Eve, and each of their human descendant has a DNA that is “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment” (Heb 9:27). Nevertheless, God inspired Apostles Peter, John, and Paul to jointly teach “humans whose names are listed in the Lamb’s book of Life are predestined to be born again of the Spirit to inherit a new DNA that provides everlasting life” before God’s scheduled destruction of everything in 2Peter 3:10."},{"c":7,"i":13,"x":"Please affirm the philosophical reality that “God’s Holiness” cannot be demonstrated to “the principalities and powers in the Heavenlies” unless “evil and death” already exist. However, neither “evil” nor “death” exist “in the heavenlies where both God and the principalities reside.” That’s the reason why God had to create a time-and- space environment that contains both “evil” and “death” “to the intent that” God could sequentially demonstrate His cause-and-effect “Holiness” to the “principalities and powers in the heavenlies.” Scripture may hint about other reasons, but Scripture reveals only one reason why God created anything at all."},{"c":7,"i":14,"x":"Ephesians 3:10 asserts “conflicted churches” are temporary and disposable tools created by God specifically for the process of educating “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” about God’s “Holiness.”"},{"c":7,"i":15,"x":"God’s rationale for creating “THE CHURCH” is that every “church” is populated with both “Tares and Wheat” (Matt 13:24ff). Thus, every earthly version of “THE CHURCH” demonstrates “the knowledge of good and evil” that was initiated by Eve when she ate “of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.”"},{"c":7,"i":16,"x":"The entirety of Scripture simply records God’s sequential cause-and-effect activity in His successful fulfillment of God’s Purpose-For-Creation. Scripture simply records what God did."},{"c":7,"i":17,"x":"God’s “only begotten Son” was prepared for that process when He became “the Lamb that was slain from the foundation of the world.” He is the same “Lamb” whom Revelations 13:8 predicts “all that dwell upon the earth shall worship him, whose names are not written in the book of life of the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world.” The Apostle Paul agrees in Romans 14:11. Every “unredeemed Tare” will recognize the Lordship of Jesus Christ despite all the “redeemed Wheat” who have already been “resurrected to everlasting life in the Heavenlies.”"},{"c":7,"i":18,"x":"The reality is that “everyone whose name is written in the book of life” is “predestined” to be “redeemed” (i.e., “purchased”) by God to be saved from the penalty of death using the shed blood of the “slain Lamb” as the “ransom” (i.e., the “purchase” price) paid to “the god of this world.”"},{"c":7,"i":19,"x":"The “Lamb of God” was “predestined from the foundation of the world” to be incarnated as a temporary “born of the flesh” human who was “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment.” The DNA of “the Lamb of God” became the pattern for the DNA gene of “death” as well as the gender determining chromosomes used by God to “make” Adam and Eve (Gen 1:26-27) so that every “born of the Flesh” male and female human would “die and be judged” according to the DNA already established for “the Lamb of God.”"},{"c":7,"i":20,"x":"God is a Spirit who has neither an “image” nor chromosomes that determine gender. Thus, it is physically impossible for God to “create man in God’s image; male and female created he them.” Instead, God used “His only begotten Son” as the pattern for the temporary and disposable “image (i.e., the DNA) that had already been prepared before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":7,"i":21,"x":"Contrary to modern theological speculation, humans do not have the freedom to volitionally choose “everlasting life.” The reality is that every human is “born of the flesh to be dead in trespasses and sin” (Eph 2:1). And “dead humans” are incapable of choosing to no longer be “dead.”"},{"c":7,"i":22,"x":"Please affirm that every human DNA and chromosome is patterned after the “image and DNA” of the temporary “Lamb of God” who was supernaturally incarnated into time-and-space as the “born of the flesh male child” of a “born of the flesh” virgin mother named Mary."},{"c":7,"i":23,"x":"God continuously repopulates “the world” with male and female descendants of Adam and Eve who share the temporary incarnated “image” of “the Lamb of God” including the chromosomes that determines gender and including the characteristic of being “appointed once to die, but after this the judgment.”"},{"c":7,"i":24,"x":"Mathew 7:14 reports “the manifold wisdom of God has planned redemption” for a “few” “born of the flesh” temporary humans who will become “born of the Spirit” (John 3:6) to inherit a Spiritual DNA of “everlasting life.” Nevertheless, “THE CHURCH” is populated with both “redeemed” and “unredeemed” God believers. And every “church” including so-called Independent “churches” affiliates with other “churches” to evangelize their preferred list of conflicted doctrines. Conflicted “churches” are tools created by God to demonstrate “the Evil of conflict” while “the manifold wisdom of God” is demonstrating “the sinless church Jesus is building against which the gates of Hell (i.e. death) cannot prevail” (Matt 16:18)."},{"c":7,"i":25,"x":"God also prepared a tree named “The Knowledge of Good and Evil” as well as “the serpent which the LORD God had made” to be tools for that same educational demonstration. But until the promised “resurrection,” both “redeemed” and “unredeemed” church attendees are temporary and disposable tools who demonstrate the distinction between “Tares and Wheat” as well as the distinction between “Good and Evil.”"},{"c":7,"i":26,"x":"That same “manifoldly wise and good” God graciously inspired various disposable humans to either record or else predict God’s cause-and-effect plan as it is being sequentially executed within the time-and-space that was specifically planned and designed to fulfil God’s Purpose-For-Creation. English speaking humans have titled that multi-authored literary compendium of diverse books as “Scripture.”"},{"c":7,"i":27,"x":"The compendium of Scripture describes “sin” as being “evil” while “the manifold wisdom of God” demonstrates everything God declares to be “Good.” God’s Purpose- For-Creation benefits “the good principalities and powers in the heavenlies” rather than benefiting “the many dead” humans."},{"c":7,"i":28,"x":"God had a Purpose-For-Creation “from before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":7,"i":29,"x":"God’s Purpose-For-Creation was statistically at risk"},{"c":7,"i":30,"x":"However, God also had “foreknowledge” of the statistical probability that His plan would be sabotaged by temporary and disposable humans who sincerely attempt to please God by resisting “the evil of sin.”"},{"c":7,"i":31,"x":"A historic example of the statistical probability of a religious attempt to resist “the evil of sin” was recorded in Matthew 26:65-68 to reveal “the high priest of God’s chosen people” attempting to resist “the evil of blasphemy.” A more modern example is “pastor teachers” sabotaging God’s Purpose-For-Creation by resisting the “evil of sin.” Bible school trained “pastors” teach the nonsense that humans who are “dead in trespasses and sin” can make-a-volitional-decision to “stop being dead” by being persuaded that they can acquire “everlasting life” by “their own free-will effort.”"},{"c":7,"i":32,"x":"It is linguistically obvious that “Holiness” must be defined before “Holiness unto the LORD” can be observed. It is also linguistically obvious that the symbiotic attributes of “Evil,” “Sin,” “Good,” and “Holiness” are each dependent on the existence of each other. No symbiotic attribute can exist by itself without the existence of all other symbiotic attributes."},{"c":7,"i":33,"x":"Accordingly, God simultaneously created every symbiotic attribute when “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth” to include both “the Tree of the knowledge of Good and Evil” as well as “an angelic Lucifer/Satan whom God had already determined would be the god of this world.” All creation was merely God’s preparation for God’s intention to demonstrate the distinction between “Good and Evil” to “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.”"},{"c":7,"i":34,"x":"Prior to Genesis 1:1 “the Holiness of God” was impossible to be known “in the heavenlies” because neither “the evil of sin” nor “death” exists “in the heavenlies.” God had to create “both the evil of sin and death” before God could demonstrate “there is none righteous, no, not one: there is none that understands, there is none that seeks after God … for all have sinned and come short of the glory of God.”"},{"c":7,"i":35,"x":"God defined “the Holy Law” that was delivered to Moses but “God’s chosen people” immediately and repeatedly disobeyed “the Holy Law.” Yet the sin of “God’s chosen people” was exactly what God planned to happen."},{"c":7,"i":36,"x":"However, God also planned for “the enmity of the Law to be abolished in His flesh, even the law of commandments contained in ordinances; for to make in Himself of twain one new man, so making peace” (Eph 2:15). “Abolishment of the Law” had always been God’s plan “from before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":7,"i":37,"x":"Prior to AD60 it was a “mystery” that God’s plan was to demonstrate the distinction between “Good and Evil” to “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.” For example, the “mystery” was never revealed to “God’s chosen people” who were “chosen” to demonstrate the impossibility of God’s Holy Law being obeyed by “unredeemed” humans (Gal 3:21ff). For example, David was “a man after God’s own heart” (1Sam 13:14) but David was never taught the “mystery” that he was “predestined to be a man after God’s own heart.” In fact, David was an exceedingly sinful “born of the flesh” human. Nevertheless, David always “Trusted the LORD with all his heart.”"},{"c":7,"i":38,"x":"I am a modern example of that same “mysterious” ignorance. The first half of my life I was taught that “God so loved the world” that He created everything to enable me and other free agent humans who are “dead in trespasses and sin” to volitionally choose to “no longer be dead” by the impossible act of “a dead person making a decision to believe in Him.”"},{"c":7,"i":39,"x":"You were likely taught to that same wisdom deficient absurdity."},{"c":7,"i":40,"x":"But the absurdity of my own doctrinal belief led me to ask who caused Eve to commit sin in an “ex nihilo” environment (Heb 11:3)? The Latin term “ex nihilo” is defined in English as “from or out of nothing.” The problem with theology"},{"c":7,"i":41,"x":"It is intuitive that an omnipotent God can create “ex nihilo.” However, God’s omnipotent “ex nihilo” effort does not explain the source for “sin” despite the sincere but absurd belief of theologians who “lean unto their own understanding” that the source for “sin” was Satan’s temptation."},{"c":7,"i":42,"x":"For example, if Satan caused “ex nihilo” “sin” then were did Satan get that “sin?” Did “sin” exist before an “ex nihilo” creation? Did “hell” exist before an “ex nihilo” creation? Where will Satan and “sinners who are dead in their trespasses and sin” exist after God’s “ex nihilo” creation is destroyed and replaced by “a new heaven and a new earth”?"},{"c":7,"i":43,"x":"Similar questions ought to force every God believer to ask, “Why did an omniscient God who knows both the beginning and the ending of everything decide to create ex nihilo?”"},{"c":7,"i":44,"x":"Can we “trust in the LORD with all our heart” to give us an answer to that question or do we have to “lean unto our own understanding” so that our “dead in trespasses and sin” intellect can manufacture an answer?"},{"c":7,"i":45,"x":"This book reports my observation of rival belief systems being preached from rival sectarian pulpits as if “pastor teachers” already know the answer. My conclusion based on those observations is that sincere sectarian church leaders “lean unto their own understanding” to market and sell conflicted opinions about that which God meant to say rather than “trust in the LORD with all their heart and He shall direct thy path.”"},{"c":7,"i":46,"x":"I admit I am guilty of the same sin as every sectarian preacher because I sincerely think I “understand” the meaning of God’s Words. However, my “understanding” conflicts with the “understanding” of rival Bible believers. That kind of “conflicted understanding” is characteristic of every religious leader who leads sectarian church affiliations to believe conflicted doctrinal opinions. I confess I am aware of my own susceptibility to that kind of “sinful” error."},{"c":7,"i":47,"x":"I am linguistically compelled to agree that Romans 3 teaches “let God be true, but every man a liar.” Every conflicted Bible school taught “liar” attempts to “judge” that which “the oracles of God” (3:2) really meant to say. My “Trust” is that I have grown in my own “understanding” to finally desire “That thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged” (3:4)."},{"c":7,"i":48,"x":"Despite my confessed susceptibility to the “lies” of doctrinal error, my intention for this book is to contextually analyze each rival “understanding” of that which God meant to say according to 2Timothy 2:15 “Study to shew thyself approved unto God, a workman that needeth not to be ashamed, rightly dividing the word of truth.” The alternative is to “lean unto my own understanding” about the real meaning of various texts of Scripture which “lying” rivals have interpreted to have conflicted meanings."},{"c":7,"i":49,"x":"Please affirm that every decision made by those who “lean unto thine own understanding” is disobedience of God’s command to “lean not unto thine own understanding.”"},{"c":7,"i":50,"x":"Please affirm the absurdity of believing that an omnipotent, omniscient, and immutable sovereign God would create anyone or anything with the capability of altering God’s own Will by making-a-volitional-free-will-decision."},{"c":7,"i":51,"x":"Yet, that absurdity is pervasive among those who claim to be Christian."},{"c":8,"i":0,"x":"My 1st hint that God had a mysterious purpose"},{"c":8,"i":1,"x":"About halfway through my Christian life, I joined a Bible study concentrating on “the Church being built by Jesus” as predicted in Matthew 16:18 and actualized by the Apostle Paul in The Acts of the Apostles. That Bible study led me to finally recognize God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":8,"i":2,"x":"The Acts of the Apostles provides the cultural and historical background for every New Testament document that follows the four Gospels. That Bible study included the establishment of the Ephesian church as well as the epistle addressed to “the saints” in that same church."},{"c":8,"i":3,"x":"I was philosophically intrigued by Paul’s writing style in the KJV of Ephesians 3:2-12 where Paul “mysteriously” breaks into his inspired explanation to explain why God did anything. The Apostle Paul inserted his parenthetic beginning with the KJV conditional “If ye have heard of the dispensation of the grace of God which is given me to you-ward …” I originally thought that parenthetic seemed artificially inserted into the context of The Gospel which Paul resumes teaching in 3:13ff. The translators of more modern Biblical versions tend to disguise the parenthetic to appear as a continuous explanation of what God did but the reality of an inserted parenthetic of God’s Purpose-For-Creation is apparent none the less."},{"c":8,"i":4,"x":"What was Paul trying to tell us? Why did Paul insert this “mysterious” parenthetic after his 2:1 assertion that “you hath he quickened, who were dead in trespasses and sins” by being 2:8 “saved through a faith that is not of yourselves: that faith is God’s gracious gift” and before the 3:13ff continuation of teaching the behavior expected of “dead sinners” whom God “promises to gift with a Spiritual birth” that de facto inherits a Spiritual DNA which both “believeth in Him” as well as inherits “everlasting life”?"},{"c":8,"i":5,"x":"My intrigue with Paul’s literature was heightened by discovering that Bible scholars are also conflicted about this parenthetic. I have never heard a Bible scholar exposit Ephesians 3:10 as if it literally reveals God’s Purpose-For-Creation. It really seems as if God has “mysteriously” withheld that “understanding” until the imminent scheduled “resurrection of the church.” That is to say that “understanding” God’s Purpose-For-Creation was “mysteriously” withheld from Bible scholars until just now. I naively assumed my new-found intrigue would also intrigue my family and friends. But they each preferred to “lean on” the sectarian “understandings” we previously learned from conflicted Bible scholars."},{"c":8,"i":6,"x":"My family, friends, and I had each been taught to believe the “sectarian understandings” of Bible scholars whose conflicted opinions about “the oracles of God” are evaluated in Romans 3:4 as being a “lie.” Some family and friends even suggested I was allowing myself to be influenced by the “lies” of fringe theological con artists or cult leaders."},{"c":8,"i":7,"x":"Perhaps you also are dedicated to the “sectarian understandings” of a Biblical scholar whom Scripture evaluates as “a liar.” My humble advice is to immediately convert to “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding. In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.” That’s a summary of the conclusion of this entire book."},{"c":8,"i":8,"x":"Nevertheless, I continued to be intrigued by Paul’s parenthesis."},{"c":8,"i":9,"x":"The verse that intrigued me most was Ephesians 3:10 where Paul asserts God’s philosophical Purpose Statement beginning with the KJV words “to the intent that …” The complete KJV translated Purpose Statement is “To the intent that, now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God.”"},{"c":8,"i":10,"x":"I admit my prior dependance on “sectarian understandings” made that text difficult to parse. However, even the best Bible scholars have the same difficulty. Publicly observable commentaries and pulpit messages reveal “conflicted understandings” (i.e., interpretations) of Ephesians 3:10."},{"c":8,"i":11,"x":"My 2nd hint that God had a mysterious purpose"},{"c":8,"i":12,"x":"God later made me aware of Isaiah 6:9-10 when God commissioned Isaiah as a prophet with these “mysterious” preclusions: “Go, and tell this people, hear ye indeed, BUT UNDERSTAND NOT; and see ye indeed, BUT PERCEIVE NOT. Make the heart of this people fat, and make their ears heavy, and shut their eyes; LEST THEY SEE WITH THEIR EYES, AND HEAR WITH THEIR EARS, AND UNDERSTAND WITH THEIR HEART, AND CONVERT, AND BE HEALED.” Jesus essentially repeats these preclusions in Matthew 13:14."},{"c":8,"i":13,"x":"These “mysterious” preclusions immediately follow Isaiah’s 6:3 vision of “Seraphim” who cry “Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory.” However, “Seraphim” could not possibly know “the whole earth is full of his glory” unless “the whole earth” had already been re-created. Nevertheless, “the whole earth” has never been “full of his glory” since “the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was pleasant to the eyes, and a tree to be desired to make one wise, she took of the fruit thereof, and did eat, and gave also unto her husband with her; and he did eat.”"},{"c":8,"i":14,"x":"So, why did “Seraphim” conclude that “the whole earth is full of his glory”? The only answer is that both God and “Seraphim in the Heavenlies” can see future events such as “God’s gifting of redemption” which mere humans cannot see until those events have literally happened in sequential time-and-space."},{"c":8,"i":15,"x":"Nevertheless, the preclusions of Isaiah 6:9ff protect “predestined” events from statistical sabotage. For example, 1Corinthians 2:8 reports “none of the princes of this world knew: FOR HAD THEY KNOWN IT, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.” That verse teaches that “before the foundation of the world” God had already guaranteed (i.e., “predestined”) the “crucifixion of the Lord of glory.”"},{"c":8,"i":16,"x":"The point of this discussion is that the “crucifixion of the Lord of glory” was precluded from statistical sabotage by precluding the leadership of “God’s chosen people” from having “eyes to see and ears to hear” the critical importance of “the crucifixion” within God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":8,"i":17,"x":"That protection from sabotage was implemented by “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge” of a SOVEREIGN and OMNIPOTENT God."},{"c":8,"i":18,"x":"My 3rd hint that God had a mysterious purpose"},{"c":8,"i":19,"x":"Luke 19:10 reports the time-and-space incarnation of “The Lamb of God who is come to seek and to save that which was lost.” John 3:16 reports “For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life.” 2Peter 3:9 reports that “The Lord is not slack concerning his promise, as some men count slackness; but is longsuffering to us-ward, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.” And Hebrews 6:18 reports it is “impossible for God to lie.”"},{"c":8,"i":20,"x":"I observe those verses are used as proof-text by Bible scholars who “lean unto their own understanding” to teach the salvation of temporary and disposable humans is attained when “whosoever is dead in trespasses and sin” makes a volitional decision to “no longer be dead.”"},{"c":8,"i":21,"x":"However, Romans 3:4 teaches “let God be true, but every man a liar; as it is written, that thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged.” The phrase “when thou art judged” refers to God believing scholars who “lean unto their own understanding” about that which God really meant to say when Jesus declares in Matthew 16:18 “I will build my church.” Bible scholars incorrectly “lean to the judgement” that this declaration by Jesus along with Matthew 28:19-20 is a “Great Commission” to persuade those who are already “dead” to populate earthly churches that publicly “Trust” non-Biblically manufactured sectarian concepts such as “dead people making-a-decision to be everlastingly saved from death unto life.”"},{"c":8,"i":22,"x":"Matthew 24:4-6 explains the reason Jesus “is building His church” when He warns “Take heed that no man deceives you. For many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and shall deceive many. And ye shall hear of wars and rumors of wars: see that ye be not troubled: for all these things must come to pass, but the end is not yet.”"},{"c":8,"i":23,"x":"Please affirm “Christ” is warning that “many who come in my name” will teach “deceptive understandings” as if those “understandings” are literally “Thus saith the LORD.” Each earthly church competes with rival earthly churches as well as competes with “the church being built by Jesus.”"},{"c":8,"i":24,"x":"Without exception every “conflicted sectarian doctrine” is the outcome of “leaning unto thine own understanding.” “Conflicted sectarian doctrines” are never the outcome of expositing the Literature of “Thus saith the LORD.”"},{"c":8,"i":25,"x":"Without exception every earthly church is established by a Biblical scholar who “deceitfully comes in my name” with the intent to religiously compete with rivals who are also “deceitful.”"},{"c":8,"i":26,"x":"No thinking person can deny that sectarian conflict is always the outcome of Bible scholars intentionally rejecting “the unity of the faith.”"},{"c":8,"i":27,"x":"Without exception Biblical context is ignored when “deceptive understandings” are being taught that a “good” God wants to “save everyone who is lost” simply because God is “not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.” If a “rightly divided” 2Peter 3:9 literally means that “God is not willing that any should perish without repentance” then God is “lying” to us because 2Peter repeatedly “reminds us” that many have already “perished.” The entire epistle of 2Peter is a “remembrance” of a “wrathful” God destroying “sinful” beings of whom some were actually human."},{"c":8,"i":28,"x":"The immediate context of 2Peter 3:9 is the “remembrance” that “scoffers” or “mockers” teach the “lie” that a “good and loving” God will never cause unbelievers to “perish” simply because “all things continue as they were from the beginning of the creation” (2Pet 3:4)."},{"c":8,"i":29,"x":"Bible scholars who “lean unto their own understanding” tend to agree it is impossible for God to “lie.” Thus, it is intuitively obvious that the “scoffers” are literally conflicted Bible scholars whom Peter claims are “deceiving” modern Christians into “understanding a lie.”"},{"c":8,"i":30,"x":"2Peter 3:9 is quoted by Bible scholars as proof-text that everyone has been enabled to “make a volitional decision to choose to be saved.” But that “lie” contradicts Peter’s purpose for the epistle as stated in 2Peter 1:10 “give diligence to make your calling and election sure.” Only those who are “called and elect” can “give diligence” with respect to God’s 2Peter 3:9 promise “that all who are called and elect will come to repentance before the end of time” – that promise is guaranteed by Creator God."},{"c":8,"i":31,"x":"Wisdom deficient Bible scholars tend to “deceitfully” ignore that “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth” after which He destroyed “the earth” with a flood along with its entire human population except for Noah and his family. And they tend to ignore that God drowned Pharoah and his army in the Red Sea. And that same God commanded Joshua to kill all the men, women, and children who currently inhabited the promised land. It is intuitive that “GOD KILLING PEOPLE ALL THE TIME” contradicts the sectarian religious chant that “GOD IS GOOD ALL THE TIME.”"},{"c":8,"i":32,"x":"That’s the reason Jesus warns His disciples that Bible scholars are being “deceptive” to the point of initiating “wars and rumors of wars” to defend their incorrect “understanding” that a “GOD IS GOOD ALL THE TIME” wants “whosoever is already dead to volitionally stop being dead.”"},{"c":8,"i":33,"x":"Conflicted Bible scholars teach that a “good” God is like the fabled Genie who granted Aladdan’s wishes (search the web for “Aladdan and the lamp” to read about that fable). Bible scholars predict healing from physical suffering, healing from financial losses, and healing from everything else if we simply express our wishes to a Genie-like God by “praying without ceasing.” In other words, sectarians teach that repeated prayers convince God that He ought to answer at least some of those requests that we repeat every week."},{"c":8,"i":34,"x":"So, why does a “GOOD” God withhold Biblical “understanding” from all those Bible scholars who pray to a “Genie like god” to do that which the God of the Bible has already promised in Matthew 6:1-8 “your Father knoweth what things ye have need of before ye ask him” so “use not vain repetitions as the heathen.” In other words, God wants us to avoid using the same prayer list week after week until we finally convince an omniscient God to do something about the requests we prayed for last week."},{"c":8,"i":35,"x":"Sectarian Bible scholars ignore that a “GOOD” God is actually “Holy and righteous all the time.” It is linguistic reality that “goodness,” “Holiness,” and “righteousness” are linguistically impossible to devalue unless “the evil of sin” already exists. God immediately demonstrated the existence of “the evil of sin” by “predestining” Eve’s “sin before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":8,"i":36,"x":"The philosophical reality is that a demonstration of God’s “Holiness” to “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” requires the cause-and-effect of “evil conflict” to be sequentially demonstrated by “CHURCHES.” My 4th hint that God had a mysterious purpose"},{"c":8,"i":37,"x":"Scripture teaches that neither “evil” nor “death” exist “in the heavenlies” where God resides. Thus, if God expects “Seraphim” to intelligently “say Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory” they must be shown “God’s Holiness being opposed by evil as well as being opposed by death.”"},{"c":8,"i":38,"x":"The evidence reported in Genesis 3 is irrefutable that God created “evil and death.” It is obvious that “the serpent which the Lord God had made” was divinely inserted into the Garden of Eden to be used by Satan. The reality is that the God whom sectarian scholars chant as being “good all the time” created an environment where “evil and death” could be demonstrated “to the intent that the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” could observe the cause-and-effect of Eve’s “sin” as well as observe Adam and Eve’s eventual “death from old age, and after that the judgement.”"},{"c":8,"i":39,"x":"The “manifold wisdom of God” is summarized in John 3:7 “Marvel not that I said unto thee, Ye must be born again.” That summarization is based on the irrefutable axiom of John 3:6 “That which is born of the flesh is flesh; and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.” John 3 teaches “a Spiritual rebirth financed by the slaying of the Lamb” which was “predestined from the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":8,"i":40,"x":"Every “born of the flesh” descendant of Adam and Eve demonstrates “the evil of sin” simply because “all have sinned and come short of the Glory of God.” And each instance of “sin” is guaranteed to result in “death” simply because “it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment.”"},{"c":8,"i":41,"x":"God’s plan is that a “Holy and manifoldly wise” God will “call and elect a few evil and spiritually dead” humans to be “born again of the Spirit to the intent that” God’s “Holiness” can be observed “in the heavenlies” by viewing an “earthly” comparison of the distinction between “good and evil.”"},{"c":8,"i":42,"x":"“Predestined sinful behavior” guarantees the success of God’s plan so God wisely prevents any chance of statistical risk to His plan by causing God’s Purpose-For- Creation to be a “mystery” to “God’s chosen people” when He withholds “eyes to see and ears to hear” (Isa 6:9-10)."},{"c":8,"i":43,"x":"Please also reference the context of Jeremiah 4:23 where God discusses His intentions for creation as if those intentions are the direct outcome of “the sinfulness of God’s chosen people and the way sin effects The Promised Land.” Every Old Testament prophet predicts God’s intentions to destroy except for the prophesies predicting the restoration of the glory of Israel. It is incredible to read that the land of Israel will again be “a land flowing with milk and honey” when today it looks like an arid desert covered with rocks and sand. God’s preclusion of “eyes to see and ears to hear” also applies to modern Bible scholars (Matt 11:25, 13:16). Bible scholars never exposit the Ephesians 3:3 “mystery” from a pulpit simply because they lack “eyes and ears to understand.” If God had given Jewish leadership “eyes to see and ears to hear” that Jesus was their “Messiah” they would never have crucified Him. Similarly, modern Bible scholars would never establish conflicted sectarian churches if God had given them “eyes to see and ears to hear and understand the mystery of God’s purpose for the church.” God- believers are precluded by “predestination” from accidentally sabotaging God’s demonstration to “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” of the distinction between “good vs evil as well as life vs death.”"},{"c":8,"i":44,"x":"That’s the same reason Jesus repeatedly charged “don’t tell anyone about this” to those whom He divinely forgave. Neither God nor Jesus want anyone or anything to sabotage the “predestined crucifixion of Jesus.”"},{"c":8,"i":45,"x":"God’s withholding of “understanding” was only hinted in the Garden of Eden when God seemed to forget to teach Adam and Eve the distinction between “good and evil.” However, God’s hints were eventually made official when God commanded Isaiah “Go, and tell this people, hear ye indeed, but understand not; and see ye indeed, but perceive not …” (Isa 6:9-10). In other words, an omniscient God didn’t forget anything."},{"c":8,"i":46,"x":"“From the foundation of the world” humans have been precluded from having “eyes to see and ears to hear” that God created “evil” “to the intent that” God’s “Holiness” could be observed “by the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” (Eph 3:10) without any risk of statistical sabotage."},{"c":8,"i":47,"x":"God’s Purpose-For-Creation has always been a “mystery” (e.g., Matthew 13:13ff and 1Cor 2:8) but the “mystery” is finally revealed in AD60 by God’s “dispensation of grace” according to Ephesians 3:2-12."},{"c":8,"i":48,"x":"Tradition teaches AD 60 is when the Apostle Paul was inspired by God to write The Epistle to the Ephesian. God authorized Paul to give you and me initial “understanding” of “the mystery” simply because the education of “principalities and powers” is already initialized by the planned formation of “churches against which the gates of Hell cannot prevail.”"},{"c":8,"i":49,"x":"The final completion of God’s Purpose is described in 2Peter 3:10 when God finally destroys everything that exists in “time-and-space.”"},{"c":8,"i":50,"x":"Scripture is easily “understood” by anyone who has been given “eyes to see and ears to hear.” But pulpit conflict between sectarian religious leaders indicates “God’s gifting” is withheld from “many pastor teachers.” My 5th hint that God had a mysterious purpose"},{"c":8,"i":51,"x":"“In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth” (Gen 1:1) “to the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known by the church the manifold wisdom of God” (Eph 3:10) “but the day of the Lord will come as a thief in the night; in the which the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up” (2Peter 3:10)."},{"c":8,"i":52,"x":"That summarization of Scriptural statements reveals God’s Purpose-For- Creation from start to finish."},{"c":8,"i":53,"x":"The remainder of Scripture is simply a report of “What” God is doing to accomplish the “Why” of His Purpose. Intuitively, the “What” can be correctly “understood” only after the “Why” is known."},{"c":8,"i":54,"x":"It is conceivable that a sovereign God had additional reasons for creation but Ephesians 3:10 seems to be the only reason reported in the Literature of Scripture. God’s inspired revelation of “The Mystery” occurred about AD60 when tradition teaches the epistle to the Ephesians was inspired by God."},{"c":8,"i":55,"x":"A possible additional reason for God’s Purpose-For-Creation is the distinction between “Dispensational” and “Covenantal” theological interpretations of Scripture. For example, it is conceivable that the resurrection of “the church” merely ushers in the events described in Revelations 7 when the “hundred and forty four thousand from the tribes of the children of Israel” are described as having been “sealed as the servants of our God in their foreheads.”"},{"c":8,"i":56,"x":"In other words, it is conceivable that both “Dispensational” and “Covenantal” interpretations of Scripture are True. But that’s beyond the scope of this book."},{"c":8,"i":57,"x":"The final hint that God had a mysterious purpose"},{"c":8,"i":58,"x":"This is the hint that finally resolved all my intrigue about God’s Purpose-For- Creation. 1Corinthians 1:9-29 is conclusive that"},{"c":8,"i":59,"x":"God is faithful, by whom ye were called unto the fellowship of his Son Jesus"},{"c":8,"i":60,"x":"Christ our Lord … For it is written, I will destroy the wisdom of the wise and will bring"},{"c":8,"i":61,"x":"to nothing the understanding of the prudent. Where is the wise? Where is the scribe?"},{"c":8,"i":62,"x":"Where is the disputer of this world? Hath not God made foolish the wisdom of this"},{"c":8,"i":63,"x":"world?"},{"c":8,"i":64,"x":"For after that in the wisdom of God the world by wisdom knew not God, it pleased"},{"c":8,"i":65,"x":"God by the foolishness of preaching to save them that believe. For the Jews require"},{"c":8,"i":66,"x":"a sign, and the Greeks seek after wisdom. But we preach Christ crucified, unto the"},{"c":8,"i":67,"x":"Jews a stumbling block, and unto the Greeks foolishness. But unto them which are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ the power of God, and the wisdom of God."},{"c":8,"i":68,"x":"Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men; and the weakness of God is"},{"c":8,"i":69,"x":"stronger than men."},{"c":8,"i":70,"x":"For ye see your calling, brethren, how that not many wise men after the flesh,"},{"c":8,"i":71,"x":"not many mighty, not many noble, are called: But God hath chosen the foolish things"},{"c":8,"i":72,"x":"of the world to confound the wise; and God hath chosen the weak things of the world"},{"c":8,"i":73,"x":"to confound the things which are mighty. And base things of the world, and things"},{"c":8,"i":74,"x":"which are despised, hath God chosen, yea, and things which are not, to bring to"},{"c":8,"i":75,"x":"nought things that are. So that no flesh should glory in his presence."},{"c":8,"i":76,"x":"The point of this lengthy context is that God deliberately withholds “understanding” from the wisest and best educated Bible scholars “To the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God.” This point is especially likely with respect to the distinction between “Dispensational” and “Covenantal” theological “understandings” of the best educated Bible scholars."},{"c":8,"i":77,"x":"Thus, my intrigue with Paul’s parenthetic in Ephesians 3:2-12 is resolved by simply “rightly dividing” God’s inspired Words to finally “understand” that the wisest and best Bible scholars cannot be trusted to explain God’s Words. Each wise and knowledgeable Biblical scholar is evaluated as a “liar” (Rom 3:4) and cannot be trusted."},{"c":8,"i":78,"x":"Only “called and elect” humans have been enabled to “rightly divide” God’s Words despite any educational attainment."},{"c":8,"i":79,"x":"The context of 1Corinthians 1:9-29 has similarity with the introduction to the Sermon on the Mount in Matthew 5:3-11 where Jesus teaches the so-called Beatitudes. Please affirm the Beatitudes literally refute “the wisdom of the wise.” In other words, Bible scholars are never characterized as being “poor in spirit,” “mournful,” “meek,” “hunger and thirst after righteousness,” “pure in heart,” “peacemakers,” or “persecuted.” Rather than being “humble” Bible scholars typically characterize themselves as having excellent academic credentials. It is only those who “were called unto the fellowship of his Son Jesus Christ our Lord” that are characterized by the Beatitudes described in Matthew 5:3-11."},{"c":8,"i":80,"x":"The “rightly divided Truth” teaches that “the manifold wisdom of God” is deliberately hidden from the wisest and best educated Bible scholars. The fact that “God hath chosen the weak things of the world to confound the things which are mighty” is the reason why only simple folk who are characterized by the Beatitudes can “Trust the LORD with all our heart.” I humbly suggest you ought to allow yourself to also become intrigued by God’s Purpose-For-Creation by a humble “study to show thyself approved unto God” by “rightly dividing the Word of Truth.”"},{"c":8,"i":81,"x":"My purpose for writing this book is described in the Sub-Title of this book to encourage every pulpit preacher to humbly de-value every conflicted “understanding” you were taught in a sectarian approved Bible school by deliberately choosing to “Trust in the Lord with all your heart” so that “God will direct thy paths.” The Bereans in Acts 17:10-11 were complimented for exactly that kind of purposeful analysis. My humble prayer is for “pastor teachers” to reject every instance of pridefully “leaning unto your own theological understanding” and eliminate every absurd instance of Christian preaching that devalues Scripture from ever being heard from the pulpit in your own church."},{"c":8,"i":82,"x":"My caveat"},{"c":8,"i":83,"x":"I am not aware of any Scriptural text that requires Christian preaching to be consistent with God’s Purpose-For-Creation. As a matter of fact, God’s Purpose Statement ACTUALLY REQUIRES SECTARIAN CONFLICT in order to demonstrate the distinction between “good and evil.”"},{"c":8,"i":84,"x":"Matthew 7:22 teaches the disturbing fact that “Many pastor teachers will say to me in that day, Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in thy name? and in thy name have cast out devils? and in thy name done many wonderful works” but Jesus will simply tell them to “depart from me, ye that work iniquity. I never knew you.” No one enters Heaven “whose name is not written in the Lamb’s book of life from before the foundation of the world.” Behavior is not an issue as demonstrated by a sinful David who was described as “a man after God’s own heart” (1Sam 13:14 and Acts 13:22). Extreme disbelief is not an issue as demonstrated by a sinful Saul on the road to Damascus (Acts 9). God specializes in “calling and electing” the most despicable people."},{"c":8,"i":85,"x":"Ephesians 4:13 teaches that God intends the outcome of preaching to be “Till we all come in the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of the Son of God, unto a perfect man, unto the measure of the stature of the fulness of Christ.” However, “the unity of the faith” has never been the goal of sectarian preaching. The definition of “Denominational Sectarianism” guarantees that “the unity of the faith” will never characterize church-attending Christians. In fact, religious sectarian conflict was deliberately created by God to demonstrate the “evil of conflict” to “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.”"},{"c":8,"i":86,"x":"1Corinthians 1:9-29 suggests that every (i.e., no exceptions) scholarly “understanding” (i.e., interpretation) of God’s Words disagrees in some sense with God’s intentions. Despite all my claims of “trusting the LORD with all my heart” I confess my own pride precludes me from “coming in the unity of the faith” with any who disagree with me."},{"c":8,"i":87,"x":"That’s my caveat of the reason my prayer is presented to God in humility. My caveat is that I sincerely want to emulate the humble prayer of Jesus when He prayed “Nevertheless, not my will, but thine, be done.”"},{"c":8,"i":88,"x":"That’s my prayer for this book. Amen."},{"c":9,"i":0,"x":"The following definitional distinctions are intended to aid analysis of the inexplicable phenomena that Bible scholars have conflicted “understandings” of God’s Words. I trust these distinctions will help explain my analysis despite any conflicted sectarian “understanding” Bible scholars have taught you to prefer."},{"c":9,"i":1,"x":"Scriptural evaluation vs Polemical accusations"},{"c":9,"i":2,"x":"Polemical accusations are always helpful when analyzing doctrinal beliefs, nevertheless, all my analytical effort simply identifies my own “hypocrisy.” You and I are both included in God’s Romans 3 evaluation that all humans are in conflict with “the oracles of God … yea, let God be true, but every man a liar; as it is written, that thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged … for all have sinned and come short of the glory of God.” The Matthew 7:1-5 “beam that is in my eye” is larger than “any mote that may be in your eye.” I am a “hypocrite, who must first cast out the beam in my own eye” but I admit I don’t do that very well."},{"c":9,"i":3,"x":"Thus, I am not qualified to judge that your “understandings” need correction. If you sense polemic in my writing it is because my writing needs correcting. I simply report what Scripture says. Your fallible “understandings” are your own responsibility."},{"c":9,"i":4,"x":"Please be assured this book is not intended to be polemical. Nevertheless, I cannot deny that Scripture teaches that “leaning unto your own understanding” (i.e., “some did not believe”) about “the oracles of God” is divinely evaluated as “lying” about “the oracles of God” (Rom 3:2-4)."},{"c":9,"i":5,"x":"Scripture vs Bible vs Literature"},{"c":9,"i":6,"x":"In this book I use the term “Scripture” as an abstraction referring to every statement God inspired to be written to the humans who are “predestined” to “understand” God’s Words. However, modern humans are rarely conversant in the language used when “Scripture” was originally inspired to be written."},{"c":9,"i":7,"x":"Thus, I distinguish “Scripture” from “Bible” because each “Bible” is a fallible attempt to translate infallible “Scripture” into some language or dialect other than the original. It is likely each “Bible” contains ambiguity due to the intrinsic fallibility of every human translator. Thus, a concordance is always necessary to reconcile inaccurate and inadequate translations."},{"c":9,"i":8,"x":"Whenever English language books quote Scripture they must copy from a published English translation. The version I typically quote is the King James Version (KJV) (this is the font I use to indicate Bible text). And it will be the old KJV simply because my computer software provides cut-and-paste linkage with Strong’s Concordance. No other reason."},{"c":9,"i":9,"x":"Typical pulpit preachers prefer more modern “Bible” translations but your choice of “Bible” is of no consequence to the thesis of this philosophically conceived book."},{"c":9,"i":10,"x":"My choice to quote from the old KJV simply provides readers with reference consistency while reading. To me it provides cut-and-paste convenience while writing."},{"c":9,"i":11,"x":"I frequently use the philosophically secular term “Literature” when speaking about God’s Words to emphasize the theologically neutral nature of this book."},{"c":9,"i":12,"x":"It is human nature for Christians to have theologically prejudiced opinions about that which God really meant to say. However, I intend this book to be neutral about conflicted theological opinions. I admit my opinions are fallible. But then, that is also true about your own fallible opinions."},{"c":9,"i":13,"x":"Accordingly, “Bible” text is quoted only for literary content and never as proof- text promoting my own theologically prejudiced opinion about God’s Truth."},{"c":9,"i":14,"x":"I intend this book to avoid polemic. However, polemic may slip in simply because I am extremely prejudiced. Please consider your shared fallibility when you think I am lapsing into polemic."},{"c":9,"i":15,"x":"Exegesis vs Eisegesis WRT Exposition vs Interpretation"},{"c":9,"i":16,"x":"“Exegesis” is defined as “the process of careful analytical study of the Bible to produce useful interpretations of those passages. The word comes from the Greek term ἐξηγέομαι (exegeomai), which means to explain or to narrate or to show the way.”"},{"c":9,"i":17,"x":"“Eisegesis” is defined as “reading into the text with a preconceived notion we may have. This can often mean coming to the Scripture with a biased cultural lens that didn’t exist during the time the Bible was written.”"},{"c":9,"i":18,"x":"“Exegesis” always treats God’s Words as “Thus saith the Lord.”"},{"c":9,"i":19,"x":"“Eisegesis” is always “Thus saith I about what the Lord hath said.” “Exegesis” is frequently a tool used to “Exposit” the definition and usage when a Scriptural word was originally inspired to be written."},{"c":9,"i":20,"x":"“Eisegesis” is an interpretation that pretends to be “Exegesis.”"},{"c":9,"i":21,"x":"“Eisegesis” is always a corruption of “Thus saith the Lord” even when theological interpretations essentially agree with “Thus saith the Lord.”"},{"c":9,"i":22,"x":"Without exception every instance of “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture” is the outcome of a conflicted “Eisegesis” of God’s Words even when segments of “Thus saith the Lord” may be “deceitfully” inserted into the sectarian approved message."},{"c":9,"i":23,"x":"Sectarian opinions vs God’s Truth"},{"c":9,"i":24,"x":"Jesus prayed for you and me in John 17:17 “Sanctify them through thy truth: thy word is truth.” It is a philosophical reality that the source for Scriptural Sanctification is always an outcome of “Thus saith the Lord.” By contrast, every sectarian claim of Sanctification is merely an opinion about that which God really meant to say."},{"c":9,"i":25,"x":"Conflicted opinions including opinions about sanctification are always an “Eisegesis” of assumptions about “thy word is truth.”"},{"c":9,"i":26,"x":"The “church being built by Jesus” is based on “thy word is truth.” The churches being built by Bible scholars are based on sectarian “understandings” about “thy word is truth.” Sectarian “understandings” always “deceitfully” compete with the Truth of God’s Words."},{"c":9,"i":27,"x":"A common phenomena is that conflicted sectarian Bible scholars tend to religiously believe their sectarian “understandings” are true reflections of the literal meaning of God’s Words. But every interpretation of God’s immutable Words mutilates “thy word is truth.”"},{"c":9,"i":28,"x":"A Big-Picture-Summary of Scripture"},{"c":9,"i":29,"x":"The Big-Picture-Summary of the sixty-six inspired “oracles of God” (Rom 3:2) reports that “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth” (Gen 1:1) to initiate a demonstration of “the manifold wisdom of God to the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” (Eph 3:10) after which “the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up” (2Pet 3:10)."},{"c":9,"i":30,"x":"The impreciseness of the English word “heaven” is due to the inadequacies of the English language. English provides only one word to describe both the atmosphere surrounding the earth as well as the universe containing stars and galaxies. 2Corinthians 12:2 also speaks of a “third heaven” outside our universe. However, residents of “The third heaven” had never observed “evil and death” before “God created the heaven and the earth.”"},{"c":9,"i":31,"x":"Thus, Ephesians 3:10 reports “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” being educated about the distinction between “good and evil.” God created “the heaven and the earth,” humans, Satan, and Satan’s demons as temporary educational tools to be used in that demonstration."},{"c":9,"i":32,"x":"God’s Purpose for Creation was to teach “the manifold wisdom” of God’s grace and mercy by comparing “God’s gift of everlasting life to the Church being built by Jesus” versus God’s “wrathful penalty of Thou shalt surely die” for the lost people within the earth-bound churches built by Bible scholars."},{"c":9,"i":33,"x":"As of AD60 “the principalities and powers” have observed the initiation of “the Church being built by Jesus” as well as the initiation of the conflicted churches being built by Bible scholars. A few humans have been “redeemed” during the process but “redemption” is merely a tool used to accomplish God’s Purpose. “The whole earth being full of His glory” will not be observed by “The whole earth” until Revelation 13:8 is accomplished."},{"c":9,"i":34,"x":"At “the end of time” everything except the “redeemed” will be eliminated from God’s sight “as far as the east is from the west” just as God intended “from before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":9,"i":35,"x":"The-title-of-this-book vs Christian-pulpit-conflict"},{"c":9,"i":36,"x":"The title of this book “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture” is an abstract notion that cannot be proven – there is no metric for comparing the intrinsic value of Scripture with the questionable value of the conflicted preaching heard from Christian pulpits."},{"c":9,"i":37,"x":"Nevertheless, every time I sense “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture” I simultaneously observe a pulpit preacher conflicting with a rival pulpit preacher. Accordingly, Christian-Pulpit-Conflict ≡ Sectarianism ≡ Christian-Preaching-That- Devalues-Scripture."},{"c":9,"i":38,"x":"That equivalence statement is True despite any Scriptural correctness or incorrectness of the preached message. It does not judge sectarian beliefs nor does it imply polemic."},{"c":9,"i":39,"x":"That equivalence statement is consistent with Romans 3 regarding “The oracles of God.” The Literature of Romans 3 teaches “Let God be true but every man a liar” simply because “all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God.”"},{"c":9,"i":40,"x":"Biblical-Preaching is always based on an Exegetical Exposition of every applicable context of “Thus saith the Lord.” Theologically-Sectarian-Preaching is always an Eisegesis of “Thus saith I about that which the Lord hath said.” But that distinction does not imply error."},{"c":9,"i":41,"x":"Theologically-Sectarian-Preaching is often observed to be structured as a counseling session that recommends emulating sectarian approved Christian behavior while ignoring any Scriptural-deficiency that is observable within the congregation and its pulpit."},{"c":9,"i":42,"x":"Pulpit preachers ought to recognize the distinction between Theologically- Sectarian-Preaching and Biblical-Preaching. But that recognition seems to be hidden by a withholding of “eyes to see and ears to hear” (Isa 6:10, Matt 13:14)."},{"c":9,"i":43,"x":"The definitional distinction between Theologically-Sectarian-Preaching and Biblical-Preaching is critical to an analysis of “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture.”"},{"c":9,"i":44,"x":"The God of Heaven vs Theophanies of God"},{"c":9,"i":45,"x":"The existence of God can be assumed by simply viewing “the Heavens declaring the glory of God” (Ps 19:1). However, God’s identification of Himself is revealed only by exposition of God’s inspired Words. There is no other means for identifying The Holy God who resides in “the Heavenlies.”"},{"c":9,"i":46,"x":"By contrast each sectarian Theophany of God is man-made by Bible scholars. The best Theophanies and the worst Theophanies each interpret or mutilate the inspired and immutable Words of God."},{"c":9,"i":47,"x":"Man-made Theophanies of God are typically identified by the names of historic theologians who are famous for conflicting with each other. I observe the historically named Theophanies of God are Arminius, Augustine, Calvin, Ignatius, Luther, Wesley, etc."},{"c":9,"i":48,"x":"Numerous lesser known Theophanies of God also exist. Lesser known Theophanies of God are honored using man-made titles such as “Pastor,” “Pope,” “Reverend,” “Vicar of Christ,” or etc."},{"c":9,"i":49,"x":"Every man-made Theophany of God believes doctrinal “understandings” which conflict with the “understandings” believed by rival man-made Theophanies of God."},{"c":9,"i":50,"x":"Every sectarian Theophany of God disagrees in some sense about the meaning God really intended when God inspired the original text of Scripture."},{"c":9,"i":51,"x":"Disagreement is the reason sectarians are identified as sectarian."},{"c":9,"i":52,"x":"Satan’s Temptation vs God’s Will"},{"c":9,"i":53,"x":"I observe Genesys 3:1-5 being typically taught to be Satan’s temptation causing Eve to sin. However, the text simply says “the serpent said unto the women, You shall not surely die for God doth know that in the day ye eat thereof, then your eyes shall be opened, and ye shall be as gods, knowing good and evil.”"},{"c":9,"i":54,"x":"The reality is that “The serpent which the LORD God had made” recited partial Truth to Eve despite being Scripturally identified as “the father of lies” (John 8:44) as well as “the god of this world” (2Cor 4:4)."},{"c":9,"i":55,"x":"Satan was used by God to initiate God’s Purpose-For-Creation in the Garden of Eden by speaking partial Truth. In fact, Adam and Eve continued physical life for more than 900 years after disobeying God."},{"c":9,"i":56,"x":"The historic reality is that typical humans live until finally dying of old age after a life of continuously repeated sin."},{"c":9,"i":57,"x":"Contrary to typical hermeneutics, Satan merely interpreted that which God said will occur when Eve chooses to act contrary to God’s “command.” Satan’s partial interpretation emphasized the human aspect of death-by-old-age effectively ignoring the spiritual death of “appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment” (Heb 9:27)."},{"c":9,"i":58,"x":"In that regard, Jesus warned His disciples “Take heed that no man deceives you. For many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and shall deceive many” (Matt 24:4). The words “beguile,” “deceive,” “tempt,” “test,” etc. each have unique Dictionary definitions but, for Scriptural applications, those English words are essentially synonymous as to their outcome."},{"c":9,"i":59,"x":"Both Jesus and the Apostle Paul use variations of the English words “corrupt deception” and “beguile” as warnings. For example, “But I fear, lest by any means, as the serpent beguiled Eve through his subtilty, so your minds should be corrupted from the simplicity that is in Christ” (2Cor 11:3)."},{"c":9,"i":60,"x":"The reality is that Satan is used by God to accomplish “beguilement” and “corrupt deceit” along with pain, suffering, and even crucifixion of God believers like Adam, Eve, Job, “The Son of Man,” and you and me."},{"c":9,"i":61,"x":"The literature of Job makes it clear that Satan can neither “deceive” nor “beguile” nor “tempt” nor harm in any way unless divinely enabled to do so by the authority of a “Holy” God."},{"c":9,"i":62,"x":"“There hath no temptation taken you but such as is common to man: but God is faithful, who will not suffer you to be tempted above that ye are able; but will with the temptation also make a way to escape, that ye may be able to bear it” (1Cor 10:13)."},{"c":9,"i":63,"x":"Adam and Eve and Satan and you and me and every other form of life within the universe is in complete subjection to the God who created cause-and-effect to be intrinsic within all of time-and-space. The end of critical definitions and distinctions"},{"c":9,"i":64,"x":"Perhaps these critical definitions and distinctions will encourage you to ask yourself the philosophical question “Why did an omniscient God who knows both the beginning and the end decide to cause these distinctions?”"},{"c":10,"i":0,"x":"The philosophical premise for this book is that knowing why God created anything yields more “understanding” about the meaning of God’s Words than the opinions of the best educated Bible scholars. In fact, Theological Opinions cannot be “trusted with all your heart” simply because Theological Opinions are always challenged by rival theologians."},{"c":10,"i":1,"x":"Every church affiliation is guilty of “leaning unto the understanding” of Theologically Opinionated Bible scholars. Both sectarian and so-called independent churches affiliate with other churches to evangelize the conflicted opinions of Bible scholars even though those opinions were developed by “leaning unto a conflicted understanding.”"},{"c":10,"i":2,"x":"“Pastor teachers” are hired by churches for pulpit ministry simply because they “Trust” specific Bible scholars. Exceptions are conceivable but “Pastor teachers” are never hired because their pulpit messages teach church attendees how to “trust in the LORD with all thine heart.” That’s the reality taught by this book."},{"c":10,"i":3,"x":"A correct premise is critical"},{"c":10,"i":4,"x":"Arguably the most popular conflicted opinion about the meaning of God’s Words is rooted in “the beginning when God created the heaven and the earth.” The popular opinion is that God reacted (i.e., changed His mind) to Satan’s temptation of Eve to “sin” rather than sovereignly “predestinating” Eve to “sin.” The premise of this book was developed after observing “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture” being rooted on a bad premise about the source of Eve’s “sin.”"},{"c":10,"i":5,"x":"The text of Ephesians 4 was inspired to reveal that God “gives pastor teachers” to churches in order to generate “the unity of the faith” (4:13). But every Bible school taught “pastor teacher” is observed rejecting God’s “gifting” by an intentional rejection of “the unity of the faith” between conflicted sectarian affiliations."},{"c":10,"i":6,"x":"God’s philosophical purpose for creating the universe"},{"c":10,"i":7,"x":"Ephesians 1:5 philosophically teaches God has “predestinated those whose name is written in the Lamb’s book of life unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of His will.” The English word “predestinated” was translated from Strong’s G4309 “προορίζω,” “from <G4253> (pro) and <G3724> (horizo); to limit in advance, i.e. (figurative) predetermine :- determine before, ordain, predestinate.” Despite the legitimacy of translating Strong’s G4309 some Bible scholars reject the concept of “predestination” because it conflicts with their opinionated “understanding” of making-a-decision to “believeth in Him.” However, when Jesus “adopts children” it is always a decision made by deity and never a decision made by humans. Adoption is always “predestinated.”"},{"c":10,"i":8,"x":"It is linguistically absurd to teach “adoption” is the outcome of a volitional decision made by humans who are “dead in trespasses and sin” (Eph 2:1) because “dead” people are divinely precluded from choosing to become “adopted by Jesus Christ to himself.”"},{"c":10,"i":9,"x":"God’s “predestination” is philosophically emphasized in Ephesians 3:2-12 where the Apostle reveals “the mystery” that God created everything “to the intent that the principalities and powers” will be educated by “churches” demonstrating the distinction between the “Tares and Wheat” (Matt 13:24ff). That demonstration was “predestinated” by “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":10,"i":10,"x":"Ephesians 3 philosophically reveals that “the good pleasure of God’s will” was hidden as a “mystery from the foundation of the world” until the AD60 “dispensation of the grace of God which is given me to you-ward” when God inspired the Apostle Paul to partially reveal “the mystery” to “the saints which are at Ephesus.” “The mystery” is scheduled for completion in 2Peter 3:10 when “the day of the Lord will come as a thief in the night; in the which the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up” simply because The Creator no longer needs any of the temporary and disposable tools He created for educating “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.”"},{"c":10,"i":11,"x":"My speculation about why God hid “the mystery”"},{"c":10,"i":12,"x":"Scripture does not reveal the reason God delayed “the dispensation of the grace of God.” However, my observations of human nature suggest that God’s Purpose requires statistical protection from sabotage by well-intentioned humans who believe God wants you and me to resist “the evil of sin” before any of us can be saved. Bible scholars tend to ignore that an omnipotent God neither needs nor wants humans to help by resisting “the evil of sin.” It is a “deceitful lie” to teach Salvation is a shared effort between God and humans."},{"c":10,"i":13,"x":"I speculate that “the manifold wisdom of God” was to statistically protect God’s Purpose-For-Creation from sabotage until after “the Church” was initiated in AD 60 such that humans who have the best of religious intentions to obey God are no longer capable of sabotaging God’s plan by attempting to resist “the evil of sin.”"},{"c":10,"i":14,"x":"One example of the risk of sabotage is that God believing Jews would never vote to crucify Jesus if they had been given “eyes to see and ears to hear” that Jesus was literally their promised Messiah (1Cor 2:8). God believing Jews also attempted to protect God’s “Holiness” by eliminating “blasphemy; because that thou, being a man, makest thyself God” (John 10:33). Similarly modern Bible scholars would never establish doctrinally conflicted sectarian churches if they had “eyes to see and ears to hear” God’s Purpose for “the church.”"},{"c":10,"i":15,"x":"However, as of AD60 there was no longer a statistical risk of sabotage that prevents “the crucifixion of Jesus.” Accordingly, the “mystery” can now be partially revealed simply because “the unified church being built by Jesus” can now be compared with “the evil conflict between sectarian belief systems.” Some"},{"c":10,"i":16,"x":"nd “Dispensational” aspects of God’s plan are essentially complete with the 2 coming of “the LORD” but completion of the “Covenantal” aspects (e.g., “the 144000” of Rev 7:4) of God’s plan seem to follow the resurrection of “the church” while preceding the scheduled destruction of 2Peter 3:10. God’s Purpose-For-Creation will be finalized by the destruction described in 2Peter 3:10."},{"c":10,"i":17,"x":"God is the authority who “predestines” which “lost” humans will be “redeemed to be included within the unified church Jesus is building.” That authority is the basis for the philosophical axiom quoted in John 3:6 “That which is born of the flesh is flesh; and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.”"},{"c":10,"i":18,"x":"Jesus logically builds on that philosophical axiom in John 3:7 where He instructs Nicodemus “Marvel not that I said unto thee, Ye must be born again.”"},{"c":10,"i":19,"x":"That same philosophical axiom is the basis for John 3:16 “that whosoever believeth in him” has already been “born again of the Spirit to inherit the DNA of everlasting life as well as inherited the Spiritual discernment to believe in Him.”"},{"c":10,"i":20,"x":"I assume my speculation is linguistically correct"},{"c":10,"i":21,"x":"All the above is merely my own philosophical speculation about why God withheld revealing “the mystery” until Scripture was almost completely inspired. However, if you find my speculation is disagreeable then what reason do you speculate for withholding revelation of “the mystery” until AD60 when the epistle was inspired to be written?"},{"c":10,"i":22,"x":"Nevertheless, the primary activity demonstrating “the manifold wisdom” of God’s Purpose-For-Creation was “predestined” to be Jesus “coming to seek and save the lost who would populate the church being built by Jesus.” The prehistoric preparation for that demonstration occurred when “the Lamb was slain before the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8, et al)."},{"c":10,"i":23,"x":"The axiom quoted in John 3:6 is the philosophical basis for the comparison between those who are “born of the flesh” versus those who are “born of the Spirit.” Everyone who is “born of the flesh is appointed once to die and after that the judgement.” On the other hand, everyone who is “born again of the Spirit” is “predestined” to inherit a new Spiritual life that is “everlasting and cannot perish” simply because a resurrected “life in the heavenlies” precludes the existence of both “sin and death.”"},{"c":10,"i":24,"x":"Since AD60 there is no longer a statistical risk of God’s Purpose-For-Creation (i.e., the “crucifixion, death, and resurrection”) being sabotaged by humans who insist on helping God by resisting “the evil of sin.”"},{"c":10,"i":25,"x":"God uses conflict between churches to demonstrate the distinction between “good and evil” as well as the distinction between “Holiness and Sinfulness.” As of AD60 the demonstration of that distinction is revealed in Ephesians 3 as being “to the intent that” God’s Purpose-For-Creation is being fulfilled. In other words, the conflict between sectarian churches was philosophically “predestined” by God."},{"c":10,"i":26,"x":"Sectarian churches are populated with both “redeemed” Christians who have “everlasting life that cannot perish” and “unredeemed” Sinners who are “appointed to death and judgement for their sin.” The admixture of “Tares and Wheat” within every sectarian congregation will be resolved “in the time of harvest” according to Matthew 13:30 when Jesus instructs “the reapers to gather ye together first the tares, and bind them in bundles to burn them: but gather the wheat into my barn.” The text is clear that Jesus already knows which of us is “wheat” to be harvested and which of us is “tares” to be burned."},{"c":10,"i":27,"x":"Sectarian conflict philosophically demonstrates that Bible scholars lack “eyes to see and ears to hear” as reported in Isaiah 6:10 and Matthew 13:10ff. Thus, Bible scholars cannot be “trusted” simply because each of them is evaluated as a “liar” in Romans 3:4."},{"c":10,"i":28,"x":"If modern “blind and deaf” Bible scholars “trusted in the Lord with all their heart” they would never “lean unto their own understanding” about the meaning of God’s Words. Even the best Bible scholars build affiliations of conflicted churches rather than “trust” Peter’s declaration in Matthew 16:16-18 “Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God” to which Jesus responds, “I will build my church; and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.” Without exception “the church” being built by Jesus is distinct from every sectarian church built by Bible scholars who exhibit a “predestined” lack of “eyes to see and ears to hear the oracles of God.” That same declaration by Peter is also the philosophical basis for the Matthew 24:4-6 warning by Jesus “Take heed that no man deceive you. For many <Bible scholars> shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and shall deceive many. And ye shall hear of wars and rumors of wars: see that ye be not troubled: for all these things must come to pass, but the end is not yet.”"},{"c":10,"i":29,"x":"Religious conflict (i.e., “wars and rumors of wars”) is the philosophically guaranteed outcome of “coming in my name and deceiving many.” Sectarian conflict is one of many examples of “the gates of hell that shall not prevail against the church being built by Jesus.”"},{"c":10,"i":30,"x":"Bible scholars are guilty of “deception” when they teach Matthew 24 as if it is eschatological discourse. Merriam-webster.com defines “Eschatology” as “a branch of theology concerned with the final events in the history of the world or of humankind.” “Eschatology” studies “the end of everything.”"},{"c":10,"i":31,"x":"The rationale for assuming that Jesus is teaching eschatology is the disciple’s question “when shall these things be?” But Jesus already knew that “wars and rumors of wars” have characterized God’s creation since “Cane killed Abel.” The reality is that “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth” to initiate “the End Times.” Every human including Adam and Eve and you and me has always lived in “the End Times.”"},{"c":10,"i":32,"x":"Obviously there are eschatological events scheduled to occur when “time literally ends” but the scholarly opinion that “wars and rumors of wars” characterize the “End Times” negates the teaching of Jesus that conflicted Bible scholars “shall come in my name” with the best of religious intentions – Bible scholars really believe they serve God."},{"c":10,"i":33,"x":"Bible scholars have been philosophically “deceived” to believe “the lie” that “wars and rumors of wars” eschatologically indicate “the End Times.” Some Bible scholars even “deceptively” teach that a sovereign God who created everything does not always get His own way. Search the web for “Does God always get his way” to see examples of theological opinions being taught by Bible scholars who sincerely believe they are serving God by “leaning unto their own understandings.”"},{"c":10,"i":34,"x":"Every eschatological opinion about “the End Times” is at risk of being incorrect simply because “the End” has not yet happened. That kind of philosophical “deception” is another example of “the gates of hell that shall not prevail against the church being built by Jesus.”"},{"c":10,"i":35,"x":"The philosophical reality is that every event in time-and-space brings us closer to “the End.” Reality suggests “the Beginning and the End” is merely a series of events that were scheduled (i.e., “predestined”) “by the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":10,"i":36,"x":"If God’s Word is correct then the “cause-and-effect of time-and-space” (i.e., “predestination”) is the means chosen by God for sequentially educating “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.” Creation of a sequential “cause-and-effect” environment was necessary because “Evil” cannot exist where God resides. Cause- and-effect is a created reality simply because absolutely nothing exists “in the heavenlies” that can demonstrate the distinction between “Good and Evil.” As of AD60 that sequential distinction had already been observed by “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies” because they can literally see “the end of time.”"},{"c":10,"i":37,"x":"When God’s education of “the principalities and powers” is finished in time-and- space “the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up” (2Peter 3:10). There will no longer be any need for “the sequential cause-and-effect of time-and-space” simply because God’s Purpose-For-Creation will be complete."},{"c":10,"i":38,"x":"God’s philosophical purpose is not ambiguous"},{"c":10,"i":39,"x":"“Deceived” Bible scholars teach the opinion that Scripture contains ambiguity that must be interpreted before it can be believed and obeyed. Those scholars “lean unto their own understanding” to manufacture conflicted hermeneutical rules for philosophically interpreting that which God really meant to say. And sectarian Bible schools teach those hermeneutics “to the intent that” conflicted “understandings” of God’s meaning are being preached from the pulpit in your own church."},{"c":10,"i":40,"x":"The philosophical reality is that the “deception” of religious leadership is intended by God as evidenced in Isaiah 6:9-10 as well as repeated by Jesus in Matthew 13:13-15. God intends the outcome of that kind of “deception” to be diverse forms of philosophical “wars and rumors of wars” as well as “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture.”"},{"c":10,"i":41,"x":"Without exception every instance of philosophical and religious “wars and rumors of wars” is the outcome of God’s Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":10,"i":42,"x":"God’s plan has always been to demonstrate the distinction between “good and evil” by creating “wars and rumors of wars” between philosophers. And some of those philosophers are also Bible scholars. Rival Bible schools teach rival doctrine “to the intent that” pulpit conflict is common between Bible school trained “pastor teachers.” This book analyzes the preaching of “pastor teachers” who studied at Bible schools established to compete with rival sectarian affiliated Bible schools. Religious leaders are taught that God’s Holy Words are difficult for mere humans to “understand.” Pulpit conflict indicates religious leaders think of themselves “more highly than they ought to think” (Rom 12:3). The evidence suggests that every instance of “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture” is motivated by the conflicted opinions taught by Godly and well-intentioned Bible scholars who have the best of religious intentions to teach “pastor teachers” to lead sectarian churches to believe sectarian approved conflicted doctrine."},{"c":10,"i":43,"x":"The observation of pervasive pulpit conflict between the wisest and best educated “pastor teachers” is confirmation of that which God inspired to be reported in 1Corinthians 1:26-29"},{"c":10,"i":44,"x":"For ye see your calling, brethren, how that not many wise men after the flesh,"},{"c":10,"i":45,"x":"not many mighty, not many noble, are called. But God hath chosen the foolish things"},{"c":10,"i":46,"x":"of the world to confound the wise; and God hath chosen the weak things of the world"},{"c":10,"i":47,"x":"to confound the things which are mighty. And base things of the world, and things"},{"c":10,"i":48,"x":"which are despised, hath God chosen, yea, and things which are not, to bring to"},{"c":10,"i":49,"x":"nought things that are so that no flesh should glory in his presence."},{"c":10,"i":50,"x":"In other words, only “few” Bible scholars have been “called and elected” to be saved despite all the decisions they think they have made."},{"c":10,"i":51,"x":"This book is a philosophical analysis of my personal observation that Christianity is characterized by sectarian disagreement about the Romans 3:2 “oracles of God.” Disagreement about the approved method for “redemption” of sinners is a pervasively common example."},{"c":10,"i":52,"x":"Some Bible scholars argue that “redemption” is attained by the free will decisions made by humans “who are already dead in trespasses and sin.” Rival Bible scholars argue that “redemption” is “predestined.”"},{"c":10,"i":53,"x":"The wisest and best educated Bible scholars argue about the Biblical means of “redemption” of sinners rather than “trust in the LORD with all thine heart.” The mere existence of ecclesiastical conflict makes it impossible to get consensus about what “the oracles of God” really mean. Every theological contradiction can be resolved by “rightly dividing the Word of Truth” but the publicly observable evidence is that preachers are being taught to hermeneutically interpret Biblical text rather than “Study to shew thyself approved unto God, a workman that needeth not to be ashamed, rightly dividing the word of Truth” (2Tim 2:15)."},{"c":10,"i":54,"x":"I have never attended an accredited Bible school so I have no academic credential for analyzing sectarian approved doctrine. But credentials are useless when rival Bible schools are publicly observed educating pulpit preachers to prepare messages according to a proprietary hermeneutic that results in a scholarly assumption about that which an immutable God really meant to say."},{"c":10,"i":55,"x":"I admit my writing could be viewed as polemic. But the publicly observable evidence of sectarian approved pulpit conflict forces me to ask who or what is the real literary source for the messages being preached in churches that claim the philosophical absurdity that their conflicted doctrinal opinions are based on God’s Words?"},{"c":10,"i":56,"x":"Sectarian conflict between the wisest and best Bible school educated pulpit preachers indicates the text commonly used for preparation of pulpit messages is a proprietary Dataset of Literature authored by multiple sectarian approved Bible scholars who teach their conflicted hermeneutical interpretations that result in sectarian approved “deceitful lies” about the “oracles of God.”"},{"c":10,"i":57,"x":"Some in my own family believe God inspired ambiguity into Scripture. My own family has been “deceived” into assuming the absurdity that God intends local church “pastor teachers” to clarify God’s ambiguity for the benefit of church attendees who lack Bible school training. The “deceptive” means used by sectarians to clarify Scriptural ambiguity is summarized by the English term “hermeneutics.”"},{"c":10,"i":58,"x":"However, using hermeneutics is never “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart and He shall direct thy path.” Hermeneutics is always “leaning unto your own understanding.” Dependence on hermeneutics is an absurdity for those who “trust in the LORD with all their heart.” That kind of absurdity forces the philosophical question “Why would an omniscient and omnipotent God allow anyone to clarify any ambiguity which an omniscient God may have inspired?”"},{"c":10,"i":59,"x":"Isn’t God capable to provide “eyes to see and ears to hear” for those whom God intends to “understand” God’s Words? It is philosophically true that being taught to depend on Bible scholars to interpret the meaning of God’s Words de facto means you are not “trusting the LORD with all your heart” and God is not “directing your path.”"},{"c":10,"i":60,"x":"If Scriptural ambiguity can be shown to literally exist it absolutely must be assumed as fulfilling God’s Purpose-For-Creation. But why would an omniscient God inspire ambiguity? Doesn’t God want us to “know the Truth so the Truth can set us free” (John 8:32)? God’s answer to those questions is likely contrary to the “deceitful” teachings of the Bible scholars whom you “Trust with all your heart.”"},{"c":10,"i":61,"x":"Without exception, accusations of doctrinal error are polemic. That’s the reason I avoid accusations of doctrinal error by relying on my own observation that every instance of Biblically based pulpit conflict is the outcome of a sectarian hermeneutical system of interpretation. Biblically based pulpit conflict is always the outcome of Eisegesis rather than Exegesis. The Christian religion is ostensibly based on the Words originally written in the literary compendium we identify using the English word “Scripture.” But that compendium has remained unchanged for thousands of years. Every sectarian conflict should have been resolved in that length of time yet Bible scholars are conflicted."},{"c":10,"i":62,"x":"This book suggests that all pulpit conflict is a cause-and-effect that was intended “In the beginning when God created the heaven and the earth.”"},{"c":10,"i":63,"x":"It is interesting to note that those who rely on sectarian approved hermeneutics typically use the honorific “LORD” to address the Author who inspired the compendium. Modern conflict exists simply because those who address the Author of the compendium as “LORD” also rely on a sectarian created Theophany of God to manufacture the hermeneutics that an omniscient “LORD” seems to have forgotten."},{"c":10,"i":64,"x":"Exegesis of “the LORD’s” compendium reveals God’s Truth. Eisegesis of “the LORD’s” compendium reveals conflicted sectarian opinions. I suggest the pervasiveness of conflicted sectarian opinions explains why “the gates of hell prevail against” every “church” except “the church being built by Jesus Christ.”"},{"c":10,"i":65,"x":"Christianity is a religion composed of philosophically conflicted sectarian affiliations which rely on sincere but conflicted Bible scholars to hermeneutically eisegete the meaning they assume God intended. An incorrect assumption of ambiguity has been “deceptively” inflicted upon Truth by the wisest and best educated Bible scholars."},{"c":10,"i":66,"x":"It is obvious that Biblical exposition is sometimes heard from sectarian pulpits. Nevertheless, every Bible school teaches “pastors and teachers to trust” the opinions of a sectarian created Theophany of God rather than “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart.” If that analysis is correct then Bible school taught sectarian preachers ought to admit they “lean unto the understanding of a Theophany of God” rather than “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart.”"},{"c":10,"i":67,"x":"The mere existence of sectarian pulpit conflict irrefutably indicates Bible schools have failed to teach the academic skill of reading God’s Literary-Compendium “to the intent of rightly dividing” every statement about every identifiable subject but especially every statement about the literary subject of God’s-Purpose-For-Creation."},{"c":10,"i":68,"x":"God’s Purpose-For-Creation is fulfilled by a bad premise"},{"c":10,"i":69,"x":"If God’s Purpose-For-Creation is to demonstrate the distinction between “good and evil” then conflicted hermeneutics literally fulfills God’s Purpose that the “evil” of scholarly “deception” will be observed by “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.” The inexplicable “mystery” is that Pulpit conflict literally fulfils God’s Purpose- For-Creation. Without exception, every Biblical hermeneutical system is manufactured to analyze what God is doing to react to “sin” rather than to ask why an omniscient God chose to create “the evil of sin.” The pervasiveness of religious conflict suggests God’s Purpose-For-Creation is divinely “misunderstood.” That’s why Eve sinned immediately after God provided everything that sustains life. That’s why “God’s Chosen People” sinned immediately after Moses received “The Law.” “Called and elect Christians” sin immediately after being “redeemed.” “Pastor teachers” sin immediately after being “gifted by God for the perfecting of the saints, for the work of the ministry, for the edifying of the body of Christ.” “Sinning.” Everything is done according to God’s plan."},{"c":10,"i":70,"x":"“From the foundation of the world” God’s Purpose-For-Creation has been to demonstrate the distinction between “good and evil.” Thus, the statistical risk has always been that religious God believers would resist “the evil of sin.” However, God believers resisting “the evil of sin” would hinder God’s Purpose-For-Creation so an omniscient God has eliminated any probability of that kind of statistical risk by hiding His Purpose as a “mystery.”"},{"c":10,"i":71,"x":"Modern Bible school education is typically based on the “deceptively” incorrect premise that everything was created because “God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life.” However, the English term “whosoever” in John 3:16 is never a universal inclusive as “deceptively” assumed by some Bible school hermeneutics. For example, the statement “whosoever believeth Ford makes the best cars” is never a universal inclusive of everyone who drives a car."},{"c":10,"i":72,"x":"“Whosoever believeth in him” is always the outcome of “predestination unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of his will” (Eph 1:5ff). It is an “outcome” rather than a “requirement.”"},{"c":10,"i":73,"x":"It is philosophically conclusive that both Testaments of the Bible are being mis- interpreted by conflicted sectarian hermeneutics deliberately designed to support the invalid premise that anyone can be saved. That premise is “deceptive” simply because it is a linguistic absurdity. And yet that seems to be exactly as God intended."},{"c":10,"i":74,"x":"Every “deceptive” interpretation fulfills God’s Purpose-For-Creation. A literal “Trust in the LORD with all your heart” is manifest by continuously asking “why” would an omniscient God do it that way? God created a philosophical Case Study"},{"c":10,"i":75,"x":"The reality is that God created everything as a Case Study to teach “the manifold wisdom of God to the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.” God initiated His Case Study by planting “the tree of the knowledge of Good and Evil” in the midst of the Garden. God may have also had additional reasons for creation but God’s inspired epistle to the Ephesians reports only this single reason."},{"c":10,"i":76,"x":"The subject studied in secular Case Studies is always hidden to protect statistical validity – the statistical term “double blind” is used to describe Case Study security. Search the web for “double blind case study” if you are not familiar with the term."},{"c":10,"i":77,"x":"I believe the necessity for “double blind” security is the philosophical reason God’s Purpose-For-Creation had to be hidden as a “mystery” until the epistle to the Ephesians was inspired in AD60."},{"c":10,"i":78,"x":"Modern Bible school teachers and students ought to be aware the “mystery” was revealed several thousand years ago in AD60 with the Apostle Paul’s conditional KJV statement “If ye have heard of the dispensation of the grace of God which is given me to you-ward” (Eph 3:2)."},{"c":10,"i":79,"x":"That conditional introduces Paul’s explanation that “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” has always been to educate “the principalities and powers in the Heavenlies” by creating a double-blind time-and-space Case Study to be used as a cause-and-effect teaching tool."},{"c":10,"i":80,"x":"Double-blind Case Study participants (i.e., disposable humans) are continuously being replaced by new disposable “born of the flesh” humans to populate God’s time- and-space laboratory until God’s Purpose for His time-and-space Case Study has been completed."},{"c":10,"i":81,"x":"The apostolic initialization of “The Church which is being built by Jesus” was completed sometime prior to AD60 so there is no longer any need for “double blind” Case Study security. All that remains is for “the principalities and powers” to observe the foolishness of Bible scholars as they create every cause-and-effect of “evil” sectarian conflict."},{"c":10,"i":82,"x":"Before creation it was impossible for “Seraphim” to intellectually “cry unto another, and say, Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory” simply because “the whole earth” did not yet exist."},{"c":10,"i":83,"x":"The need for a “double blind” Case Study also explains why conflicted hermeneutics are taught in Bible schools. Bible scholars and the Bible schools they established were “predestined from before the foundation of the world” to teach conflicted hermeneutics. The invalid premise of Free-Will is assumed by “many” sectarians. But there is literally no such thing as Free Will in all of God’s creation just as there is no such thing as a Random Event. God’s creation operates according to the cause-and-effect of Newton’s 2nd Law of Motion. For example, the location of every celestial body is known in perpetuity. The sectarian premise of a Free-Will effectively rejects God’s Sovereign Will."},{"c":10,"i":84,"x":"Readers who are Biblically proficient are also requested to appraise my quotes from Scripture to affirm I have accurately applied “Thus saith the Lord” rather than manufacture the kind of polemic that would have been discovered and rejected by the Bereans in Acts 17:11."},{"c":10,"i":85,"x":"I humbly confess I am a member of the set of those whom God evaluates as “liars” in Romans 3. Thus, my prideful words ought never be conflated with statements of Truth. Nevertheless, I humbly request that you pause reading my book to meditate on the philosophical implications to World History if Adam and Eve had obeyed God and the implications to World History if every Biblical scholar would “trust in the LORD with all your heart and lean not unto thine own understanding.”"},{"c":10,"i":86,"x":"The most significant question asked in this book"},{"c":10,"i":87,"x":"As you meditate on those philosophical implications please also meditate on this particularly revealing question:"},{"c":10,"i":88,"x":"Can you conceive any justification for the existence of so many doctrinally similar Sectarian Churches and Affiliations who compete with each other despite believing similar Biblically based doctrines?"},{"c":10,"i":89,"x":"That single question may be the most critically revealing question asked in this entire book. Sectarian “pastor teachers” deliberately and purposefully reject “the unity of the faith” as gifted by God (Eph 4:11ff)."},{"c":11,"i":0,"x":"The prior chapter presented a Philosophical justification for this book. This chapter presents a Biblical justification for the same book."},{"c":11,"i":1,"x":"Even though I am the author of this book my pen name is Theophilus. The only reason my pen name is significant is that I am addressed in both Biblical documents divinely inspired to be authored by Luke."},{"c":11,"i":2,"x":"This is the way I am addressed in the Gospel of Luke."},{"c":11,"i":3,"x":"Forasmuch as many have taken in hand to set forth in order a declaration of"},{"c":11,"i":4,"x":"those things which are most surely believed among us, even as they delivered them"},{"c":11,"i":5,"x":"unto us, which from the beginning were eyewitnesses, and ministers of the word; it"},{"c":11,"i":6,"x":"seemed good to me also, having had perfect understanding of all things from the"},{"c":11,"i":7,"x":"very first, to write unto thee in order, most excellent Theophilus, that thou mightest"},{"c":11,"i":8,"x":"know the certainty of those things wherein thou hast been instructed."},{"c":11,"i":9,"x":"And this is the way I am addressed in the Acts of the Apostles."},{"c":11,"i":10,"x":"The former treatise have I made, O Theophilus, of all that Jesus began both to"},{"c":11,"i":11,"x":"do and teach, until the day in which he was taken up, after that he through the Holy"},{"c":11,"i":12,"x":"Ghost had given commandments unto the apostles whom he had chosen."},{"c":11,"i":13,"x":"Luke wants Theophilus to be aware of certain Truths"},{"c":11,"i":14,"x":"Luke teaches “the certainty of those things” (Lk 1:4) such as “the Son of Man is come to seek and to save that which was lost” (Lk 19:10) by “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God to be crucified and slain by wicked hands” (Acts 2:23)."},{"c":11,"i":15,"x":"I am “certain” that the English term “the Son of Man” refers to the offspring of the womb of a human female virgin named Mary (Lk 1:26ff). Mary’s child was named Jesus as ordered by “the angel Gabriel.”"},{"c":11,"i":16,"x":"Jesus is “The Son of Man” simply because Mary, His mother, was descended from Adam and Eve."},{"c":11,"i":17,"x":"I am also “certain” that Mary’s virgin womb was impregnated by “God’s Holy Spirit” (Lk 1:35). Thus, Jesus was also the “Son of God” simply because Jesus was a descendant of God the Father."},{"c":11,"i":18,"x":"Both “certainties” were “predestined” by “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” such that the “Son of Man” co-existed with the “Son of God” in the incarnated human body of “the Lamb slain before the foundation of the world.” That co-existence was announced by Jesus in John 14:7 when “the incarnated Son of Man” declared “If ye had known me, ye should have known my Father also: and from henceforth ye know him, and have seen him.”"},{"c":11,"i":19,"x":"That co-existence also established God’s DNA pattern for the “born of the flesh humans” whom “the Son of Man came to seek and to save.” It is “certain” that every “born of the flesh” human co-exists with a “born of the Spirit” human whose name was registered in “the book of Life before the foundation of the world” (Rev 13:8). Thus, I am “certain” that both “human life” and “Spiritual life” are “the gift of God lest any man should boast” (Eph 2:9)."},{"c":11,"i":20,"x":"The English word “lost” in Luke 19:10 was translated from the Greek word “ἀπόλλυμι”; Strong’s G622, “from <G575> (apo) and the base of <G3639> (olethros); to destroy fully (reflexive to perish, or lose), literal or figurative :- destroy, die, lose, mar, perish.” That definition applies to every “born of the flesh” human whom God made to be a child of “your father the devil” (John 8:44) who is also “the god of this world” (2Cor 4:4)."},{"c":11,"i":21,"x":"“The devil” was created by God to be “the god of this world” who owns every “born of the flesh” human including “The Son of Man” who “died and after that was judged to be without sin so that He could ransom the lost.” “The determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” planed the “redemption” that paid the ransom price established to purchase “a few” (Matt 7:14) of the “slaves of sin” (Rom 6:17) who were owned by “the god of this world.”"},{"c":11,"i":22,"x":"“The Son of Man” was divinely prepared for His assignment to “redeem that which is lost” from ownership by “the god of this world” by being “led by the Spirit into the wilderness, being forty days tempted of the devil” (Matt 4:1). The fact that “he fasted forty days and forty nights” simply emphasizes that Jesus was “tempted of the devil” both physically as well as morally. In fact, the incarnate Jesus “was tempted in all points” as the worst-case example of every “born of the flesh” human slave owned by “your father the devil.”"},{"c":11,"i":23,"x":"God established “the born of the flesh Son of Man” as the final “Sin-Offering” which was officially initiated in Leviticus 4:1ff even though “Able,” the second son of Adam and Eve implied that he already knew about that “Sin-Offering.” “The Son of Man” declared His assignment was complete “when Jesus had cried with a loud voice, he said, Father, into thy hands I commend my spirit: and having said thus, he gave up the ghost” (Lk 23:46). Until that instant “the Son of Man” was still capable of submitting to “the god of this world.” However, while still on the cross “he said, it is finished: and he bowed his head, and gave up the ghost” after which He was buried as a “born of the flesh” human who had died."},{"c":11,"i":24,"x":"The only thing that distinguished “The Son of Man” from every other “born of the flesh” human is that Jesus “was in all points tempted like as we are, yet without sin” (Heb 4:15) – no other “born of the flesh” human can make that claim."},{"c":11,"i":25,"x":"The official Levitical command to sacrifice for infractions of the Law was divinely replaced when God “abolished the Law” (Eph 2:15) as reported in Galatians 4:4-5 “But when the fulness of the time was come, God sent forth his Son, made of a woman, made under the law, to redeem them that were under the law, that we might receive the adoption of sons.”"},{"c":11,"i":26,"x":"It was necessary for “the Son of Man” to be crucified because neither “God-the- Father” nor “God-the-Son” can be “tempted to sin” nor can either of them “die.” Only the shed blood of a completely “sinless” human could provide the ransom paid to “your father the devil” for the “redemption” of those who had been born to be “slaves to sin” (Rom 6:16)."},{"c":11,"i":27,"x":"Some Bible school trained religious leaders teach that Ephesians 1:7 defines “redemption” to be nothing more than “forgiveness of sin.” Please affirm that “redemption from sin” can never be conflated with “forgiveness of sin.” Non- equivalence was emphasized by Jesus when He charged those whom He “forgave” to not reveal their “forgiveness” to anyone because that knowledge could sabotage His eventual crucifixion by the most religious God believers in the world."},{"c":11,"i":28,"x":"The conclusion of Luke’s Certain Truth"},{"c":11,"i":29,"x":"The point of this review of Luke’s assertions of “certain” Truth is to allow God’s own Words to describe “the manifold wisdom of God to the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God” (Eph 3:10). And Jesus, “the Son of Man” predicted “I will build my church and the gates of Hell shall not prevail against it” (Matt 16:18). “The gates of Hell” are not defined but “prevailing against unity” is the equivalent of religiously “leaning unto your own conflicted understandings.”"},{"c":11,"i":30,"x":"The initiation of “THE CHURCH” is critically important to the fulfillment of God’s Purpose-For-Creation. However, “seeking and saving the lost” is merely a single step in the process of “Jesus building His CHURCH” so that “the manifold wisdom of God’s salvation” can be demonstrated to “the principalities and powers in heavenly places.”"},{"c":11,"i":31,"x":"“The eleven disciples” (Matt 28:16-20) were commissioned to “Go ye therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Ghost: teaching them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you: and, lo, I am with you always, even unto the end of the world.” But none of “the eleven disciples” is reported to have appealed to Isaiah 49:6 “I will also give thee for a light to the Gentiles, that thou mayest be my salvation unto the end of the earth.” Without exception, the Apostle Paul is only Apostle described in Scripture as fulfilling God’s promise to Isaiah when Paul became “the Apostle to the Gentiles” (Rom 11:1-13). Accordingly, the so-called “Church Age” is one of the “Dispensations” revealed in Scripture."},{"c":11,"i":32,"x":"The only non-apostolic “Christian church” identified in Scripture was led by James, the half-brother of Jesus. It seems the church located in Jerusalem was populated entirely by Jews who believed that the crucified and resurrected Jesus merely fulfilled the Law of Moses. Churches organized to practice some denominational form of obedience to the Law of Moses are never Biblically organized. By contrast, God is the Organizer of “the unified church being built by Jesus.”"},{"c":11,"i":33,"x":"Please affirm that neither “the eleven disciples” nor “the apostle to the Gentiles” has responsibility to “seek and save that which is lost.” Only Jesus has that divine responsibility. And only “the eleven disciples” were given the “Great Commission to go into all the world and preach the Gospel.” “Preaching the Gospel” proclaims the Good News rather than “win souls” (Prov 11:30)."},{"c":11,"i":34,"x":"God’s Purpose-For-Creation was never that Adam and Eve and their descendants would be without sin else there would be no one for Jesus to “Seek and Save.” Rather, every descendant of Adam and Eve is a sinner who is “born of the flesh” to be “that which is lost.” Every “born of the flesh” human is a temporary and disposable tool for demonstrating the need for “the Son of Man to seek and save that which was lost.” Adam and Eve immediately demonstrated their need for salvation exactly as God intended (i.e., “predestined”). Every “born of the flesh” descendant of Adam and Eve continues to demonstrate that need exactly as God intended (i.e., “predestined”)."},{"c":11,"i":35,"x":"It has always been a “mystery” that Adam and Eve and their descendants each enter life as children of “your father the devil” to be used as an object lesson in the education of “the principalities and powers.” Readers who are Biblically proficient are asked to affirm Ephesians 3:2-10 literally reveals “The mystery” of God’s Purpose- For-Creation."},{"c":11,"i":36,"x":"Luke’s assertion of “certain Truth” is the God inspired source for all the above conclusions derived by “Trusting the LORD with all my heart.”"},{"c":11,"i":37,"x":"Luke was there when the Gospel was challenged"},{"c":11,"i":38,"x":"Luke also wants Theophilus to know “the certainty” that the Grecian Luke “had perfect understanding of all things from the very first” (Lk 1:3). That suggests that Luke was present when “some of them were men of Cyprus and Cyrene, which, when they were come to Antioch, spoke unto the Grecians, preaching the Lord Jesus” (Acts 11:20). Or else Luke’s assertion “from the very first” may refer to the Acts 13:2 event when “the Holy Ghost said, separate me Barnabas and Saul for the work whereunto I have called them.” Or “from the very first” may reveal that Luke literally interviewed Mary after the birth of Jesus was angelically announced."},{"c":11,"i":39,"x":"Doctor Luke may have already been hired to serve as the personal physician of a prominent Jewish Pharisee named Saul."},{"c":11,"i":40,"x":"Scripture is not clear when Luke’s “perfect understanding” began. But it is not important because tradition teaches that Luke was “the Grecian Doctor” who always traveled with Saul/Paul. Thus, “the certainty of” 1st Century God-believers challenging the doctrine taught by “Barnabas and Saul/Paul” was personally observed by “The Grecian Doctor” Luke as those events happened in time-and-space after “Barnabas and Saul” had been “called and separated” by “the Holy Ghost” (Acts 13:1ff) but before the Acts 15 Church council was called."},{"c":11,"i":41,"x":"The 1st Century challenges by Jewish God-believers were driven by their faith that a “righteous” God would never “abolish” the requirement to obey “The Law of Commandments” which God explained so thoroughly in the books of Leviticus (the 1st report of the Levitical Law) and Deuteronomy (the 2nd report of the Levitical Law)."},{"c":11,"i":42,"x":"Perhaps your Bible scholars taught you to believe that obeying the “Law of Commandments” describes the process by which you attain the Holiness of Entire Sanctification. But the Old Testament reveals “God’s righteous Law” being continuously disobeyed by “God’s Chosen People.” The uncomfortable truth is that everyone shares the same guilt as “God’s chosen people.” God teaches that even the slightest instance of “sin” must be paid for by a blood-shedding sacrifice. Ephesians 2:15 teaches “The Law of Commandments” was never intended to “redeem sinners.”"},{"c":11,"i":43,"x":"The 1st Century Jewish believers assumed the means for attaining Entire Sanctification was obedience of the Mosaic Law. Some modern sectarians essentially agree with those 1st Century God-believers that Entire Sanctification is a process that is divinely shared between God and humans. Some sectarians literally teach the Ephesians 1:7 divine gift of “redemption” is nothing more than “forgiveness of sins” that precedes Entire Sanctification. But Ephesians 2:15 is clear that obedience is “abolished” as the means for attaining Entire Sanctification because “the Law” never offered “redemption.”"},{"c":11,"i":44,"x":"“God’s Chosen People” as well as some modern sectarians are correct that “Holiness unto the LORD” is defined by God’s “righteous Law.” However, neither God nor Moses nor any prophet taught God’s “righteous Law” financed “redemption” from Satan’s ownership."},{"c":11,"i":45,"x":"Contrary to a common sectarian “understanding” of Ephesians 1:7, “forgiveness” is merely a function of “redemption.” “Forgiveness” is neither equivalent to nor a substitute for “redemption.” “Redemption” finances an “everlasting” purchase from the ownership of Satan while “forgiveness” is always temporary (i.e., Jesus said “go and sin no more”). In other words, Christians are “forgiven” eternally only because they have been eternally “redeemed” rather than receiving a temporary “forgiveness” that must be followed by the command to “go and sin no more.”"},{"c":11,"i":46,"x":"It is intuitively obvious an omniscient God never expected “God’s Chosen People” to comply with “the Law” simply because “God’s Chosen People” were “predestined” by God to “crucify the Lord of Glory” (1Cor 2:8)."},{"c":11,"i":47,"x":"Biblically proficient readers know the assumptions of 1st Century God-believing “Chosen People” were wrong because “the Apostle who was commissioned by the resurrected Jesus as the Apostle to the Gentiles” (Acts 9:15) was inspired to reveal that “abolishment of the law of commandments” has always been God’s Purpose “which in other ages was not made known unto the sons of men (e.g., God’s Chosen People), as it is now revealed unto his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit … To the intent that now, unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places, might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God” (Eph 3:2-10)."},{"c":11,"i":48,"x":"God’s Purpose-For-Creation was to teach “the knowledge of good and evil” to “the principalities and powers in heavenly places” so they could intelligently worship God by declaring “Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory” (Is 6:3). Education of “the principalities and powers” divinely began by viewing Eve’s proclivity to “evil lust” (James 1:14-15) and continued by viewing that same “evil lust” in “God’s chosen people.”"},{"c":11,"i":49,"x":"As of AD60 the time-and-space education of “the principalities and powers” has been partially completed by the Apostle Paul’s initiation of “THE CHURCH being built by Jesus.” The next step of God’s Purpose is the “resurrection” of earthly church attendees who have been “called and elect” out of “the earthly version of THE CHURCH” to be instantly reinstated as “the Heavenly version of THE CHURCH which Jesus is building.”"},{"c":11,"i":50,"x":"Eventually, “the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up” (2Peter 3:10). The time-and-space attribute of creation will no longer exist because a completed educational process eliminates any further need for the intrinsic cause- and-effect of time-and-space. Before “God created the heavens and the earth” “The principalities and powers in the 3rd heaven” (2Cor 12:2) had no opportunity to learn about “evil.” But, since “creation of the heavens and the earth, the principalities and powers” literally observe every time- and-space occurrence of “the evil of sin.”"},{"c":11,"i":51,"x":"Establishment of “THE CHURCH” was “predestined by the manifold wisdom of God before the foundation of the world.” God’s Old Testament teaches the need for “the lost to be sought and saved” (Gal 3:24). God’s New Testament teaches God’s “mysterious” plan for resolving that need. Both Testaments describe disposable humans being used to demonstrate “God’s manifold wisdom” to “the principalities and powers in the heavenlies.”"},{"c":11,"i":52,"x":"“The time-and-space version of THE CHURCH” is populated with both “redeemed” and “un-redeemed” God-believers. But “the Heavenly version of THE CHURCH” is populated with only “redeemed” God-believers who have been “Spiritually born again to have the DNA of everlasting life” and whose “names were written in The Lamb’s Book of Life before the foundation of the world.”"},{"c":11,"i":53,"x":"God’s Purpose-For-Creation was “To the intent that the principalities and powers” could view “the coming of the Son of Man to seek and to save” everyone who was listed in “the Lamb’s book of life” (Rev 20:12). Accordingly, “The Law was our schoolmaster to bring the called and elect unto Christ so that they might be justified according to the faithfulness of God to fulfil His promise” (Gal 3:23-25). The evidence also suggests God created humans to have the appearance of self-generated faith but a self-generated human faith has never justified anything. “God’s justifying Faith is not of yourselves. God’s justifying Faith is always the gift of God. God’s justifying Faith is not of works lest any man should boast” (Eph 2:8-9)."},{"c":11,"i":54,"x":"The reality is that God does whatever God wants to do despite any conflicted opinions about the self-generated “faith” that may be manufactured by sectarian Christians who have been “deceived” into believing “the lie” that they were given a volitional free will to make those kinds of “everlasting life” decisions."},{"c":11,"i":55,"x":"Those whom “Jesus came to seek and save” were “predestinated unto the adoption of children by Jesus Christ to Himself, according to the good pleasure of His will” (Eph 1:5). “Adopted children” never “choose” their adopting parents. Every “adopted child of God” has been divinely “chosen” (i.e., “called and elect”) by “the good pleasure of Jesus Christ” to eventually become the “redeemed” population of “The Heavenly Version of THE CHURCH.”"},{"c":11,"i":56,"x":"Every “un-redeemed” and “un-adopted” member of “the earthly version of THE CHURCH” will spend eternity in Hell along with “their father the devil” simply because they are each “vessels of wrath fitted to destruction” (Rom 9:20ff). By contrast, the “called and elect” are re-created as “vessels unto honor” who will “not perish but have everlasting life” (John 3:16) simply because they have been “born again of the Spirit” (John 3:3ff) to inherit a Spiritual DNA that guarantees “everlasting life” as well as enables “believeth in Him.”"},{"c":11,"i":57,"x":"Each “calling and election” is an outcome of God’s Purpose-For-Creation. God “predestined” that Purpose by creating a “world” having a dimension of time-and- space controlled by cause-and-effect. It is impossible for an immutable God’s cause- and-effect to be altered by “whosoever believeth in Him.” Accordingly, church attendees who depend on self-generated “faith” have never been Spiritually “born again.” Saving “faith” is “not of yourselves: that kind of faith is the gift of God” (Eph 2:8)."},{"c":11,"i":58,"x":"Church attendees typically listen to stories about Jesus yet they remain “un- redeemed and un-adopted” humans who are owned by “the God of this world” until the God of Heaven “lovingly and graciously” causes (i.e., “predestines”) a “new Spiritual birth.”"},{"c":11,"i":59,"x":"God’s “determinate counsel and foreknowledge” has no provision for volitionally generated belief. God’s created cause-and-effect results in religious conflict between sectarian affiliations being divinely established by precluding “many who say to me in that day, Lord, Lord” (Matt 7:22ff) from “understanding God’s Words” even though they were trained at an approved Bible school. “There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth” (Lk 13:28). “Nay but, O man, who art thou that replies against God? Shall the thing formed say to him that formed it, why hast thou made me thus?” (Rom 9:20)."},{"c":11,"i":60,"x":"All the above is Scripturally reinforced in 1John 5:1 “Whosoever believeth that Jesus is the Christ is born of God.” But “believing” is never the cause of salvation. “Believing” is always an after-the-fact human response that results from being “predestined” to be “born of God.” Thus, God’s salvation is Eternally Secure for “whosoever” has been divinely “born again” but salvation is Eternally Insecure for “whosoever” merely self-generates “belief in Him” by a volitional-free-will decision."},{"c":11,"i":61,"x":"God’s plan has always been for the benefit of “the principalities and powers in Heavenly places” rather than for the benefit of disposable humans who incidentally may be either “redeemed” or “un-redeemed.” “Redeemed” humans are merely incidental beneficiaries of God’s plan by being graciously “adopted” for “everlasting” residence in “Heavenly places.”"},{"c":11,"i":62,"x":"The prophet Ezekiel predicted “being born again” in 36:26 “A new heart also will I give you, and a new spirit will I put within you: and I will take away the stony heart out of your flesh, and I will give you a heart of flesh.” Some theologians argue the context of Ezekiel’s prediction allows only “God’s chosen people” to benefit, nevertheless, God’s New Testament adds detail to Ezekiel’s prediction by “That which is born of the flesh is flesh; and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit” (John 3:6) “therefore, if any man be in Christ, he is a new creature: old things are passed away, behold, all things are become new” (2Cor 5:17). Those verses seem to apply to both “God’s chosen people” as well as Gentiles who are “called and elect” to be divinely gifted with “a new heart.”"},{"c":11,"i":63,"x":"It was “determined before the foundation of the world” (Eph 1:4; 1Pet 1:20) that God- the-Father would supernaturally create natural birth as well as spiritual re-birth."},{"c":11,"i":64,"x":"Some disposable humans will eventually learn they were “called and elect according to the good pleasure of His will” (Eph 1:5). However, only “called and elect” Gentiles as well as “a predestined number of God’s chosen people” will benefit from the divinely provided gift of being “born again of the Spirit” according to God’s Purpose- For-Creation."},{"c":11,"i":65,"x":"The issue of “abolishing the law” forced the Acts 15 council at the Jerusalem church. Luke reports the Jewish challenges were rejected by the council in an epistle written by James to be hand-delivered to the churches established by “Barnabas and Saul/Paul.”"},{"c":11,"i":66,"x":"The document described in Acts 15:23 may have been recorded for modern Christians as the New Testament epistle that bears the name of “James, the brother of the Lord.” The epistle of “Jude, the servant of Jesus Christ, and brother of James” may also be based on that Acts 15:23 document simply because God’s intention has always been for Scripture to explain Scripture thus avoiding even the hint of ambiguity that must be theologically interpreted by conflicted Bible scholars."},{"c":11,"i":67,"x":"Nevertheless, Luke is concerned because “the certainty of those things delivered to us by the Apostle whom Jesus had chosen” is being denied by 1st Century “chosen people” who mutilate God’s immutable Words."},{"c":11,"i":68,"x":"Sincere theological scholars frequently suggest alternative ways to change (i.e., mutilate) God’s immutable Words. Despite the sincerity of Bible scholars, pulpit messages are observed being based on theological mutilations of God’s Words rather than based on an exposition of God’s Words. However, the Biblical requirement for pulpit messages is “the things that thou hast heard of me among many witnesses, the same commit thou to faithful men, who shall be able to teach others also” (2Tim 2:2). It sounds like Paul is commanding preachers to exposit Scripture rather than preach a sectarian approved “understanding” of Scripture."},{"c":11,"i":69,"x":"However, preachers must know “the things that thou hast heard of me” before “those things” can be preached. Thus, Biblical proficiency ought to be a priority – there are no alternatives to Biblical proficiency. Proficiency in counseling (i.e., topical preaching) may offer some benefit to those who lack “trust in the Lord” but proficient counseling skills ought never be an alternative to proficient Biblical exposition."},{"c":11,"i":70,"x":"Theological writings, especially the conflicted writings of sectarian Theophanies of God such as Calvin and Wesley, are never a source for Truth. Theological writings are of value only as added affirmation of local preachers who “trust in the Lord for eyes to see and ears to hear.” The only source for Truth is God’s Literature. The opinions of sectarian Theophanies of God are never a source for Truth."},{"c":11,"i":71,"x":"Luke is concerned because knowing “the determinant counsel and foreknowledge of God” is of more eternal importance to “The principalities and powers” than learning about any sectarian challenges (i.e., “the gates of hell”) to the eternal church being built by Jesus (Matt 16:18)."},{"c":11,"i":72,"x":"Theophilus has observed similar challenges"},{"c":11,"i":73,"x":"Theophilus shares Luke’s concern because modern Bible school trained preachers are observed challenging the beliefs of rival preachers just as 1st Century Jewish leaders challenged “the certainty of those things delivered unto the apostles.” Modern preachers emulate the doctrinal challenges of 1st Century Jewish leaders."},{"c":11,"i":74,"x":"Modern challenges to God’s Words are publicly observable in the form of “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture.”"},{"c":11,"i":75,"x":"For example, modern Bible school trained sectarians devalue John 3 by teaching “anybody can be saved by believing in Him.” I have literally heard Bible school trained sectarians emulate Nicodemus as recorded in John 3:4 by assuming that Jesus was using the metaphor of birth to offer the option of volitional belief to “Whosoever believeth.” But that kind of doctrinal assumption is a devaluing (i.e., a literary corruption) of the message being delivered to Nicodemus."},{"c":11,"i":76,"x":"Jesus responded lovingly and graciously to Nicodemus as well as to modern Bible school trained sectarians by explaining in John 3:5ff that a Sovereign God “Verily, verily” controls “being born of the Spirit” just as God “Verily, verily” controls “the wind.” Both “the wind” and every instance of “the birth process” is “Verily, verily, by the good pleasure of God’s will.”"},{"c":11,"i":77,"x":"I have heard 21st Century sectarian preachers devaluing Scripture by claiming the term “whosoever believeth in Him” is a universal inclusive that invites every human to “believeth in him.” But John 3:16 teaches the exact opposite of the “deception” that salvation is universally inclusive."},{"c":11,"i":78,"x":"For example, baseball fans talk about the exploits of “whosoever” plays baseball for the Cubs but “whosoever is dead” is eternally precluded from playing baseball for the Cubs. Neither can “whosoever is dead in trespasses and sins” (Eph 2:1) make a volitional decision to stop being “dead” by volitionally deciding to “have everlasting life.” The common sectarian doctrine of universal inclusiveness is a “deceptive” academic abuse of the English language."},{"c":11,"i":79,"x":"The linguistic problem with “whosoever believeth in him” is emphasized by the literature of James 2:19 “Thou believest that there is one God; thou doest well: the devils also believe, and tremble.” Sectarians emulate “the devils.”"},{"c":11,"i":80,"x":"My caveat"},{"c":11,"i":81,"x":"All the above was the outcome of simply reading the Biblical Epistle to the Ephesians without any attempt to interpret the meaning. The Apostle Paul reveals the “mystery” that God’s Purpose-For-Creation was to educate “The principalities and powers.” Nevertheless, you may think I have been overly zealous in my Biblical justifications for my book – you may think I have manufactured Scriptural detail to surreptitiously prove my point."},{"c":11,"i":82,"x":"I have literally experienced vehement religious resistance to my claim of Biblical justifications. Thus, I humbly beg you to forgive any accidental polemic you may think you have observed."},{"c":11,"i":83,"x":"Here is the literal reality:"},{"c":11,"i":84,"x":"• Those who agree with me have been led by God to agree."},{"c":11,"i":85,"x":"• Those who disagree with me are also led by God to disagree."},{"c":11,"i":86,"x":"• God sovereignly leads both agreement and disagreement."},{"c":11,"i":87,"x":"God never requires God’s Purpose-For-Creation to be acknowledged. It is conceivable that even preachers who preach a “lie” may have literally been “Born again of the Spirit.” In fact, I “Trust” it to be so. The reality is that God’s Purpose- For-Creation has always been a “mystery” to believers as well as unbelievers. The evidence is that it continues to be a “mystery” despite God’s inspiration in AD60."},{"c":11,"i":88,"x":"The point of this book is that those who either agree or disagree with me are each temporary and disposable educational tools used by God such that God’s Purpose is being accomplished. In fact, “God is good all the time; All the time God is good” even when we vehemently disagree."},{"c":11,"i":89,"x":"I am constantly reminded of Romans 12:3 “For I say, through the grace given unto me, to every man that is among you, not to think of himself more highly than he ought to think, but to think soberly, according as God hath dealt to every man the measure of faith.” I write using the pseudonym Theophilus to disguise my embarrassment about the weakness of my own self-generated faith. All my words have been evaluated by God in Romans 3:4 “God forbid: yea, let God be true, but every man a liar, as it is written, that thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged.” That verse evaluates me as being a “liar” while God alone is “justified in thy sayings.”"},{"c":11,"i":90,"x":"Accordingly, I confess that I am a “liar.” But then, God also evaluates Augustine of Hippo, Jacobus Arminius, John Calvin, Ignatius of Loyola, the current Pope, Joseph Smith, John Wesley, as well as the very best radio and TV preachers as “liars.” God evaluates the leadership of every affiliation of churches as being “liars.”"},{"c":11,"i":91,"x":"And God evaluates that you also are a “liar” despite your agreement or disagreement about God’s Purpose-For-Creation as revealed in this book."},{"c":11,"i":92,"x":"“Leaning unto your own understanding” may be an eternal problem for those who address Jesus as “LORD” but that kind of “understanding” has nothing to do with your “predestined” listing in “the Lamb’s book of life.”"},{"c":11,"i":93,"x":"My caveat is that “leaning unto your own understanding” of that which God really meant to say is of no consequence to God’s gift of “everlasting life.” God graciously “predestines” salvation despite your absurd decision to “lean unto your own understanding” rather than “Trust in the LORD with all your heart.”"},{"c":11,"i":94,"x":"“Believeth in Him” is absolutely required but none of us is saved because of our self-generated belief. “Believeth in Him” is the “predestined” outcome of “your name being listed in the Lamb’s book of life” rather than a sectarian approved method for attaining “everlasting life” by making a volitional free will decision to no longer be “dead in trespasses and sin.”"},{"c":12,"i":0,"x":"The conditions preceding God’s creative effort"},{"c":12,"i":1,"x":"God’s literature is the only source document that can reveal the rationale motivating God to create anything. That document teaches that time-and-space did not exist before God was motivated to create it."},{"c":12,"i":2,"x":"In that regard, Exodus 3:14 identifies God as “I AM.” God was the present tense “I AM” who pre-existed everything in time-and-space. Revelation 1:8 declares “I AM Alpha and Omega, the beginning and the ending, saith the Lord, which is, and which was, and which is to come, the Almighty.” God existed before “the beginning” of creation and will continue to exist after “the ending” of creation. God is eternal."},{"c":12,"i":3,"x":"The names “I AM” and “Alpha and Omega” indicate it is continuously “now” (present tense) where God resides. Thus, God’s rationale or motivation for Creation cannot result from a sequential cause-and-effect. But the Genesis account reveals that everything was created as a sequential cause-and-effect event that occurs in time-and-space."},{"c":12,"i":4,"x":"Thus, God’s rationale for creating must be described metaphorically simply because humans cannot conceive anything that exists outside the sequential cause- and-effect of our time-and-space dimension. For example, the literature of Revelations 4 uses metaphor to describe Heavenly construction materials that simply don’t exist in time-and-space. Things that are indescribable can only be described metaphorically."},{"c":12,"i":5,"x":"Revelation 13:8 uses metaphor to describe those “whose names are not written in the Book of Life of the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world.” The metaphor is written in the past tense for us humans even though there is neither past tense nor future tense where “I AM” resides."},{"c":12,"i":6,"x":"The literature of Isaiah 6 describes “seraphim crying unto each other, and saying, Holy, Holy, Holy is the LORD of hosts. The whole earth is full of His Glory” That obviously describes a future time-and-space testimony because the “I AM” has always been “Holy” but “seraphim” have just discovered that “The whole earth is full of His Glory.”"},{"c":12,"i":7,"x":"Nevertheless, Isaiah 6 describes a real event. Revelation 4:8 describes a similar event except “the seraphim” are described metaphorically as “four beasts.” Each of these descriptions uses metaphor to describe a sequential cause-and-effect event that occurred in a dimension that has no sequential cause-and-effect."},{"c":12,"i":8,"x":"The events are real but each description is metaphorical for the benefit of time- and-space residents whose perception is restricted to observing only sequential cause-and-effect events."},{"c":12,"i":9,"x":"The “I AM” simultaneously observes “the beginning and the ending” of every sequential event that has ever occurred or will occur in time-and-space. More to the point of this chapter, it seems “the principalities and powers” who reside with God “in heavenly places” have that same capability."},{"c":12,"i":10,"x":"If that is true then “The principalities and powers” can observe finished events that time-and-space humans think haven’t happened yet."},{"c":12,"i":11,"x":"For example, “The principalities and powers” viewed the “ransom atonement” being paid by “the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world.” By contrast, time-and-space humans think the “atonement” wasn’t paid until about 2000 time-and-space years ago. “The principalities and powers” have similarly already viewed “The Day of the Lord” (2Pet 3:10) even though time-and-space humans think “The Day of the Lord” is yet future."},{"c":12,"i":12,"x":"The omnipotent “I AM” could have instantly spoken creation into existence within His own Heavenly dimension. But He didn’t. The “I AM” personally describes His effort as a deliberate dragging out of creation over six sequential days of time-and-space cause-and-effect."},{"c":12,"i":13,"x":"Why did God take six days to do that which He could have done instantaneously? I am not theologically trained so I am not credentialed to offer a theologically correct answer. Nevertheless, I observe the question “Why did God take six days to create” is typically ignored by Biblically trained theologians. But I suggest answering that question is critical to understanding God’s Purpose for all His creative effort."},{"c":12,"i":14,"x":"Humans are restricted from viewing either the beginning or the end of time-and- space. However, “the principalities and powers in heavenly places” have already observed both the creation and the final destruction of time-and-space."},{"c":12,"i":15,"x":"Time-and-space Humans observe everything sequentially but “the principalities and powers” have already observed the destruction of creation (2Pet 3:10) as well as observed “the new Jerusalem” (Rev 3:12, 21:2.) Thus, the “principalities and powers” have already viewed the beginning and end of God’s temporary time-and-space case-study. The “I AM” who resides in “the heavenlies” has already accomplished everything He intended to demonstrate by creating a temporary and disposable environment populated with temporary and disposable humans. Please pause reading to meditate on the limitations and restrictions of a temporary and disposable time-and-space environment. The Heavenly perspective of our time-and-space bubble can only begin to be understood after extensive meditation about predicted events that living humans are incapable of either “understanding” or experiencing."},{"c":12,"i":16,"x":"The purpose for God’s creative effort"},{"c":12,"i":17,"x":"Ephesians 3:10 reveals the “I AM’s” Purpose-For-Creation (i.e., “to the intent that…”). The “I AM” has created sequentially executed events. Thus, the Ephesians context requires lengthy meditation. It requires “trust in the Lord with all your heart and He will direct your path.”"},{"c":12,"i":18,"x":"The analysis in this book is my inadequate and fallible attempt to describe God’s elaborately complicated Purpose that He planned in a dimension that exists outside our created dimension of time-and-space."},{"c":12,"i":19,"x":"Each sequential step of God’s time-and-space creation as well as everything that has happened after creation was planned and executed (i.e., “predestined”) “by the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God” (Acts 2:23)."},{"c":12,"i":20,"x":"I admit I was never taught this concept during the first half of my life. Thus, I never taught this concept to my children. The generations of my family have historically been God-believers and we have always claimed to trust God but none of us has ever heard this concept taught by the preachers in the churches we attend. This conceptual explanation of Creation has always been a “hidden mystery” within our religious communities."},{"c":12,"i":21,"x":"However, God has allowed me to read the literature of Ephesians 3:2-10 without “leaning unto my own understanding.” Thus, I was forced to humbly admit that nothing was created for the benefit of us humans. The preamble to God’s Purpose Statement is recorded in Ephesians 3:2-9 “How that by revelation he made known unto me the mystery; (as I wrote afore in few words, Whereby, when ye read, ye may understand my knowledge in the mystery of Christ) which in other ages was not made known unto the sons of men, as it is now revealed unto his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit; That the Gentiles should be fellow-heirs, and of the same body, and partakers of his promise in Christ by the gospel: Whereof I was made a minister, according to the gift of the grace of God given unto me by the effectual working of his power. Unto me, who am less than the least of all saints, is this grace given, that I should preach among the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ; And to make all men see what is the fellowship of the mystery, which from the beginning of the world hath been hid in God, who created all things by Jesus Christ.” Verse 10 reveals “To the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known by the church the manifold wisdom of God.” Thus, everything was created for the benefit of “the principalities and powers” and nothing was created for the benefit of us temporary and disposable humans."},{"c":12,"i":22,"x":"Hebrews 9:27 reveals “it is appointed unto men once to die.” Thus, every human including Adam and Eve was created to die – typically we humans die of old age, however, “the principalities and powers” who reside “in heavenly places” are neither temporary nor disposable like us humans."},{"c":12,"i":23,"x":"Egotistical humans tend to think creation was for our benefit but the humiliating reality is that humans are merely temporary and disposable tools being used by God to accomplish a temporary time-and-space task for the benefit of “the principalities and powers.” Each temporary and disposable human (i.e., you and me) lives for a moment and then we die."},{"c":12,"i":24,"x":"The literature of Scripture is replete with reports of entire populations being destroyed by God’s “wrath.” Noah’s Flood is a notable example. Another notable example is God’s command to Joshua to destroy the disposable nations that populated the “Promised Land.” Those disposable nations were destined for destruction due to their corrupt lifestyle of worshipping “Molech” and sacrificing their own babies to that non-existent god. The “good” God of “wrath” righteously planned for their destruction."},{"c":12,"i":25,"x":"Scripture is clear that “God so loved the world.” But it is also clear that “loving the world” was not a motivating force when temporary and disposable humans like Adam and Eve were judged “thou shalt surely die” even though they had been created and or “born of the flesh” without prior knowledge of either “good or evil.”"},{"c":12,"i":26,"x":"“The principalities and powers” are obviously more important to God than any humans who are created to be temporary and disposable."},{"c":12,"i":27,"x":"The elimination of temporary and disposable humans who challenge God is an extremely obvious cause-and-effect of God’s Plan. In that regard, Theophilus suggests Luke’s observation of 1st Century Christians challenging “the certainty of those things wherein thou hast been instructed” was also according to God’s Plan. It also describes every instance of modern sectarian conflict."},{"c":12,"i":28,"x":"Given the obvious reality that humans are temporary and disposable, why would any modern theologian think that God did all this Creation stuff so that temporary and disposable humans could purchase “everlasting life” by simply making a volitional decision to “believe in Him”? It is incredible that egotistical theologians believe disposable humans are precious even though “God is love.” Please affirm that every disposable human is born to be “dead in trespasses and sin” (Eph 2:1) and is incapable of choosing to do anything at all. Humans especially cannot choose to “believe in Him” (John 3:16). That’s the way an omniscient and omnipotent God planned for everything to work."},{"c":12,"i":29,"x":"Ephesians 3:10 teaches “the principalities and powers” are so important to God that He took 6 days to create an elaborate but disposable world including disposable humans “to the intent that the principalities and powers in heavenly places” could observe “the manifold wisdom of God” as a sequential cause-and-effect activity."},{"c":12,"i":30,"x":"Human participation in God’s time-and-space case study will eventually be complete. The literature of 2Peter 3:10 predicts “But the day of the Lord will come as a thief in the night; in the which the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up.” Peter reports the final step of God’s Plan will be the elimination of God’s entire temporary time-and-space."},{"c":12,"i":31,"x":"However, eternity continues after time-and-space is eliminated. The elimination of time-and-space is mentioned in a song written by James M. Black “When the trumpet of the Lord shall sound, and time shall be no more … when the roll is called up yonder, I’ll be there.”"},{"c":12,"i":32,"x":"God’s graciousness is displayed by God’s creation"},{"c":12,"i":33,"x":"The literature of Hebrews 9:27 teaches that you and I were each created to be disposable. However, “a few” disposable humans have been graciously “called and elect” to be “born again by the Spirit” (John 3:8) to inherit a new Spiritual DNA of “everlasting life.” Those “few called and elect humans” will escape the elimination of time-and-space into an eternity of “everlasting life.”"},{"c":12,"i":34,"x":"Humans who are “called and elect” will benefit greatly because the “called and elect” are divinely protected from “the judgment” of “a good” God’s “wrath” according to “the manifold wisdom of God.”"},{"c":12,"i":35,"x":"“The manifold wisdom of God” ≡ “the Grace of God.”"},{"c":12,"i":36,"x":"“The many” disposable humans who are not “called and elect” will simply get whatever God created them to get – nothing more and nothing less. Satan and his demons are also disposable and will get exactly what they were created to get. “For God so loved the world” that “the world” will get exactly that which a “good” God planned “before the foundation of the world.” Accordingly, it is absolutely true that “God is good all the time; All the time, God is good.” Who are the principalities and powers"},{"c":12,"i":37,"x":"Those who reside in time-and-space are precluded from knowing “the principalities and powers in the Heavenlies.” Nevertheless, it is clear they are not disposable humans."},{"c":12,"i":38,"x":"The only information available to time-and-space humans is that “the principalities and powers” reside where God resides. Angels and Seraphim (perhaps even Satan and his evil demons) may be included in “the principalities and powers” but we can’t be sure because God does not say so."},{"c":12,"i":39,"x":"“The principalities and powers” reside “in the heavenlies” where the sequential cause-and-effect of time-and-space does not exist. Dimensions “in the third Heaven” seem to have some similarity with the created dimension of The Universe but the dimension of “the Heaven and Hell” have always been a “mystery” to time-and-space humans. It is a “mystery” to us simply because we are disposable and don’t need to know all those extraneous details."},{"c":12,"i":40,"x":"The logical implications of cause-and-effect"},{"c":12,"i":41,"x":"Every event within our created dimension of time-and-space is the outcome of a cause. This is true even when the cause is unknown to us mere humans."},{"c":12,"i":42,"x":"Nothing happens that was not caused by God. And every cause results in an event. Random events may be allowed by God in some other dimension but random events do not exist within our dimension of time-and-space."},{"c":12,"i":43,"x":"Randomness does not exist at the sub-atomic level despite the expensive Cyclotron experiments being studied in hope of learning about the Higgs Boson and proving/disproving Heisenberg’s thesis about “The Uncertainty Principle.” Please affirm that an unpredictable sub-atomic event is evidence of scientific ignorance rather than evidence of randomness."},{"c":12,"i":44,"x":"Neither does randomness exist at higher levels of complexity as proposed by Darwin in his thesis titled “The Origin of Species.”"},{"c":12,"i":45,"x":"Studies of biological mutations may have medical and academic benefits but questioning how life originated is evidence of scientific ignorance rather than evidence of random mutations."},{"c":12,"i":46,"x":"Scripture suggests every event in time-and-space is caused by a prior event simply because God uses sequential cause-and-effect to demonstrate “the manifold wisdom of God” to “the principalities and powers in the Heavenlies.” The evidence suggests there was no other reason for God’s creative efforts. Cause-and-effect is essential to God’s plan. By contrast, Cyclotron experiments and evolutionary studies are proposed by humanistic scientists to demonstrate the absurdity that disposable humans don’t need an eternal God. Thus, “Professing themselves to be wise, they became fools” (Rom 1:22)."},{"c":12,"i":47,"x":"Wisdom deficient theologians have neither “eyes to see nor ears to hear.” They agree with humanistic scientists by devising doctrine to teach that humans are capable of volitional free will choices despite any “predestined” cause-and-effect established by God. That explains their foolishness."},{"c":12,"i":48,"x":"For example, typical Christians seem to be aware when a “salvation” event occurs but wisdom deficient humanistic sectarian-created Theophanies of God conflict about the volitional intellectual decisions disposable humans must make to cause a “salvation” event to occur. Sectarian-created Theophanies of God teach the wisdom deficient humanistic doctrine that “salvation” is a volitional free will choice that needs no “predestination” by a sovereign God."},{"c":12,"i":49,"x":"Despite conflicted theological doctrines manufactured by sectarian-created Theophanies of God, the literature of John 1:3 asserts “All things were made by him and without him was not anything made that was made.” Thus, God’s literature seems to indicate that a Creator God could conceivably have veto authority over everything including “All things” about which sectarians are observed to conflict."},{"c":12,"i":50,"x":"Yet, the evidence is that God rarely vetoes sectarian conflict. Nor does God immediately veto debates about “the certainty of” God’s Words. It seems the human sin of questioning “the certainty of” God’s Words as well as all other human sin was planned by “the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God.”"},{"c":12,"i":51,"x":"There is nothing that characterizes the time-and-space Christian religion more than religious conflict. Every sectarian segment of that which egotistical theologians assume to be God’s Universal Church is characterized by conflict with rival egotistical sectarians."},{"c":12,"i":52,"x":"It seems that God planned sectarian conflict to demonstrate “the manifold wisdom of God” to “the principalities and powers” using the cause-and-effect example of local churches being populated by “predestined called and elect” God-believers who sit next to those who were deliberately created to be egotistically conflicted sectarians."},{"c":12,"i":53,"x":"It is intuitively obvious that not every member of a local church is also a member of God’s Universal Church."},{"c":12,"i":54,"x":"Nevertheless, God graciously “calls and elects a few” out of our sectarian churches to be included within God’s Universal Church despite the obvious universal conflict between sectarian rivals. The obvious implications of sectarian conflict"},{"c":12,"i":55,"x":"Theologically created sectarian Theophanies of God are observed teaching that a sovereign God effectively cancels His own sovereign control of cause-and-effect by allowing humans to volitionally cause the population of God’s Heaven to be expanded (i.e., salvation is volitionally acquired). Some of those same sectarian Theophanies of God extend the contradiction by teaching Heaven’s population can be volitionally reduced (i.e., salvation can be lost)."},{"c":12,"i":56,"x":"Those kinds of Biblical interpretations are effectively the Magna Carta of sectarianism – sectarians declare themselves to be free from God’s sovereign control just as the Magna Carta stripped governing control from British monarchs."},{"c":12,"i":57,"x":"True-sovereigns control everything. By contrast, very little is controlled by pseudo-sovereigns. For example, Queen Elizabeth II of England was a pseudo- sovereign who controlled virtually nothing. She couldn’t even control her own family much less control the British Empire."},{"c":12,"i":58,"x":"British royalty is merely a figurehead supported by taxation without representation. As I am writing this paragraph, some tax-supported British royalty (i.e., Harry and Megan) don’t even reside on British soil."},{"c":12,"i":59,"x":"Sovereign control by a British Monarch was stripped by the Magna Carta in 1215. Since then, all decisions have been made by Parliamentary peers."},{"c":12,"i":60,"x":"The common theological concept of Partial-Sovereign-Control is a logical absurdity yet some sectarian-created Theophanies of God attempt to teach that absurdity as if it is their Magna Carta from God’s sovereignty."},{"c":12,"i":61,"x":"Theologians who teach that absurdity are frequently observed contradicting themselves by teaching that God’s Words are preeminent to all other words just as British citizens typically believe the nonsense that they are governed by British Royalty."},{"c":12,"i":62,"x":"Scholars are aware dictionaries define “Sovereign” as “a supreme ruler, especially a monarch” but sectarian theologians inexplicably redefine that definition to limit God’s sovereign control of time-and-space."},{"c":12,"i":63,"x":"The literature of Deuteronomy 4:2 and Revelation 22:18-19 seems to teach it is sin to redefine the meaning of any of God’s preeminent Words. If those verses apply to all of Scripture, then pulpit attempts to explain (i.e., “understand”) Scripture must be done carefully and respectfully to ensure correctness. The risk of incorrect clarification is eternal damnation and yet sectarian clarifications are famous for conflicting with rival sectarian clarifications. Sectarian preachers always conflict with rival preachers. Both sides of that conflict also conflict with God’s Words. Theologians who matriculated at an academically deficient Bible school may be humanly excused for preaching nonsense. But why would an educated theologian claim authorization to clarify (i.e., mutilate) the immutable Words omnisciently inspired by a sovereign God? That kind of educated thinking is the antithesis of “Trusting the LORD with all thine heart.”"},{"c":12,"i":64,"x":"Every theologically motivated clarification of Scripture is an opinionated mutilation of a preeminent text which had been sovereignly inspired by God to be both immutable and inerrant."},{"c":12,"i":65,"x":"Imagine the effect on theological conflict if egotistical theologians would humbly and respectfully pray to a sovereign God to request an explanation of their questions about the meaning of His inspired Words."},{"c":12,"i":66,"x":"Think about how the Christian life would appear if Christians would humbly relinquish the absurdity that sectarian theologians control the meaning of God’s Words. Think how the Christian life would appear if Christians would humbly pray “not my will but thine be done”?"},{"c":12,"i":67,"x":"“Theological-Interpretation” is the cause and “Pulpit-Conflict” is the effect when egotistical theologians usurp control from a sovereign God by choosing to “lean unto their own understanding” rather than humbly and respectfully “trust in the Lord with all their hearts.”"},{"c":12,"i":68,"x":"Following is a list of questions intended to demonstrate the futility of theologically sectarian interpretations"},{"c":12,"i":69,"x":"• Why did an God create Adam even though He omnisciently knew they would"},{"c":12,"i":70,"x":"sin?"},{"c":12,"i":71,"x":"• Why does God tell us that Cain martyred Abel?"},{"c":12,"i":72,"x":"• Why does God tell us about “The Flood”?"},{"c":12,"i":73,"x":"• Why does God reveal the gross disobedience of “God’s Chosen People”?"},{"c":12,"i":74,"x":"• Why does God tell us about “His only begotten Son” being crucified?"},{"c":12,"i":75,"x":"• Why doesn’t God just “forgive” us and then declare “it is finished”?"},{"c":12,"i":76,"x":"• If God “is not willing that any should perish” then why does everyone perish?"},{"c":12,"i":77,"x":"Answers are de facto when God’s Purpose is recognized."},{"c":12,"i":78,"x":"My credentials to summarize God’s plan"},{"c":12,"i":79,"x":"You don’t need a theological education to analyze the Literature of Scripture. Anyone who can read is credentialed to analyze the Literature of Scripture."},{"c":12,"i":80,"x":"I was taught to read as an adolescent in the early grades of elementary school. Therefore, I have those credentials. You are reading this book so it is obvious you also have those credentials. My summary of the Literature of God’s plan is in the next chapter titled “The conclusion of this book.” Please read that chapter to see if my summary agrees with your summary."},{"c":13,"i":0,"x":"No one cannot improve on the wise conclusion God inspired to be written by Solomon. Solomon records that inspired conclusion in the form of a “command” in Proverbs 3:5-8"},{"c":13,"i":1,"x":"Trust in the LORD with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own"},{"c":13,"i":2,"x":"understanding. In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths. Be"},{"c":13,"i":3,"x":"not wise in thine own eyes: fear the LORD and depart from evil. It shall be health to"},{"c":13,"i":4,"x":"thy navel, and marrow to thy bones."},{"c":13,"i":5,"x":"During the first half of my life, I was taught that the Proverbs are merely suggestions about that which God believers ought to obey. That kind of interpretation was also taught to apply to Proverbs 22:6 “Train up a child in the way he should go: and when he is old, he will not depart from it.” Parents of unruly children frequently claim they have done all they could do to “Train up their unruly child in the way he should go.” However, that is an appeal to nonsense because even the best parents can always do a better job."},{"c":13,"i":6,"x":"But my observation of the evidence is that sectarian Christians who teach that the Proverbs are merely generalities rather than guaranteed outcomes are frequently the same Christians who have children who have in some sense “departed from God’s Truth.” It is common for those who have wayward children to claim that they have done everything they can be expected to do but their free-willed children have somehow disobeyed despite their parents’ very best effort to train their wayward children."},{"c":13,"i":7,"x":"It is common for guilty humans to want to blame someone or something other than themselves. That is exactly what Adam and Eve did when confronted by God in Genesis 3:19-13"},{"c":13,"i":8,"x":"And the LORD God called unto Adam, and said unto him, Where art thou? And"},{"c":13,"i":9,"x":"Adam said, I heard thy voice in the garden, and I was afraid, because I was naked;"},{"c":13,"i":10,"x":"and I hid myself. And the LORD God asked, who told thee that thou wast naked?"},{"c":13,"i":11,"x":"Hast thou eaten of the tree, whereof I commanded thee that thou shouldest not eat?"},{"c":13,"i":12,"x":"And Adam said, the woman whom thou gavest to be with me, she gave me of the"},{"c":13,"i":13,"x":"tree, and I did eat. And the LORD God asked the woman, what is this that thou hast"},{"c":13,"i":14,"x":"done? And Eve said, the serpent beguiled me, and I did eat. Modern sectarians emulate Adam and Eve’s technique for “passing the buck” when they teach the nonsense that Satan was an effective force who prevailed against God by causing Eve to commit sin."},{"c":13,"i":15,"x":"However, if Satan is capable to prevail against God at the beginning of time, then it would be utter nonsense to believe God can prevail against Satan at the end of time. And yet that is exactly what many wisdom-deficient Bible scholars seem to believe and teach."},{"c":13,"i":16,"x":"What is your own interpretation of the importance of the 1st half of Proverbs 3:5 that states “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart.” Do you think that statement is literally God’s command or is it God’s suggestion? I ask the same question about the 2nd half of Proverbs 3:5 that commands “Lean NOT unto your own understanding.”"},{"c":13,"i":17,"x":"As of AD60 the epistle to the Ephesians has informed modern humans about why God created anything. That information is written “to the intent that now unto the principalities and powers in heavenly places might be known BY THE CHURCH the manifold wisdom of God” (Eph 3:10). Accordingly, every pulpit message must recognize that every CHURCH is nothing more than a gathering of humans who are metaphorically identified as being either “tares or wheat.” And every “pastor teacher” who offers “dead tares” the option of choosing to no longer be “dead” by simply “believeth in Him” is guilty of a wisdom deficient “leaning unto his own understanding” rather than “trusting the LORD with all his heart.”"},{"c":13,"i":18,"x":"The conclusion from reading this book is the responsibility of each reader no matter how sincerely you address Jesus as LORD and no matter how sincerely you claim the accuracy of your conflicted belief system. A sovereign and omniscient God has “predestined” everything to happen the way God wants it to happen."},{"c":13,"i":19,"x":"Do you really think God want you to read and trust the published commentaries and study helps written by Bible scholars who conflict with rival Bible scholars who also publish commentaries and study helps?"},{"c":13,"i":20,"x":"Does your preferred “pastor teacher” “Trust in the LORD with all his heart?” or does your preferred “pastor teacher” “lean to his own conflicted understanding” about that which sectarian approved commentaries and study helps say?"},{"c":0,"i":0,"x":"This book is dedicated to my wife, family, and friends because they sincerely want to believe Bible school taught “pastor teachers” correctly interpret Scripture. However, without exception, “pastor teachers” are being taught by Bible school professors to hermeneutically interpret Scripture in a way that conflicts with the hermeneutics taught by rival Bible school professors. That also seems to explain why pulpit messages tend to be Christian preaching that devalues Scripture."},{"c":0,"i":1,"x":"Bible school taught “pastor teachers” homiletically teach church attendees to “lean unto hermeneutical understandings written by God believing but conflicted theologians” rather than “lean not unto your own understanding” as Proverbs 3:5 commands. Thus, typical church attendees hear only Christian preaching that devalues Scripture."},{"c":0,"i":2,"x":"My wife and I were each reared to believe the doctrines taught at conservative Bible schools. Thus, we taught our children to believe those same doctrines even though those doctrines conflict with the doctrines taught by rival Bible schools. The spouses of our children also believe doctrines taught at conflicted Bible schools. Our family is characterized by faith in God as defined by a conflicted hermeneutical understanding of the Christian Faith. Each in our family is involved in church ministries that hermeneutically conflict with other church ministries while simultaneously claiming to “Trust in the LORD with all thine heart.”"},{"c":0,"i":3,"x":"God’s Words that were inspired to be written in Ephesians 3:3-9 report that God deliberately “hid” His Purpose-For-Creation as a “mystery” before “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.” That reality is the basis for this book that questions why Bible school taught belief systems always result in sectarian conflict? This book attempts to answer that “mysterious” question."},{"c":0,"i":4,"x":"It seems the Spiritual leaders of every Bible school disobey God’s inspired Words by “leaning unto their own understanding about that which God really meant to say” rather than “Trusting in the LORD with all thine heart such that God will direct thy path.” That also seems to explain the reason why “In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth.” That “mystery” is the basis for this book titled “Christian preaching that devalues Scripture.” It is a philosophical axiom that knowing WHY anything happens is always more instructive than knowing WHAT may have been historically reported as happening."}]};